{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 3309688, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Athelios", "body": "As others said, to make it spawn you need to kill [npc=159901] by stepping over them. If you want to make this process faster, you can use [item=168419] and [item=172063]. The food will give you speed each time you step on one of the little spiders, and the mount equipment will prevent slows from the big spiders. After a couple of rounds in the area, you should see the message from ravenomous announcing its spawn.", "date": "2021-03-18T19:19:01-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 5215707, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "yvesicle", "body": "I managed to trigger Ravenomous to spawn by killing one of the patrolling elite Boneweaver Rampagers after about 15 minutes unsuccessfully squishing the critter spiders.", "date": "2021-07-07T19:46:12-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}}
