{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 1437984, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nethris", "body": "[b]Short fight tactics, updated for live and for heroic[/b]\n\n[b][i]TL;DR version: DONT STAND IN THE FIRE[/i][/b]\n\n3 phases and a transition phase in between. 4th phase in heroic only.\n\nPhase 1\n\n-Switch tanks every 3 debuff stacks.\n-Dont get hit by hammer or its lava waves.\n-Trigger lava traps when you can afford it.\n-Dont clump up.\n-Dont get knockbacked in to lava.\n\nTransition 1\n\n-Kill adds before they reach hammer. Closest ones first. Use knockbacks & stuns. Death grip also works.\n\nPhase 2\n\nSulfuras Smash remains from Phase 1, lava traps and knockback are gone.\n-Split raid on both sides of room, empty in middle.\n-Dont stand in Engulfing Flames\n-When Ragranos uses Molten seeds, move to the center, pop survivability cooldowns and aoe until the adds that spawn are dead. During second seeds, you will get Sulfuras Smash at the same time. Easiest way to deal with this is to go close to the edge of Raggy's pool and the smash will simply go over you.\n\nTransition 2\n\n-Kill adds before they reach the hammer, just like in transition 1.\n-2 big adds spawn in addition to smaller adds. Burn these while moving them around, if you get the debuff, move anywhere where ANY of the adds are not moving towards.\n-Small adds > Big adds.\n\nPhase 3\n\nSulfuras Smash and  Engulfing Flames will remain from previous phases.\n-Living Meteors will spawn continually, which follow players around and kill them (and anyone nearby) if they reach them. Attack the meteors to knock them back. Split the raid in half like in p2 and knock the meteors toward the middle. Once there are too many meteors, start kiting them if needed.\n-If the meteors hit lava waves, [i]something [/i]happens to them. As far as I know, its only for the sake of the achievement.\n\nHeroic:\n\nP1:\n\n-Similar to normal. Time magma traps carefully to prevent any deaths.\n\nTransition 1:\n\n-Same as normal, except different spawn locations (?). The more death grips/typhoons etc. you have, the better.\n\nP2: \n\n-Easiest way to handle Molten Seeds is to group up in mid, wait for them to start flying in the air, then have EVERYONE move away. No one takes damage, all the seeds are clustered, but timing is crucial. Simply aoe/typhoon them down afterwards. If not working, simply single target them down. Will take longer though.\n-Engulfing flames comes 4 times in a row for 3 seconds at each part, stand near the edges everytime to prevent unneeded damage/deaths.\n\nTransition 2:\n\n-Same as normal/transition 1, remember no failing with the debuff! If possible, keep one son of flame up while you kill scions. \n\nP3: \n\n- Heroism either as soon as raggy comes up or after scions are dead. Same as normal + the new engulfing flames. \"Chill time\" before P4 considering tactics. HUGE dps requirement. 140 seconds to go from 40->10% to avoid extra living meteors from spawning. If Scions are still up when raggy comes back, only cleave them down. All DPS needs to focus rag.\n\nEdit: With the nerfed HP, you can hit P4 with just one meteor. Much easier in 10man than in 25.\n\nP4:\n\n-Designate at least 2 (3rd can be a melee backup. Only one in 10man) players to extinguish dreadflames as soon as they spawn, do NOT let them spread. Cat druids with passive movement speed ++ They cast faster and faster the longer you stay in P4, acting as a soft enrage. Handle them as long as you can, at the end dont bother trying to keep the whole room clear, simply have a path to the next Breadth of Frost and a clear zone where your raid needs to be.\n-Create groups that stand on the edges of breadth of frost. Max 8 players per group (should be 7. Thats for 25, 10man is ez), triangle style on the edges. You should never see Magma Geyser.\n-Once a second Breadth of frost spawns, kite a living meteor to the first one, kill it and quickly move the next Breatdh.\n-When Empower Sulfuras casts, have your current tank kite raggy to the entangling roots.", "date": "2011-06-09T17:45:32-05:00", "rating": 95, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Also to add on, if anyone on the quest chain for [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=71086]Dragonwrath[/url], this fight is even harder, as that player and all around them take a large constant damage from [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=101228]this[/url].  Edit: Sorry about the double-post with the comment right below me.", "creationdate": "2011-08-09T20:38:22-05:00", "id": 257664, "rating": 29, "commentid": 1437984, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sfangcleaveftw", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-09-15T08:19:30-05:00", 12, "Nethris"]}
