{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 1512449, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "805867", "body": "After looking through my World of Logs list, it seems that Wrath of Ragnaros, his single target knockback, doesn't target any melee classes that are in melee range. This means melee can effectively stack which helps out healing a bit.", "date": "2011-09-07T22:18:26-05:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Only in phase 1 though and 3 though. In phase 2 when seeds are spawning if the melee are stacked on each other and don't react quickly enough they'll take massive splash damage from everyone elses seed and most likely die.", "creationdate": "2011-09-08T11:46:29-05:00", "id": 263255, "rating": 9, "commentid": 1512449, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rygol", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 1514382, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sas148", "body": "Those of you pursing the acquisition of [item=71086]; please note, while on Phase 3 of the quest line requiring you to use [item=71085] to collect 250 Smouldering Essence, you will not be able to acquire any from Ragnaros.  There isn't a body to harvest the essence from on normal difficulty and even on heroic (where there is a body after defeating him), it won't allow you to do so.", "date": "2011-09-10T03:30:42-05:00", "rating": 39, "indent": 0, "roles": 258, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-05-14T00:10:12-05:00", 3, "Sas148"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 1523287, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "nater131", "body": "Hotfix 9/20\r\nRagnaros' health and damage have been reduced by 25% on normal difficulty.\r\nRagnaros' damage has been reduced by 15% on Heroic difficulty.\r\nMagma Trap damage has been reduced on all difficulties.\r\nThe health and damage of additional enemies in this encounter have been reduced by 25% on normal difficulty and 15% on Heroic difficulty.\r\nWrath of Ragnaros now knocks targets up, but not back, on normal difficulty.", "date": "2011-09-20T19:30:08-05:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 1528754, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Podima", "body": "Please note that [spell=98237] has an interrupt component - if any caster is within the melee AOE range (extends out quite far - if you have a hunter pet, watch where they stand to attack and stay behind them), their non-instant spells will be interrupted when this goes off and they'll be locked out of that school for 5 seconds. This can be somewhat disastrous for healers.\r\n\r\nDBM has a timer for this spell as well, so you can move when it's coming up if you feel the need to stay closer. You should be roughly in the back half of the platform, around 25-30 yards from the tanks.", "date": "2011-09-27T10:48:16-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 1531597, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Eillesthis", "body": "As a Survival Hunter, I've tried to be thorough and test CC abilities on the [npc=53140] during the transitions.  Most of the things I have tried do not even make them blink:\r\n[spell=13809]\r\n[spell=1499]\r\n[spell=19503]\r\n[spell=5116]\r\n[spell=19386]\r\nMonkey's [spell=90337]\r\n\r\nSo far the only thing I've found that does work is a\r\nWasp's [spell=56626]\r\nwhich means a\r\nBat's [spell=50519]\r\nwould almost certainly work as well.\r\n\r\nNot only does it seem just to be stuns (as others have said), Effect: Apply Aura: Stun is not enough, it has to be Mechanic: Stunned.", "date": "2011-09-30T12:27:51-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 1536311, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "citrique", "body": "Heroic is a somewhat different encounter than normal, especially after the rather sweeping nerfs to the normal version.\n\nOur guild ended up 3-healing the 25-man version of the encounter for a kill.\n\nPhase 1 is mostly the same. The major differences are that detonating a Magma Trap causes everyone in the raid to receive a Magma Trap Vulnerability debuff which causes them to take 50% additional damage from detonated traps for 45 seconds. What this means is that you cannot detonate a trap for 45 seconds afterward, causing you to slowly accumulate additional traps that will persist after the phase has ended. Ideally this number will be as close to 0 as possible, in our case it was 1.\n\nWhat we did was had ranged DPS mostly stay on the left side of the boss along with the tanks, with melee on the right so they could DPS the boss from behind and avoid parries. A couple ranged (with legendaries) stood behind the melee on the right. A shaman healed the melee group solo. When the third and fourth traps were about to be cast, ranged DPS would venture towards the back of the platform to cause the trap to spawn there, then move back in so Hand of Ragnaros could not knock them off. The trap(s) which persists beyond phase 1 needs to be placed as close to the edge as possible so it is avoidable and out of the way for subsequent phases. If it is placed close enough to the edge of the platform, it can be ignored for the remainder of the fight.\n\nDPS in phase 1 is primarily focused on pushing the transition before you get a fifth trap. Otherwise DPS doesn't matter an awful lot and a focus on survivability is best taken.\n\nDuring the P1-P2 transition, the major difference is that Sons of Flame reaching the hammer will instantly wipe the raid upon detonation (400K damage or so) and they have a huge amount more health. We assigned Death Knights to grip Sons closest to the hammer on the \"long\" side of a split (hammer to the left or right) with moonkin/ele shaman knockbacks for the \"short\" side. The transition phase is the roughest for healers with lots of random damage from Lava Bolts. Tranquility was used to catch up at the end of the phase before Rag re-emerged.\n\nDuring Phase 2 the major differences are that Molten Seeds/Elementals work differently. Elementals gain a buff which causes them to be immune to CC and do more damage, and they gain an additional instance of this buff for every other Elemental which is within a few yards of them. Therefore there are two ways to deal with these - the raid spreads out very far apart and each player deals with their own add where it spawns, or the raid stacks up and moves as one large group just before the Seeds land, then AOEs the adds down after they spawn before they reach anyone. We used the latter method for 25-man, the former method is more viable for 10-man. Ragnaros will cast \"World in Flames\" after every add wave, which works like the Heigan Dance. It's best for players to stand roughly inbetween where the bands of Engulfing Flames can spawn so their movement is minimized to avoid this.\n\nWe blew our one extra trap up after the first Engulfing Flames of P2 was done and covered it with Spirit Link.\n\nDPS on Ragnaros himself is most important in Phase 3. When Ragnaros casts World in Flames, he is unable to cast any other abilities or do a phase transition. Therefore, what we did was we slowed DPS around the 44% mark and waited for him to do another seed/add wave (the third). After killing the adds, we then got him as close to 40.6% (the mark where he submerges) as possible and waited for him to start casting World in Flames. When he starts this cast, you have the entire 9 seconds of him casting it to burn as much of his HP as possible, then he will start the submerging dialogue and you will have another 8 seconds of DPS before he goes under. Doing this can shave 5-6% off of his health which is damage you do not need to do in phase 3.\n\nThe second phase transition is the same as the first in regards to Sons and Lava Scions. The goal here is to kill both Scions before Ragnaros re-emerges. Any Sons of Flame which are still alive after he re-emerges will detonate regardless of where they are after 3 seconds. What we did was we would leave one Son alive while burning the Scions down, then kill the Son just as he re-emerged. Ideally both Scions will be dead as he re-emerges.\n\nPhase 3 works the same as normal aside from World in Flames. The ideal goal in this phase is to have as few meteors as possible, thus P3 being a DPS race. Our goal was 1 meteor. We burned the boss and used Bloodlust after the first World in Flames cast ended. When the meteor spawned, Death Knights knocked it back away from the raid so that it could be ignored as much as possible during the phase. When Ragnaros reaches 10% health, he cannot cast any other abilities (including summoning more meteors) and all damage done to him will reduce the amount of health he starts with in phase 4, so he should be burned until submerging.\n\nThere is a ~15 second window between P3 and P4 where Concentration Potions or other abilities that would be otherwise dangerous can be used.\n\nNote that as P4 starts, you CANNOT approach the boss until his legs appear coming up from the ground, if you run towards him before this you will fall in the lava and die.\n\nPhase 4: When the Druid NPCs spawn, they freeze any meteors on the platform. These should be knocked back to the edge. Ragnaros will then emerge from the lava starting at 50% health minus whatever you were able to knock off below 10% of his HP before he submerged. The raid should assign 3 main positions where groups of 7 people will stack in a triangle around Breadth of Frost to avoid Molten Geysers forming. Any player who gets Fixate from a Meteor at this point will need to kite it around the outside of the raid for as long as possible before knocking it away and returning to the raid stack to drop their Superheated stacks. Players returning must move straight in towards their group and not try to come in sideways between two groups as this can trigger a Geyser and wipe the raid. When the second Breadth spawns, the raid moves to it, and the player with Fixate will bring the meteor into the first Breadth where it will become frozen and can be killed. It is imperative that this Meteor is killed, Meteors that become frozen take 50% more damage and should die within a few GCDs.\n\nRagnaros himself will channel \"Empower Sulfuras\" causing any melee attacks he does to do 500K damage to the entire raid. A warrior tank is rather ideal here. When the Entrapping Roots spawn, the tank must wait for Ragnaros to start channeling his Empower cast, then must move to the other side of the roots so the boss walks into them and is stunned before being able to melee with this buff. Stunning him / kiting him causes the Empower buff to fall off. Heroic Leap, life grip, Stampeding Roar / a swiftness potion are best used here so the tank can accomplish this. The remainder of the phase is repeating this while Dreadflame extinguishers (classes that can do a lot of damage on the move such as Hunters, or classes with high movement speed such as feral druids/shamans) work to keep paths clear around Breadth and roots spawns. The \"enrage\" is running out of room on the platform due to Dreadflame spreading.\n\nThe major factors for downing this boss are\n\n- High DPS from everyone in P3/P4\n- Minimize damage taken from Engulfing Flames\n- Good positioning\n- Good RNG with P4 spawns", "date": "2011-10-06T08:45:44-05:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-10-06T08:53:54-05:00", 1, "citrique"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 1536324, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "citrique", "body": "Also for Death Knights:\r\n\r\n[item=43672]\r\n\r\nWorks when using Death Grip on a Living Meteor, making us the best class to deal with knocking these back.\r\n\r\nNote that ANY player ability used on a meteor will knock it back and cause it to change target. This includes any taunts, Wind Shear, applying Curse of Elements, or anything else.", "date": "2011-10-06T08:57:13-05:00", "rating": 26, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Nice to know that taunt affects it. When my warrior gets geared enough Ill remember this.", "creationdate": "2011-12-09T16:23:35-06:00", "id": 494915, "rating": -2, "commentid": 1536324, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sanga27", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 1539368, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "GeneralK", "body": "[b]just a few tanking tips for Rag[/b]\nthis is a 2 tank fight.\n\neach time u are tanking him he'll periodically cast burning wound on you. this is a mild dot that slowly ramps up damage around 3-4 stacks. at this time your other tank should swap.\n\np1.5 : for sons of flame paladin tanks can glyph holy wrath and stun 2 adds at the same time..bursting a son down to 50% then using hammer of justice to stun the other one beside you. it is imperative for pally tanks to have holy wrath glyphed as its a huge asset. save your shield of righteous 3 holy power for a son and blast him away.\n\nphase 2: \nburning wound from phase 1 continues, taunt accordingly\nmost groups will mark a left side and right side like X and Square where the entire raid will stack. when molten seeds hits the raid be sure to strafe left or right (depending on direction but keep urself facing rag so u dont get critted or owned) (if u are uncertain or slightly rusty in this u can pop a CD on each molten seed kiting) \nu do not need to hit rag  as u run across if that makes it easier to strafe.\n\n[u]for engulfing flames - *** really important *** if engulfing flames spawn right beside ragnaros melee range.. be sure u run out but stay on the very edge so rag can still melee you. this will prevent him from 1shotting other melee( its difficult to master but entirely possible).\n[/u]\n\n\n\nphase 2.5 (lava scions and sons)\nthis gets slightly trickier but heres how most groups do it.\nif u end up on the left side pickup the left scion and the 2 sons .  if u are on the right side pickup the right scion and the 2 sons.\n\nthe scion spawns about 2-3 seconds before Sons do so u have time to fire avenger shield at it before dispending with the sons of flame adds. this is the trickyest part of the fight for tanking normal.\n\nonce both scions die its basically a tank and spank while avoiding the meteors. good luck to all of you.", "date": "2011-10-10T01:49:07-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-10-10T01:50:28-05:00", 1, "GeneralK"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 1542596, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Drag0nsAng3l", "body": "For those wondering what the 4th phase abilities, buffs and debuffs are:\n[spell=100915] is the stacking debuff\n\n[spell=100503] is the debuff you get when standing in the [spell=100503] (used by [npc=53872]), this makes the stacks of [spell=100915] drop.\n\n[spell=101015] is the buff you get when utilizing [spell=100766] (casted by [npc=53875]). This allows the extinguishing of [spell=100675]\n\n[spell=100646] is the spell used by [npc=53876], into which [npc=52409] needs to be dragged to stop [spell=100628] from killing the raid.", "date": "2011-10-14T09:16:35-05:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-10-14T09:18:32-05:00", 3, "Drag0nsAng3l"]}
