{"commentv2": 1, "number": 74, "id": 3224342, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "itsnotemy", "body": "It looks like there were multiple bugs with Ragnaros not spawning after killing all bosses in the raid, so now Ragnaros spawns as soon as you enter the raid. Thought it was funny to hear his welcome speech as soon as you pop in the instance. It actually has a cooler feel tbh.", "date": "2020-08-20T02:19:40-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 75, "id": 5245504, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "deepspace8", "body": "Why doesn't this list his loot?  It shows one thing.  He drops plenty of other stuff.  I got the Pureblood Fire Hawk mount from him off 25-man normal and was trying to find out the drop rate.  I've ran this many times before, though.  I'm exalted with the faction.", "date": "2021-09-01T07:22:56-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 5220156, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Akori", "body": "To get the Pet you'll need to access a \"hidden\" vendor in the second room of the instance. \r\nRight after the first boss you'll run down the stairs to the right and the shopkeeper is in the right corner.\r\nOnce there he will trigger a dialog [small]\"Psst! Hey you. Unassuming visitor. Do you like small creatures?\"[/small]\r\nTarget the shopkeeper and write [b]/yes[/b] and the interraction will trigger the ability to trade.\r\n\r\nTo purchase the pet you'll need 2143g and [item=180532], [item=180533] and a  [item=180522].\r\nIf you're lucky you'll already have them. In my case I went for pickpocketing and got them all within 3 hours.\r\nThe Oxxein Lockbox can be found  in Maldraxxus, the Solenium in Bastion and the Phaedrum in Ardenweald. \r\n\r\nVideo: https://youtu.be/Qo-T2RSQptE", "date": "2021-07-13T09:34:51-05:00", "rating": 25, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Exact NPC is called Shopkeeper at 68.79, 39.78, which as you go down the steps and turn right is in the north-east corner of that area. I had to write /yes to his same question three times before he became a vendor with the pet", "creationdate": "2021-07-14T16:17:45-05:00", "id": 1501515, "rating": 6, "commentid": 5220156, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Trojanhorse", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I can confirm I had to run back and forth and target with /yes a few times before the vendor option became available.", "creationdate": "2021-08-21T15:12:00-05:00", "id": 1508810, "rating": 3, "commentid": 5220156, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "taima7700", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 5263037, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "babybad06", "body": "It took me about 3 hours as well to pickpocket the lockboxes.  My rouge was only level 51, but was able to fly to each of the zones with twist of fates on.  In Maldraxxus I tried various mobs across the zone while eventually getting one off a [url=https://www.wowhead.com/npc=159757/necromancy-acolyte]Necromancy Acolyte [/url] after about 45 min.  Next I went to Bastion, where it took about 2 hrs before I got one of a [url=https://www.wowhead.com/npc=157599/forsworn-acolyte]Forsworn Acolyte.[/url]  Lastly, I went to Ardenweald and got lucky within 15 min getting one off a [url=https://www.wowhead.com/npc=159415/brittlebark-trickster]Brittlebark Trickster[/url] (they may have a low drop rate, but high density).  I sent the lockboxes to my main toon, went into the dungeon with a group to clear past the 1st boss, and went to the vendor.  It took a min before the Shopkeeper whispered me, but once they did I actually did a /nod and could purchase the pet from them.  The lockboxes were still locked, though I don't believe that matters.  Good Luck!", "date": "2021-10-04T20:04:30-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2021-10-04T20:07:52-05:00", 5, "babybad06"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 144, "nreplies": 13, "sticky": 0, "user": "2950", "body": "I wonder why there's no loot table here yet. Even Anub'Rekhan from Naxxramas has a loot table.", "date": "2006-09-13T02:54:04-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Ragnaros is a very easy and fun fight for ranged dps. Starting from right off the bat you can dps him down. After 3 minutes he drops down and his sons come up. You then run to the collapse spot your guild shows you and it helps if you FD and lay a frost trap to slow them/entrap if you have the talent. After you guys get the sons down you resume your dps on him until he dies. And as a ranged dps you dont need too much FR, I have done it with 100, but its nice to have between 100-150. Bring plenty of arrows too because your dps really counts.   Here is a more detailed explanation of the entire f", "creationdate": "2006-09-13T02:54:05-05:00", "id": 285962, "rating": 45, "commentid": 144, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "shaman", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "That is just so wrong. Ragnaros was one of the Elemental Lieutenants of the Old Gods *in Azeroth*, after their defeat at the hands of the Titans he was banished to the Elemental Plane and then summoned by the Dark Iron Dwarves.", "creationdate": "2008-03-22T17:06:47-05:00", "id": 28909, "rating": 37, "commentid": 144, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "83142", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "We're talking about the elemental lord of fire. A creature of pure mana and fire. A creature who waged war against the titans when the world was young. Him, and all his elemental allies were banished to another plane where they still wreaked havoc on the mortal world. A monster of unimaginable power. A power that dwarfs Kil'Jaedan or Illidan.  And he's a ranged character's bitch now. Its sad. Once the symbol of raids all across the game. Now an afterthought, not even a memory to most players. Just a monster that is joked about on rare ocassions.", "creationdate": "2008-08-26T03:28:06-05:00", "id": 44544, "rating": 42, "commentid": 144, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "193663", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well, this is merely Ragnaros' corporeal form. Not ONLY is it only a portion of his might (Much like Kil'jaeden) he was summoned too soon by Executus. So this Ragnaros is a weakened, tiny piece of Ragnaros' full power. His true form lies within the Elemental Plane.", "creationdate": "2009-01-30T13:23:39-06:00", "id": 76634, "rating": 34, "commentid": 144, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "65244", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vPt1bckqJmU&feature=related    [b]Never Forget[/b]", "creationdate": "2009-02-12T00:03:49-06:00", "id": 79544, "rating": 44, "commentid": 144, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ahea", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 3026, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Odinn", "body": "Ragnaros is the final boss in Molten Core, the original 40-man dungeon crawl-style raid instance.  He drops all of the \"Tier 2\" armor set leggings, as well as several other highly-sought items.\r\n\r\nThere is some disagreement about the approach to this boss, largely brought about by discrepancies in gear, but, generally speaking, you will need a well-balanced, fairly well-geared raid group, and they will need a respectable amount of Fire resistance.", "date": "2006-11-06T14:02:47-06:00", "rating": 123, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 4547, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "3118", "body": "In my experience, precision Sons of Flame control yields a kill.  Make sure everyone understands the strategy for that.  \r\n\r\nThe sons are basic level 60 elites.  Immune to fire but nothing else.  Slowing, freezing, fear, horror, silence, and taunt effects all work. Hunter ice traps, frost nova, and challenging shout are all key to any Son control.", "date": "2006-11-26T03:38:04-06:00", "rating": 53, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, if you can keep the sons under control without letting them burn  a lot of mana, you will have a much greater chance of success.", "creationdate": "2006-12-18T22:52:16-06:00", "id": 286370, "rating": 4, "commentid": 4547, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Chaosangel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 6651, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "7049", "body": "The Molten Core lies at the very bottom of Blackrock Depths. It is the heart of Blackrock Mountain and the exact spot where, long ago in a desperate bid to turn the tide of the dwarven civil war, Emperor Thaurissan summoned the elemental Firelord, Ragnaros, into the world. Though the fire lord is incapable of straying far from the blazing Core, it is believed that his elemental minions command the Dark Iron dwarves, who are in the midst of creating armies out of living stone. The burning lake where Ragnaros lies sleeping acts as a rift connecting to the plane of fire, allowing the malicious elementals to pass through. Chief among Ragnaros' agents is Majordomo Executus - for this cunning elemental is the only one capable of calling the Firelord from his slumber.\r\n(Lore from the official World of Warcraft website)", "date": "2006-12-05T18:27:04-06:00", "rating": 79, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 6725, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "7073", "body": "Ragnaros is the Final Boss in Molten Core, below is a website that is very helpful at explaining the difficult fight: http://pacifistguild.org/ragnaros/", "date": "2006-12-05T19:30:13-06:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 7957, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "7121", "body": "His loot table consists of..\r\n\r\nAll class Tier 2 Leggings (Transcedance/priest, Bloodfang/rogue, ten storms/shammy, netherwind/mage, nemesis/warlock, wrath/warrior, stormrage/druid, dragonstalker/hunter, judgement/paladin)...\r\n\r\nand other goodies..\r\n\r\nNot a hard boss to kill really.. for beginning guilds, tank should have 315 fire resistance, but its a tank and spank fight.", "date": "2006-12-06T21:05:04-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 9365, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "kane", "body": "Melee Players should have Min 200 FR and range should have 100-150 FR. I do say min as doing it well but you could have less and still take him down.", "date": "2006-12-07T18:59:59-06:00", "rating": 30, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Going to say that if you're in a pre-BC guild, or raiding it on your 60, no more than 150 is needed as a main tank, and even less for ranged.", "creationdate": "2009-02-07T02:26:29-06:00", "id": 386614, "rating": 0, "commentid": 9365, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "223769", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 9427, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "8198", "body": "As a hunter, it is actually best if you wear as much DPS gear as possible. FR gear is hardly needed as hunters take the fewest AoE fire balls and also have (for the most part) the most HP of the ranged damage dealing classes. Well, except for warlocks. Anyway, if you can push the DPS charts you will be much more useful in Rag attempts/kills and let the other classes worry about surviving. We have feign death.", "date": "2006-12-07T19:22:04-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not quite....   sure, you will do slightly less damage if you aren't in your Tier 1 armor, but if you are dead, you aren't doing any DPS.", "creationdate": "2006-12-08T17:32:21-06:00", "id": 286062, "rating": 4, "commentid": 9427, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "8876", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 11571, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Binary", "body": "It's very important (especially for newer guilds) to dps as much as possible.\r\nAssigned healers need to keep the dps alive at all costs, and all ranged dps should begin their attacks from very start of the fight and never let up, as range cannot gain aggro with a melee target within Rag's reach.\r\nThe sons do drain mana, so if you're a class that can kite the sons,  do it. Priests fear, mages blink, etc.\r\nA good goal is to have Rag at 30% before he submerges for the first time.", "date": "2006-12-08T17:18:00-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 11580, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "8952", "body": "Rag can be a very tough fight if your strat consists of certain elements. Chances are if you are a beginning guild you will die a few times.\n\nOur strategy has been to have a challenging shout rotation for all the warriors with FR when the sons come up, and watch for the knockback, other than that its a piece of cake.", "date": "2006-12-08T17:23:40-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 11854, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "8403", "body": "With the release of the 2.0 patch, I believe Rag has become much easier.  Not that he was nerfed, but that the classes were over all largely improved.  In personal experience with my own guild, just last weekend we were only able to get Rag to about 40% before we wiped.  That was the best we could do at the time.  Only one week later, nearly all the same gear, but brand new talents, we managed to get him to 10% before the sons were even summoned, the sons were killed within one minute, and Rag fell as though he were no more difficult than Golemagg.  These new talents are definitely a help, so if your guild hasn't attempted Rag since the patch, and you've been trying to kill him for weeks, I suggest you give it a go ASAP.  You may be surprised at the difference and improvement.  =D", "date": "2006-12-08T23:23:33-06:00", "rating": 49, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "With only 1 million hit points... This guy is probably 5 manable with BT gear. XD", "creationdate": "2007-11-15T23:09:39-06:00", "id": 316735, "rating": -2, "commentid": 11854, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Foxpaw", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 14785, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "9631", "body": "We used to use the aoe taunt tactic when the sons came in for the warriors to control the sons and then aoe them. But indeed since the 2.0 patch we don't need it. He just goes down before sons....", "date": "2006-12-13T09:43:56-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 17156, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chaosangel", "body": "Ragnaros is the first real \"gear check\" in endgame raiding (except maybe Bloodlord Mandokir and having tank with a lot of defense).  Downing him is a significant achievement for any guild mostly because it shows that they are willing and able to farm for fire resist gear and greater fire protection potions en masse.", "date": "2006-12-18T22:55:43-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 17236, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "7293", "body": "Yes, he is the 1st target to really bring down in a raiding guild, requiring collective effort and perseverance. One could say that Raggy makes or breaks raiding guilds. He provides training for the basic skills to face BWL and AQ40, and further down the line Naxxramas.", "date": "2006-12-19T07:50:15-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 57490, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "17843", "body": "The Lords of Vengence, Damage Inc. , and another guild downed Rag on Blade's Edge. What sucked was this it dropped TWO I repeat TWO Leggings of the Ten Storms, I mean, after all that, it drops Shammy gear! WHY!?\r\n\r\nThat is all, we spanked him with only five people dying because they ran into the lava like idiots. -.-", "date": "2007-03-26T11:41:05-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 106218, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "51712", "body": "Has anyone tried raggy since TBC came out? like with a lvl 70 group? I'm just curious, because i wanna try taking my guild through for fun one day, and i'd like to know how many people we';d need", "date": "2007-06-17T22:21:10-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "In our last attempt, we had one tank, two priests and a paladin healing, and about 15 DPSers.  We dropped Ragnaros before the first wave of sons.  Note that you will still want your tank in full Fire Resistance gear, to prevent the knockbacks.  Other than that, everyone should have enough health in their level 70 gear that FR is not needed for everyone else.", "creationdate": "2007-06-17T22:40:10-05:00", "id": 301937, "rating": 0, "commentid": 106218, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Aeryn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "10 i guess i managed to solo the first trash mobs with 3 players, 1 tank, 1 dps and 1 healer.", "creationdate": "2007-08-09T09:56:24-05:00", "id": 308060, "rating": -1, "commentid": 106218, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "10891", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
