{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 405720, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "169612", "body": "Ragnaros isn't the hardest boss Pre-tbc , its someboss in Naxx ( dont know wich one for sure)", "date": "2008-10-14T11:24:50-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "4H wasn't hard, it was a gear+stupidity check.  C'Thun pre-nerf and post nerf was hard.  Pre nerf it was impossible, both with skill and mathematically. I remember the #$%^ing match in the R&D forum(that's raid and dungeons before blizz changed the name) over it.  Post nerf it was still so difficult, that guilds would farm all the content upto clearing the trash, then goto Naxx, because it was easier.  Not only did you need to spend forever clearing trash, but once you got to the boss.  Looking at it wrong generally meant your guild was going to spend an entire night wiping their face with the", "creationdate": "2008-10-14T11:24:51-05:00", "id": 417790, "rating": 11, "commentid": 405720, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "elilla", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "im going to go with the four horsemen. the likes of which went 7 weeks of attempts before a world first kill. still hold that record to this day.", "creationdate": "2008-10-17T08:31:03-05:00", "id": 51106, "rating": 7, "commentid": 405720, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "106152", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I've got to disagree with you there, Four Horsemen was certainly a difficult fight to execute, but its difficulty wasn't the reason that it took so long to beat. The only reason that the Four Horsemen hold that title is due to the ridiculous gear requirement it had. People had the execution of the fight down in the first couple of weeks, they just didn't have the 8 tanks with 4pc Dreadnaught.", "creationdate": "2009-01-22T01:33:18-06:00", "id": 74509, "rating": 9, "commentid": 405720, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "128688", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote]Looking at it wrong generally meant your guild was going to spend an entire night wiping their face with their asses.[/quote]  Feels like your current level 85 runs where some naive fool will stand in the doorway, and get a \"look\" from C'thun which will in all probability kill someone.", "creationdate": "2011-02-27T10:35:19-06:00", "id": 228723, "rating": 2, "commentid": 405720, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ithuraen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
