{"commentv2": 1, "number": 38, "id": 551515, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "213712", "body": "Now does it still require the water to summon him?", "date": "2009-01-07T13:41:27-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Next patch (3.0.8), the essence won't be needed to summon him anymore.", "creationdate": "2009-01-09T11:38:57-06:00", "id": 71460, "rating": 5, "commentid": 551515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "170332", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "if we dont need the essence to summon him,then how we can summon him?  need answer please", "creationdate": "2009-01-20T23:16:09-06:00", "id": 382182, "rating": 1, "commentid": 551515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "rehaili", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The bosses' runes are doused when you defeat them.", "creationdate": "2009-01-22T01:32:48-06:00", "id": 382531, "rating": 0, "commentid": 551515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "128688", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Defeat Majordomo and he'll summon Rag", "creationdate": "2009-01-23T09:51:38-06:00", "id": 382868, "rating": 0, "commentid": 551515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "medina", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Once all other bosses (minus Ragnaros ofc) have been killed, Majordomo Executus will automatically spawn.", "creationdate": "2009-01-24T07:08:10-06:00", "id": 383118, "rating": 0, "commentid": 551515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Lighter", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 557915, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "301983", "body": "Before TBC expansion he was very hard boss and it took time to beat him\r\nIn these day he is easy may he hasnt good rate drop but the items,weapons and armor are pretty good for  lvl 57-62", "date": "2009-01-11T13:43:23-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I wouldn't say this is true. Once you learn the fight and gather enough buffs, he was quite easy. After my guild's second kill of him back in the days(we hadn't even killed Razorgore by then), we managed to get him down before the first submerge.  Back then you could stack as many elixirs as you wanted to, and if nobody died and melee was careful not to get knocked back, he would go down pretty fast", "creationdate": "2009-01-25T14:21:25-06:00", "id": 75419, "rating": 2, "commentid": 557915, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Returner99", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 573013, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tadzulempke", "body": "Now that we don't need any Quintessences, do we still have to defeat Majordomo Executus to reach Ragnaros?", "date": "2009-01-21T10:49:03-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "yes, just did the MC run. We must defeat Majordomo and then we need to go where Ragnaros appears when summoned. You will find Majordomo there, talk to him and he will summon Ragnaros, no quest/water or anything else needed.", "creationdate": "2009-01-22T14:10:14-06:00", "id": 74577, "rating": 3, "commentid": 573013, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "lovelywaz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The water never had anything to do with Ragnaros himself. Once all the runes are doused, Majordomo will appear to investigate. Once he realizes that he'll get killed(when all of the adds are down), he'll surrender and go summon Ragnaros.", "creationdate": "2009-01-25T14:23:21-06:00", "id": 75420, "rating": 2, "commentid": 573013, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Returner99", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 586062, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Crowax", "body": "A few days ago, we were running old raids just for fun. We were 2 mages,  a priest and my pally tank.\r\n\r\nRagnaros is summoned automatically after defeat of Majordomo Executus (he appears after all other bosses are dead). I didn't know about the knockbacks (didn't play vanilla xD). I felt so useless in the fight... \r\n\r\nAlso Executus was hillarious...we got his adds oom as we were unable to kill them before they heal themselves :D\r\n\r\nWhole MC is soloable now by a class that can take a few hits - if you know what to do. Like firedemon said. You just have to be in raid group to enter.\r\n\r\nPS: confirmation code 'dotmm'...locks are coming back!", "date": "2009-01-29T02:52:18-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-29T02:53:08-06:00", 1, "Crowax"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 42, "id": 586287, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "301983", "body": "Ragnaros is the lord and ruler of all fire elements,so, a NPC there summons him and then Ragnaros execute him with a single attack\r\n\r\nTo fight ragnaros it will be good tanks have hight fire resistance cause of every single attack he deals FIRE damage\r\n\r\nRagnaros have a spell that summons NPCs called son of ragnaros and you have to killed them quickly or maybe the entire raid go wrong.Be carefull of \"Wrath of Ragnaros\" he knocks players back and if they threw to the lava they will die especially TANKS.\r\n\r\nGood luck and now go fight him", "date": "2009-01-29T07:28:36-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 593616, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "calvin95376", "body": "You can solo all the trash if you can take a few hits but not the bosses. There may be one or 2 that are possible, but with a Druid tank and Priest Healer we went through and cleared every boss includeing Ragnaros.", "date": "2009-02-03T08:04:48-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Sorry, that's just plain wrong.  As a resto druid, I solo'd every [b]boss[/b] on MC. I may have used feral offspec on one or 2 of them, but just to make it faster.  It all comes down to know how to use your items/professions/skills.", "creationdate": "2009-09-08T11:53:49-05:00", "id": 120939, "rating": 9, "commentid": 593616, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "246648", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
