{"commentv2": 1, "number": 123, "id": 1292336, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Bethek", "body": "Trying to solo him as a prot warrior, can be abit of a challenge.\r\n\r\nSince you're the only one in melle range, he'll knock you back/up now and then, meaning you've got to either charge/intercept to not get thrown back into the lava.\r\n\r\nCould always use a parachute cloak too, but since that's got a minute c/d and he'll use the knockback more often than that, spamming charge/intercept is needed, else you go splat on the way down :(", "date": "2011-01-13T16:16:09-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 124, "id": 1297648, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "726951", "body": "I just did him as an 85 Death Knight, average 342 ilevel DPS gear and blood tanking spec. The key to this fight, for me, was positioning. Success or failure hinged on avoiding fall damage, as it seems to for most classes. To that end, I used glyphed Path of Frost and I always made sure I had a frost or death rune up for when he was going to knock me back - this helped with some of the falling damage but the most important part was standing in the right place.\n\nThe right place to stand, for me, was exactly south-east  of him, perhaps 1 or 2 feet from the lava pool he is in. That way, when I was knocked back I would always land on the rocky outcrop behind me. Out of the whole fight (maybe 5 knockbacks?) I took falling damage twice, which ended up being 20k a time (health pool of 130k). When he was at 23k HP left over the sons came, which were no bother with heart strike.", "date": "2011-01-17T11:00:14-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "85 Blood DK, mainly 333 gear with Zin'Rokh sword, solo'd Molten Core start to finish.  Ragnaros was very easy, there is an even easier way, rather than use a rock outcrop to land on as mentioned above, position yourself so that there is a large expanse of lava behind you, Ragnaros will use knockback on you many times during this fight and the fall damage can be hefty.  I took on fall damage and decided it wasnt going to work, moved and subsequently landed in the lava each time without fail (very easy to position yourself for this, was South of Ranaros on the map and back positioned so I did NO", "creationdate": "2011-01-17T11:00:15-06:00", "id": 477280, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1297648, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "pudsley", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-01-17T11:01:00-06:00", 1, "726951"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 125, "id": 1301986, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tech23", "body": "Soloable by a fury warrior in regular dungeon gear as of cataclysm release.  I had 336 average item level.  Glyphed blood thirst, and when he knocked me back i used intercept every time.  I averaged 6-7k dps.  sons came up around 20% and i used cleave / whirlwind to dispatch them.", "date": "2011-01-20T15:35:52-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-01-20T15:38:28-06:00", 1, "Tech23"]}
