{"commentv2": 1, "number": 131, "id": 1339792, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "494229", "body": "Soloed as a 85 prot warrior. Wiped 5 times before seeing a previous post here showing the [url=http://img100.imageshack.us/img100/8962/placement.jpg]best spot [/url]to tank him. Thanks mate!\r\n\r\nStaying there you will always land on a lava pool, avoiding the falling damage. After landing I swam as fast as I could, spamming charge, so I would get back to Ragnaros in little time. That's also important cause his ranged attacks were hiting me for 5,4K.\r\n\r\nThat's pretty much everything. Use your cooldowns wisely. If you don't have it already, make a healing macro using Last Stand, Berserker Rage and Enraged Regeneration (and Healthstone, Health Potion if you have those available, always nice for pvp situations). I activated mine when my life went down to 60% and again by the end of the fight.\r\n\r\nHave a good farming!", "date": "2011-02-17T12:42:54-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 132, "id": 1341601, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "naiohme", "body": "just solo'd as a 85 protection paladin. it was extremely easy once i realized where you should tank him. There's a spot where when you get knocked back you'll land in lava instead of taking fall damage on the ground. hope this helps.", "date": "2011-02-18T22:26:01-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 133, "id": 1341810, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kahzria", "body": "Getting cocky with your super-awesome level 85 and teaming up with your equally cocky level 85 tank boyfriend and taking this guy on is probably not the best idea.  I'm guilty of it...and I had the repair bill to show for it.\n\nWarcraft safely, people.  Bring a friend.  \nHe's a heckuva lot easier than he used to be...But he's still a BAMF.  =)\n\nEdit:   Forgot to mention that if you can avoid the fall damage altogether by finding \"that spot\", you'll be okay.  Otherwise, see above.", "date": "2011-02-19T04:21:43-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You've managed to find 'that spot'? Won't the ladies be happy!", "creationdate": "2011-04-13T23:52:39-05:00", "id": 237721, "rating": 16, "commentid": 1341810, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kasa24", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "She's definitely right - getting cocky is not a good idea.   I thought that since the level was so far below mine that I could take him on as a Frost mage and kept getting interrupted everytime I was knocked back from him.  Referenced this 'spot' she was talking about the second time, though, and didn't have that problem...but still died.  (Though not nearly as fast.)  Brought a Prot Warrior along with me, we both stood in that one magical area and he went down nice and easy.", "creationdate": "2011-11-22T17:03:34-06:00", "id": 279438, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1341810, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "915180", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-02-19T04:23:19-06:00", 1, "Kahzria"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 134, "id": 1345554, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "792455", "body": "Ragnaros the Firelord is an incredibly powerful Elemental Lord and master of all fire elementals. He rules over his minions from deep inside the fiery core of Blackrock Mountain. It is possible for two handed mace wielders to obtain a mortal-sized copy of his weapon, [Sulfuras, Hand of Ragnaros].", "date": "2011-02-22T01:40:37-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 135, "id": 1346682, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ignite", "body": "Managed to solo him without too much trouble on a furry warrior with crafted 339 pvp set and a couple BOE 333 2h maces wasn't too tough. I try to make it as easy as possible by eliminating the need to fight him in a position that requires somewhere to land I just sure that I had the \"Skirmisher\" talent with causes your intercept to be on a 20sec CD instead of 30. With that just make sure you have the rage for it around the timer and I spam it and charge back down as he knocks me away and continue to beat on him. Might record it next week when i do him again if people are interested. Good luck!", "date": "2011-02-23T00:26:14-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 136, "id": 1347988, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "LordSothe", "body": "http://media.mmo-champion.com/images/news/2011/february/ragnaros2.jpg\r\n\r\nTWO SHOES! YOU HAVE GIVEN ME TWO SHOES, EXECUTUS! WHAT IS THE MEANING OF THIS FOOTWARE?", "date": "2011-02-24T05:40:14-06:00", "rating": 107, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "lol!", "creationdate": "2011-02-24T23:47:10-06:00", "id": 479748, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1347988, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tripfel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ragnaros has feet?!? 0.o", "creationdate": "2013-02-15T21:18:06-06:00", "id": 633045, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1347988, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Shoadowolf", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ever been so angry that you grew LEGS!?", "creationdate": "2013-05-29T10:38:17-05:00", "id": 663710, "rating": 13, "commentid": 1347988, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tyerr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Core Forged Greaves, right? the only shoes he drops?", "creationdate": "2016-08-12T16:43:47-05:00", "id": 959755, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1347988, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ikechi", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 137, "id": 1355995, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "782722", "body": "I just finished soloing him on a level 85 hunter, ilevel 340. I've never even done that raid before. I recently tried to solo it a few weeks ago. But after a couple bosses I was simply too tired to finish. But I digress.\r\n\r\nAnyways, I didn't even know the fights. But it was still a cake walk to one shot every boss. I did most of the raid with a worm pet. But I used a spirit beast on Ragnaros. I probably didn't need it, but I was wearing my T5 as well.", "date": "2011-03-03T06:10:32-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 138, "id": 1357988, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "785993", "body": "Solo'd it with my enhancement shaman 85 (ilevel 342) Patch 4.0.3\r\n\r\nWas only helping a guy kill the last boss of BRD but then out of curiosity (just started playing wow midway through wrath) wanted to know how that raid was. Since I didn't know how the raid worked, took me a while to get to him.  Cant say it was the easiest fight, due to the ridic amounts of knock backs, I pretty much had to use greater healing wave every time I had 5 stacks of maelstrom do to the 350 faceplants I had during the battle. \r\n\r\nAt the end he droped some purples and [item=1973]", "date": "2011-03-05T04:39:05-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 139, "id": 1363437, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "157502", "body": "Soloed as a lvl 85 fury warrior with ilvl 328. If you have the talent skirmisher it will reduce the CD on intercept to 20 seconds and you will always have it up for the knockback. Having rage for it shouldn't be a problem, but just make sure you have 10 rage almost all the time and you're safe.\r\n\r\nI popped my reck and death wish at the start of the fight and didn't drop below 60%. Good luck!", "date": "2011-03-10T18:15:44-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 140, "id": 1364483, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "wintermadness1", "body": "How easy is Rag to solo at 85? I'm melee, and I know that although his health is no problem at all, some fights have mechanics that you simply can't get around with one person. Is there anything like that?", "date": "2011-03-11T21:53:56-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I soloed him very easily as a frost mage, I believe no melee class will have a problem as long as you can heal yourself through the fight. The only trouble is the knockback, be sure to have a lava lake on your back when you get thrown or you will end up dying from fall damage. Other than that you should have enough dps to kill him before he submerges and summons the ads.", "creationdate": "2011-03-13T19:03:53-05:00", "id": 481375, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1364483, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Chromell", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can position yourself so when he knocks you back, you land in the lava. The only thing he does that can get close to killing a level 85 is the fall damage from the blast.  I doubt there is a dps class that [i]can't[/i] solo him at 85, he was, and still is, a relatively simple encounter.", "creationdate": "2011-03-14T12:11:57-05:00", "id": 232183, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1364483, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LeminaAusa", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 141, "id": 1368197, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "squirrel3333", "body": "def cake as an 85 feral druid as long as you make sure to feral charge / skull bash (if feral charge is on CD) when you get the knockback.", "date": "2011-03-16T05:53:40-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 142, "id": 1372073, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "moopert", "body": "Easy as an enhancement shaman, use ghost wolves and earth elementals to be in range of the knockback so you can duck out and not get hit.", "date": "2011-03-20T19:43:04-05:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 143, "id": 1377464, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "697870", "body": "Here is a video of [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=11502]Ragnaros[/url] vs my level 85 Blood Death Knight http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jSzh5zQ1S48.\n\nThe video does not show the entire fight, but it does show where I think a good place to stand is (worked for me)\nso that when you get knocked back you land up on a rock which does significantly less damage vs landing on flat ground.\n\nIf you are an engineer you can avoid fall damage for some of the fight (or if you are fortunate enough for Ragnaros\nto hit you less than once per 30 seconds than it would work for the entire fight) if you use a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=10518]Parachute Cloak[/url] which has only a 30 second cooldown.\nAlso if you use the cloak try to click on it when you get close to the ground instead of as soon as possible.\nWhen I clicked on it as soon as I was up in the air I would drift back quite a ways and it takes a long time to\nrun back.", "date": "2011-03-27T11:38:10-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-03-27T15:52:51-05:00", 6, "697870"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 144, "id": 1388463, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "wikholm", "body": "[url=http://i53.tinypic.com/1z3q9np.jpg]Stand here to avoid fall dmg[/url]", "date": "2011-04-10T14:51:07-05:00", "rating": 54, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is a perfect spot, found the same through wowwiki and came to post the image, but found this one better. If you stand in the middle of that little \"alcove\" you'll get knocked back straight into lava, I didn't go below 99% health at any time during the fight (85 blood DK ilvl 383) due to falling damage or anything else. Thanks wikholm!", "creationdate": "2012-05-10T14:22:42-05:00", "id": 542605, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1388463, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "517885", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 145, "id": 1398701, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Thatguy45", "body": "Level 84 blood Dk, easily soloed.  You can avoid fall damage if you position yourself right.", "date": "2011-04-24T17:36:43-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 146, "id": 1398877, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Majiktusk", "body": "Just soloed as a level 85 prot warrior. The most important thing to remember is to position yourself with you back to the giant lava pool so a mistake will not mean instant death. But as a warrior, a small mistake can make the difference between a kill or a wipe. When he knocks you into the air, be sure to spam your charge button so you will not take any damage from falling or his ranged attack (which hurts a lot). If you can get the charge down, its a DPS race. Once you get him to 20% and you can use Victory Rush, its all over.", "date": "2011-04-24T23:53:24-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
