{"commentv2": 1, "number": 153, "id": 1427749, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kazzo", "body": "[b]I can solo whole MC with my affliction warlock.\nLet me explain how to solo Ragnaros! (this might work for hunters to)[/b]\n\nThe thing is with Ragnaros, is that he goes down in the lava [submerge, is what it's called on DBM]\nWhen he does that he goes down and you can't dps him. Then he starts summoning Sons of Flames these come with eight at a time. The first time I tried Ragnaros he got me there.\n\nSo now we know what can kill us (you can also survive this, don 't get me wrong but my technique might work way better). So now we know our biggest threat.\n\nThis is how it works:\n\n- Before you start the event, set your pet next to Executes. He will be our tank [I use a voidwalker]\n\n- Also in the outer ring, place you portal down. I will explain this later.\n\n- Once started you want this to do:\n\n* Keep your pet alive [mine didn't even needed healing, but it might do]\n* Use teleport when Ragnaros knocks you back\n* Pop [b]ALL CD[/b]'s in this fight, but why? We want to kill him [u]before[/u] he sumberges! So you got about 3 minutes and and a few seconds to kill him. We use the portal to safe us time. Sometimes you don't get knock backed at all but I didn't figure out why not.\n\n[b]After 2 mins loot him and be proud![/b]\n\n[i]Note: Yes you can kill him in about 2 mins. Instead of portal you could stand in the lava but if you are using life tap often that can be a problem. Hunter can use disengage instead of portal![/i]", "date": "2011-05-26T03:46:47-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-07-05T05:15:14-05:00", 5, "Kazzo"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 154, "id": 1436411, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Octapulse", "body": "If you're having trouble finding the 'sweet spot' where being punted won't result in fallback damage, it's quite feasible at 85 to just sit in the lava and cast at him. His Magma Blast does around 4k, and you take spell pushback and 500 damage every few seconds from sitting in the lava... that's measly compared to the possible 70+k damage you can take from fall damage if you're punted badly.", "date": "2011-06-07T14:22:30-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
