{"commentv2": 1, "number": 200, "id": 1988981, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "FreelancerMerc", "body": "On November 17 2014 (WoW's 10th anniversary) There will be a [b]max level[/b]-[i][b]LFR[/b][/i] version of  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=2717/molten-core]Molten Core[/url] most likely separating Molten Core in wings (like all LFR editions of raids). \r\n\r\nBy killing [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=11502]Ragnaros[/url] in the Max level-LFR edition you will be awarded with a [url=wod.wowhead.com/spell=170347]Core Hound mount[/url].\r\n\r\nThe Molten Core LFR will be available for the entity of WoW's 10th anniversary (November 17-December 1) and to people who log within that period of time, you will also get a free [url=http://beta.wowhead.com/item=115301]Molten Corgi[/url] battle-pet.\r\n\r\n(During the anniversary a [url=http://us.battle.net/wow/en/blog/15107686/gearing-up-to-celebrate-10-years-of-world-of-warcraft-8-6-2014]PvP Event[/url] is also included that will remind you of the good old days)\r\n\r\nI don't know if they are revisiting the bosses in order to change the abilities but I doubt since Blizzard is trying to bring this old school feel back for a little. I will keep this post up-to-date with any new information we get on our hands.", "date": "2014-08-06T16:56:23-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
