{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 809349, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "184466", "body": "A note to every ele shaman, boomkin, and to a lesser extent, hunters: these mobs seem to have [u]fairly high nature resistance[/u]. My elemental shamans damage is much lower than it should have been on these mobs, and when I checked combat log (even with 20 spell penetration) a lot of spells were being partially resisted.", "date": "2009-08-12T16:01:24-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "All boss-level mobs have an inherent partial resist rate that cannot be overcome, even with spell penetration (this even affects the Holy school). You are incorrect in your assumptions.  From Wowwiki: [i]\"Note that this formula renders level 83 bosses as having 15 magical resistance against level 80 player attacks. Unlike all other magical resistance in the game, this resistance from level difference cannot be overcome by spell penetration.\"[/i]", "creationdate": "2009-08-20T12:39:21-05:00", "id": 117410, "rating": 1, "commentid": 809349, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "AudreyChandler", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The dps drop you experience Rayleke. Is no doubt the dps loss that I am pretty sure everyone suffers from not have buffs from other classes. At least this is how I have resolved this dps for myself. I experience it on every toon and liberally add X amount of dps for all situations that this comes up in.", "creationdate": "2011-12-22T05:09:27-06:00", "id": 500112, "rating": 0, "commentid": 809349, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "265489", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 813723, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hullken", "body": "If I'm not misstaken they now instantly regain their health up to 100% once they hit 1 hp.\r\n\r\nThis is great for everyone that have a tallent/tier-bonus that does a dot spell based on your crit damage. For example mages have ignite, hunters have piercing shots, dk's have blood-baked strikes and so on. And when this things occur on dummies with 1 hp they get a not so nice damage reduction because you actually only hit for 1 damage and the rest is overkill and therefor ignite or other such spells also ticks for 1 damage instead for a % of the shown damage.", "date": "2009-08-16T16:23:29-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The health replenishment seems entirely random and does not occur as soon as it hits 1 HP. From my experience, as long as someone keeps attacking it, the dummy will remain at 1 HP indefinitely (or for a very long time, at least).", "creationdate": "2009-08-20T12:33:34-05:00", "id": 117408, "rating": 0, "commentid": 813723, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "AudreyChandler", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Its gains 50% of its hp every 20 minutes regardless of mortal strike type effects. It also appears to heal for 300 every 5 seconds.", "creationdate": "2009-09-25T02:11:46-05:00", "id": 124162, "rating": 0, "commentid": 813723, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "FlailofFury", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-08-16T16:28:06-05:00", 2, "Hullken"]}
