{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 857676, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Fjobben", "body": "One question, if you are recounting your DMG on this dummy, do damage-increasing effects from other players, not in your group, who are also hitting the dummy help you?", "date": "2009-10-02T12:11:53-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "IF the other player is debuffing it, your numbers may be skewed.  Example: My shammy is slapping it for 100 dps with zero crit %, and a paladin walks up and smacks the dummy with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=20337]Heart of the Crusader[/url], thanks to this debuff, I now have 103 dps, since slapping crits for double damage and I gained 3% crit.", "creationdate": "2010-05-28T13:51:47-05:00", "id": 165589, "rating": 1, "commentid": 857676, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nazeka", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
