{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 2373990, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "JammerCZ", "body": "If you main Alliance like me and used your 100 boost thinking you could quickly grab these items... you're in luck!\r\n\r\nHilderic has it right, however you can also go through the scenario. When you get to the docks, DO NOT hand in the quest. What I did instead was to log out. The next time I logged on I was greeted with a quest notification... for the Broken Shore!  Accept the quest and you can safely drop the \"first\" Broken Shore quest. You may need to log back in after this to get the phasing to work correctly, but it did work for me.", "date": "2016-08-27T00:15:18-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 2380859, "nreplies": 10, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mauria", "body": "Still available in Legion! For those of us who had already run past this vendor and onto the boat without knowing we were missing out, I have good news: From the character creation screen, there is a 'trial' character option. I created a random hordie, used the hearthstone in her bag which was set to Orgrimmar, sent her the required gold from an alt, then sent her back outside where Ravika was happy to sell her a few treasures. After learning them, I thanked my little random toon for her service and sent her back to the nether.", "date": "2016-09-01T16:45:32-05:00", "rating": 112, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes! Thank you! This works perfectly!", "creationdate": "2016-09-03T15:20:52-05:00", "id": 967403, "rating": 5, "commentid": 2380859, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "dangerfox", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "As of 9/8/2016 She is still out there selling everything. I tried this on a character that had not accepted or started the Broken Isle quest, I didn't even accept the warchief quest that auto pop ups. I just X'd out of it.", "creationdate": "2016-09-07T23:30:13-05:00", "id": 971697, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2380859, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "scarlocke", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "can't up this enough, thank you. Still works as of 7.1", "creationdate": "2016-10-27T05:39:53-05:00", "id": 1001682, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2380859, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rokondrius", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This needs to be upped more. Holy hell. You just took me from \"incredibly upset\" to \"YAY!\"", "creationdate": "2016-10-27T22:40:29-05:00", "id": 1001994, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2380859, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Antikytheria", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Upvoting because you made my anger disappear! :D", "creationdate": "2017-07-10T03:19:39-05:00", "id": 1062170, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2380859, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "insatiable7", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 2406136, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "BananaInc", "body": "If you're like me and went purely Alliance-sided, you can still easily obtain this! As of now, there is not a limit on the number of active 100 trial characters you can have (Or at least not a restriction on two 100 trials). Simply put:\r\n[ol]\r\n[li]Made a level 100 trial orc[/li]\r\n[li]Used my hearthstone when I spawned which by default is set to Orgrimmar to dodge the Broken Shore[/li]\r\n[li]Relogged once I got to Orgrimmar which then gave me the quest chain for the Broken Shore scenario[/li]\r\n[li]Did the scenario and the whole quest chain up to getting the trinket from Sylvanas. With all of the gear I earned through the quest chain, I sold them off for the gold since I only started out with 10.[/li]\r\n[/ol]\r\nAfter I got enough gold to buy everything I needed, I logged out, made a second trial character (Don't delete the first trial account for obvious gold reasons), did the same steps 2 and 3, and mailed all of the gold I earned on my first trial to my second.\r\n\r\nWith this, I was able to buy the shoes and three toys from the gold from the gear in the quests even though all of my characters are part of the Alliance. Cheers!", "date": "2016-09-18T01:40:23-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The post before you said the exact same thing.", "creationdate": "2016-10-27T13:29:51-05:00", "id": 1001820, "rating": -9, "commentid": 2406136, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Purgatorywolf", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "There is a faster way without multi-char creation I have posted on this page also.", "creationdate": "2016-10-31T04:45:08-05:00", "id": 1003434, "rating": -1, "commentid": 2406136, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Netimerin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 34, "id": 2414242, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "raethgir", "body": "As an Alliance player, I didn't have a high level character for this or anything. I haven't tested any low level characters either really. But I discovered I could create a trial character, port to Orgrimmar with Hearthstone, grabbed new legion quest, mailed the trial character gold, and then the trial character bought the items and added them to my account toys. I afterwards deleted said trial character and still had the toys in my toy box.\r\n\r\nFor anyone looking for an easy way to get this stuff that don't necessarily play horde. /kudos", "date": "2016-09-25T15:47:16-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The post before you said the exact same thing.", "creationdate": "2016-10-27T13:29:22-05:00", "id": 1001819, "rating": -9, "commentid": 2414242, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Purgatorywolf", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 35, "id": 2435489, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hakaisha", "body": "If you missed this NPC with your Horde character and only had one at the level?\r\n\r\nThen I got the solution for you, make a trial level 100 horde character, wire over 50g, heartstone to ogrimmar, and go buy it, and then it is yours for all time.", "date": "2016-10-27T04:06:40-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The post before you said the exact same thing.", "creationdate": "2016-10-27T13:29:04-05:00", "id": 1001818, "rating": -8, "commentid": 2435489, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Purgatorywolf", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 36, "id": 2437941, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Netimerin", "body": "[b]If you only have Alliance chars, read me![/b] - [u]This is valid as of 7.1.0![/u]\nHere is an easy way to get these toys NO existing gold or Horde Characters Required\n\n[b]Prerequisites:[/b]\nA 'Battle' Pet of level 10 or above\n\n[u][b]Step 1:[/b][/u]\nCreate a \"Trial\" Horde Character. I selected Orc to ensure I would hearth to Orgrimmar and would have the additional reputation for discounts\n[u][b]Step 2:[/b][/u]\nVendor everything you can (Including the 4 bags) \n[u][b]Step 3:[/b][/u]\nFly over to [npc=63626] and he will have a quest which will send you to battle [npc=66126].\n[u][b]Step 4:[/b][/u]\nUpon arrival to fight Zunta (Remember you get given a flying mount!) he will have a daily quest. Accept the quest and quickly beat his level 2 pets\n[u][b]Step 5:[/b][/u]\nBuy your toys\n\nThe total gold aquired from vendoring the items and beating the 2 pet quests in one fight should be approx 52g give or take. The toys, at their full cost, should cost 50g - remembering that we are getting a discount and I ended up getting them all together for 38g\n\nI tried this thanks to Mauria's Post [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=113615/ravika#comments:id=2380859]Here[/url].", "date": "2016-10-31T04:41:27-05:00", "rating": 40, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Works perfectly, thanks a million!", "creationdate": "2017-12-11T04:46:19-06:00", "id": 1088858, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2437941, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Vayaasu", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Still works! Thanks!", "creationdate": "2018-02-11T11:01:17-06:00", "id": 1099365, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2437941, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "excalibrax", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "January 2021, Version 9.0.2. Still works great, though I would caveat that she is located on Echo Isle and NOT Bladefist Bay.", "creationdate": "2021-01-15T19:08:30-06:00", "id": 1441752, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2437941, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "SenteKhazModan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-10-31T04:44:02-05:00", 3, "Netimerin"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 2445676, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "Petitgreen", "body": "On the french comments part Cleclestria said that you can found the NPC on echo isles at 57.51 - 62.42 (in front of Vol'jin House) that work for me on Hyjal-EU the 17/11/16", "date": "2016-11-17T17:14:15-06:00", "rating": 21, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This should be upvoted more.", "creationdate": "2016-12-23T19:31:59-06:00", "id": 1018619, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2445676, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "lonewolf83", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I have a level 23 tauren druid that i had in org and went all the way down there. standing on the spot and don't see Ravika at all? Am I missing something?", "creationdate": "2017-01-01T21:03:28-06:00", "id": 1020569, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2445676, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "paredin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "/way Echo Isles 57.51, 62.42", "creationdate": "2017-01-23T08:27:47-06:00", "id": 1027360, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2445676, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "tbhimonp", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Very important bit of information for those that do not play horde often or at all. Echo Isles is actually it's own zone. If you put in the coordinates of 57.51, 62.42 while in durotar, it will take you to the very wrong location. The comment above me mentions exactly how to enter it in any zone with Tom Tom, but gave no explanation beyond that. So either wait until you are in the Echo Isles zone to type in the coordinates, or use /way Echo Isles 57.51, 62.42 as mentioned above.", "creationdate": "2017-01-29T09:13:27-06:00", "id": 1028906, "rating": 5, "commentid": 2445676, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Soundfx4", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "She's phased unless you're level 100+ and did some Legion and/or artifact quest. (Not sure which one exactly is the trigger, I just know that my lvl 100 with no artifact couldn't see her, while the one with artifact saw her just fine.)", "creationdate": "2017-01-30T21:16:20-06:00", "id": 1029317, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2445676, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Saro", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
