{"commentv2": 1, "number": 65, "id": 5166246, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ifloops", "body": "As of 9.0.5, this is the fastest way to buy all 3 toys and the cosmetic from this vendor, assuming you don't have a Horde character or otherwise can't find Ravika:\n\n\n[ol]\n[li]Own any Lvl 25 battle pet (or any battle pet that can defeat some lvl 3s, very easy).[/li]\n[li]Make a class trial Horde character.[/li]\n[li]Immediately hearth to Orgrimmar.[/li]\n[li]Go to the Battle Pet Trainer in Orgrimmar (Varzok, near flightmaster) and accept his quest to defeat Zunta.[/li]\n[li]Go to Zunta in Durotar (pet icon on map), accept her quest to defeat herself, then defeat her. Accept her quest to defeat Dagra.[/li]\n[li]Go to Dagra in Northern Barrens (pet icon on map), accept her quest to defeat herself, then defeat her. [/li]\n[li]Turn everything in to Dagra.[/li]\n[li]Vendor your bags/gear if necessary.[/li]\n[li]You should now have the required 87g.[/li]\n[li]Fly to Ravika at Echo Isles.[/li]\n[/ol]\n\n/way Orgrimmar 52.37 59.19 Step 1: Battle Pet Trainer (take Zunta quest) \n/way Durotar 43.78 28.73 Step 2: Zunta \n/way Northern Barrens 58.52 52.88 Step 3: Dagra\n/way Echo Isles 57.52 62.27 Step 4: Ravika (87g required)", "date": "2021-05-01T14:00:47-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2021-05-01T14:01:48-05:00", 2, "ifloops"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 66, "id": 5253662, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kalonjuud", "body": "I'm an alliance player, but just boosted a level 50 mage for mount collecting group purposes. I tried to use this vendor but alas the vendor was invisible on my boosted character. So all I had to do was create a class trial, use hearthstone to orgrimmar, go back on my other horde character, mail gold and 1 piece of food (wouldn't send without the food otherwise), THEN go back to the class trial, make my way to the vendor (which I could see now) and buy the toys which are then account bound. So there you go.", "date": "2021-09-15T08:16:38-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 3218564, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sipder2", "body": "To pull [npc=159153] you need [item=173001], i got it after complete [quest=58128] and have chance to drop from Depraved Mobs around Halls of Atonement - Revendreth.\n\n/way 71,2, 42,4 High Inquisitor Radu\n/way 72,7, 53,2 Depraved Mobs\n\n[b]Video location[/b]: https://youtu.be/ZxEYilKlE4Y", "date": "2020-07-21T10:19:17-05:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2020-09-12T11:11:06-05:00", 1, "Sipder2"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 3226163, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "GreatAndPowerful", "body": "Once you dispel his barrier with the sinstone you'll be able to fight him and he'll cast a debuff on you that does damage over time. This stacks four times, and on the fourth stack it'll turn into a 2 min debuff that ticks for quite a lot of damage and there isn't much you can do unless you can dispel magic.\r\n\r\nAs a hunter, I soloed this guy by letting my pet tank and once I reached 2-3 stacks of the debuff I'd go stand behind a pillar (for quite a long while) until the debuff wore off. This took me several tries as it hits for quite a bit.", "date": "2020-08-28T12:10:24-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The pillar strategy was a huge help to this hunter. Thank you! I'd hit him until the debuff showed up and ticked some, then pop mend pet or Exhilaration and hide til the debuff came off.", "creationdate": "2020-12-02T14:57:58-06:00", "id": 1417671, "rating": 1, "commentid": 3226163, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Seraclover", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 3265639, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "droidito", "body": "I was ilvl 165, tried as a shadow priest, almost got him.  Got frustrated at the couple of adds that would respawn on his platform and swapped to discipline.  I dragged him over to a nearby platform where there were no adds, dispelled the debuff, and dodged the black rain.  It took a while, but I was never in danger of dying.  \r\n\r\nAlso note that on his platform there are 2 cages that you can use to stun him for I think 10 seconds.  For classes that cannot dispel, you may be able to use these to prevent another stack of the debuff (I didn't test this).", "date": "2020-12-03T15:58:33-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
