{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 1722796, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kurasu", "body": "These creatures spawn in the city of Booty Bay and Tol Barad. However, these creatures can spawn as a not-tameable version. Also, these seem to share spawns with other critters when are in the area of the Bay: crabs and roaches (and potentially long-tailed moles and rats). \n\nPut all together, this makes this a very difficult pet to catch for your collection if you're farming for it in The Bay. The best thing to do is to fight/kill all other critters that show up in the city, and pray that they will start spawning as a tameable Wharf Rat, or that a wharf rat will pop up as a secondary (an occurrence that seems to be fairly rare here).\n\nEDIT: Corrected to remove mention of only spawning in Booty Bay, as it now spawns in Tol Barad.", "date": "2012-09-28T07:25:37-05:00", "rating": 38, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not entirely true. I managed to see one as a secondary to a Shore Crab on Jaguero Island while I was waiting for the rain to spawn a Baby Ape. 'course, like an idiot I killed it by accident, but it's at least possible to see it outside of Booty Bay.", "creationdate": "2012-09-28T11:54:24-05:00", "id": 575370, "rating": 8, "commentid": 1722796, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "zeterai", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "found in booty bay after patch 5.1", "creationdate": "2012-11-28T04:30:11-06:00", "id": 604000, "rating": -2, "commentid": 1722796, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "thunderold", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-12-10T05:51:06-06:00", 3, "Kurasu"]}
