{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 1792827, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Slaytannia", "body": "Went to Jaguero Isle to get one of these. Starting battling Shore Crabs. Found a common Wharf Rat rather quickly. Found an uncommon shortly after that. Spent the next three hours running around battling every pet and killing every mob (waiting for the rain) and only ever saw it a few more times as poor or common. \r\nWent to turn in for the night, flew over to Booty Bay to mail some crap to my bank toon, saw that Booty Bay was full of battle critters. Mostly were beetles, spiders, etc. But one rat. Sitting on top of All Things Flora. I decided what the hell. \r\nLow and behold, there was my rare Wharf Rat.", "date": "2013-01-05T04:01:11-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 1817236, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "1062573", "body": "So, I did a little testing into farming a rare of this pet.  Let me start by saying, yes, you can find this pet in Booty Bay and Tol Barad; if you're farming on a level 90 character, I recommend farming in Tol Barad.  Booty Bay has an issue where a lot of the spawn points for the Wharf Rat will be in areas where the battle area is obstructed and you can't actually pull it.  \r\n\r\nAs for Tol Barad, the rat spawns in Rustberg Village, the town to the northeast.  Despite it's name, it can spawn anywhere along the roads of the city (including the road that runs east-west in between Rustberg Village and Largo's Point / the spider area at the edge of the city) or along the docks of the wharf.  There is always one Wharf Rat spawn at a time; once you kill this, a new one will spawn in 30 seconds or less, often instantly.  This gives you a very consistent source of Wharf Rats to pull.  Also, the only secondaries that can spawn are Wharf Rats and Squirrels, and you get 2, so on average you're getting TWO Wharf Rats everytime you pull (the primary spawn plus one secondary spawn on average).  This leads to a very large number of chances for a rare in a short time.\r\n\r\nThe downside to farming in Rustberg is the combination of mobs that will actually aggro onto you with the fact you can't just fly around.  My suggestion is that you should run around in a loop, including the east-west running road at the southern edge of the town and the docks (basically, run around the edges of the town).  Most spawns occur on either this southern road or the docks, and this path will let you see spawns in the center of the town anyway.  Don't stop to kill enemy mobs unless you get dismounted.  Once you see a spawn, stop far enough away from it that you won't accidentally kill it, aoe down whatever has aggrod onto you (at 90 this shouldn't take more than a few seconds), then pull the Wharf Rat.  Repeat until you have a rare.", "date": "2013-02-23T05:03:44-06:00", "rating": 23, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The comment about there only being one up at a time is inaccurate - when i was in Rustberg Village, they were everywhere, even after i stopped battling them; in fact, on one occasion, down on the docks, i had 2 showing on my mini-map at the same time.", "creationdate": "2013-03-13T22:40:30-05:00", "id": 641551, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1817236, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "skarpethinn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 1828271, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "skarpethinn", "body": "The single spawn point showing on the Tol Barad map is an incomplete indication of the wharf rat spawns - they are everywhere in Rustberg Village and its environs.\n\ni saw about a dozen while i was doing the Rustberg Villagers daily, and it only took me 2 fights to get a rare. \n\nThey seem to spawn only wharf rats as secondary pets as well - at least the 2 pet battles i did had wharf rats as all three combatants in both fights.\n\nAlso, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=61323#comments:id=1817236]sirinad's comment below[/url] is wrong:\n\n\"There is always one Wharf Rat spawn at a time; once you kill this, a new one will spawn in 30 seconds or less, often instantly\"\n\nThis is inaccurate - when i was in Rustberg Village, they were everywhere, even after i stopped battling them; in fact, on one occasion, down on the docks, i had 2 showing on my mini-map at the same time.", "date": "2013-03-13T22:35:11-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-03-13T22:40:09-05:00", 3, "skarpethinn"]}
