{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 492978, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "DraconisFarin", "body": "You need to know the recipe for the hog/chopper in order to be able to bring up the purchase screen. This, in turn, requires exalted with your faction's vanguard (alliance vanguard or horde equivalent). With the material requirements and investment involved, don't expect to see motorcycles for sale for less than 17.5-20k.", "date": "2008-12-06T04:00:18-06:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 496657, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "Iroared", "body": "I had no problem buying the limited availability part.\nNot that I have that much gold myself =[\nI hope we would get more than 100g tips for making these...\n\nOh by the way you get the [li]Get to the choppa![/li] achievement by just making it, even if you give it to someone afterwards (they get the achievement when they use the key I suppose).", "date": "2008-12-07T21:54:10-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Why would you get more than 100g tip for making these?  If someone puts down the money and gives you all the titansteel bars and cobalt bolts, then I think 100g tip is more than fair.  Do you tip a Jewelcrafter 100g for cutting a gem that requires an exalted rep pattern or a 500g BoE pattern?  No.", "creationdate": "2008-12-26T15:37:53-06:00", "id": 374861, "rating": 0, "commentid": 496657, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "283684", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Then why do you pay 15% tips in restaurants?", "creationdate": "2009-01-07T17:18:37-06:00", "id": 378504, "rating": 8, "commentid": 496657, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Iroared", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Sadly, some people dont.....  PS: 15% from what i heard is a \"meh\" tip now a days... some waiters have the \"balls\" to ask you for 18% to 20%! (True in some parts of New York, information taken from my big brother's experiences)", "creationdate": "2009-01-14T17:28:20-06:00", "id": 380528, "rating": 0, "commentid": 496657, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Floral", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "only 15%!  Cheap A$$!", "creationdate": "2009-02-12T19:36:15-06:00", "id": 387951, "rating": 0, "commentid": 496657, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "231054", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This was fixed in 3.1 and no longer works.", "creationdate": "2009-06-04T04:55:24-05:00", "id": 101851, "rating": 7, "commentid": 496657, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Snoweh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-07T21:54:27-06:00", 1, "Iroared"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 506378, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "275470", "body": "u need 450 engi only to buy them or also to hold them in the bag?", "date": "2008-12-12T17:54:39-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not sure what you mean exactly, but this is how it goes;  1) 450 Engineering and Exalted with Alliance Vanguard (or the horde equivalent) in order to buy and learn the recipe. 2) Having learned the recipe is the requirement for being able to buy the items from Roxi. 3) Once constructed, the bike can be traded freely until it's been memorized (bind on use).  As a side note, both me (when I made it) and the friend (when he scribed it) I made this for got the achievement (Get to da choppah!).", "creationdate": "2008-12-13T16:52:06-06:00", "id": 64439, "rating": 14, "commentid": 506378, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "dakoth", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "stealing materials and/or money from players even if its given in trade for an agreed good or service violates the EULA, you can get it back and the thief banned.", "creationdate": "2009-01-02T10:12:41-06:00", "id": 376815, "rating": 3, "commentid": 506378, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "163402", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If you're really concerned, you can read Blizzard's official [url=http://us.blizzard.com/support/article.xml?articleId=20459]policy[/url] on such things.  By the way, it doesn't it violate the [url=http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/legal/eula.html]EULA[/url].  But it [b]does[/b] violate the [url=http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/legal/termsofuse.html]Terms of Use[/url].  You agree to both when you install the game and after every patch.", "creationdate": "2009-01-07T01:18:58-06:00", "id": 378298, "rating": 5, "commentid": 506378, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bryanc", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "are you by chance replying to a deleted post bryanc?  You're comment seems out of place.", "creationdate": "2009-08-10T16:33:16-05:00", "id": 419736, "rating": 1, "commentid": 506378, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "435622", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Hmm, maybe he means can you buy the parts and trade with another character. I can only see this of any use if you were, say xfering servers and had the gold to get the parts but not the other mats (or only some of the parts) before you or your engineer left.  [edit] the parts ARE tradeable and anybody can hold them, no Eng of any level required. A guildie just got a deal on the gatherable parts (about 20%, the lucky @#$%) and had my engineer make it for him.", "creationdate": "2010-09-05T20:16:59-05:00", "id": 180621, "rating": 1, "commentid": 506378, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "2nafeesh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
