{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 1704330, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kurasu", "body": "Despite the pet list's insistence that these are found in Tirisfal, I have been unable to find a single one of these pets outside of Undercity proper. Getting one of these as an Alliance is going to be a trial and a half. It will likely be easiest to create a Horde character, if you can, and use your selection of pets to get your rat. \n\nThere are rats which can be found in the outer 'Ruins Of Lordaeron', but these are ordinary [npc=61366] mobs.\n\nUndercity rats share spawns with maggots and roaches down there, as well. In other words, if you are unable to find an Undercity Rat, clear out some of the other critters (either by killing them all, or battling the non-rat capturable mobs) and you will give the rats room to spawn in their place.", "date": "2012-08-25T17:34:36-05:00", "rating": 83, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You can use a horde on any server so unless you have all 50 character slots used up then you can just make a lowbie for this specific purpose on a different server. Hope that's useful information for someone. Took me a while to really connect the dots on this myself because I'm so used to getting all my pets on one account for warcraftpets.com.", "creationdate": "2012-10-14T19:54:04-05:00", "id": 585106, "rating": 16, "commentid": 1704330, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "elvisdumbledore", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Make a Goblin Death Knight: You can get the goblin pet, you have the flight paths to easily knock out the Battle Trainers of Kalimdor, you can grab the Big City Pet Brawlin' Horde, and easily get the pets that only spawn in Horde cities.", "creationdate": "2012-10-26T13:46:32-05:00", "id": 591260, "rating": 19, "commentid": 1704330, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "brionl", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "brionl mentioned a goblin pet. Is this a companion pet? And how and when can it be acquired?", "creationdate": "2014-01-31T16:00:06-06:00", "id": 725655, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1704330, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tauriavas", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Shore Crawler [pet=63097] is the goblin-specific pet. Your goblin can buy it from a pet battle trainer.", "creationdate": "2014-03-19T10:58:45-05:00", "id": 735596, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1704330, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "803163", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Horrible to find a rare Undercity Rat... battle / kill now for 3 days all the rats I can find.", "creationdate": "2014-10-09T04:52:19-05:00", "id": 777495, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1704330, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Longeria", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-12-10T05:23:19-06:00", 4, "Kurasu"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 1727908, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1039046", "body": "yes for my server this is bugged so if you cant click and battle them open a ticket and hopefully you they fix this issue theres only 2 left also. server jubei'thos", "date": "2012-10-01T20:42:50-05:00", "rating": -12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 1729667, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Farzeer", "body": "Quite an annoying pet to get. Been flying around undercity for 2 hours now and i've been able to find 4 undercity rats (Lots of maggots and roaches tho). ALL 4 rats has been in places where i can't attack them (Area is obscured, or the area isn't flat enough)", "date": "2012-10-03T07:09:29-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 1737012, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "FuxieDK", "body": "I could only find ONE of these bastards in UC, and it was running around behind one of the Auctioneers, giving me the message \"Pet battle area is obscured\"..\r\n\r\nAfter 5 minutes, I killed it with a Moonfire, in hope it would force a spawn of a new one somewhere else..\r\n20 minutes later, still no Undercity Rat :(", "date": "2012-10-09T22:45:55-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The thing to do here is find an ability you have that counts as agressive, but deals no damage. Aggro your pokemon (I use Tranq Shot ironically) and it will run about like a Chicken with its head cut off. It won't be battleable during this time, but you will get a short window when it de-aggros, BEFORE it heads back to where it's supposed to be. Click it quick, battle, capture, enjoy.", "creationdate": "2012-10-10T18:05:07-05:00", "id": 582685, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1737012, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Aliandrin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can also drop down to straight/even ground, next to the ramp that leads up to each of the auctioneers and either click the rat, or spam 'interact with target' while facing parallel to the ramp.. when you pet battle, the opponent usually appears in whatever direction you're facing. So even if an opponent is up above you in some place where there's not enough room, you can still battle it if you're tricky. The one in the old PVP room with Sylvanas, unfortunately, has no 'safe' spot like this in which to fight :(", "creationdate": "2012-11-10T21:47:33-06:00", "id": 597745, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1737012, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Hezkezl", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 1738991, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "Aliandrin", "body": "One thing that's been working for me in these kinds of situations is this strategy.\n\n1. Slay the [i]critter[/i] versions of the battle pet you want.\n\n2. Slay the [i]pokemon[/i] versions of the battle pets that spawn in the area that you do not want.\n\nIn this example, slay all critter versions of Undercity Rat and all pokemon versions of Roach and Maggot. This seems to give you pokemon versions of the Undercity Rat a little more quickly.\n\nThe critter and pokemon versions of the same spawn are probably linked, meaning that if you slay critter Undercity Rats, some come back as catchable Undercity Rats. Pokemon are also probably linked with each other, meaning that there will only be so many catchable ones in one area at one time, which are usually mixed between all of the kinds that spawn. So what makes this technique work is opening enough \"holes\" for the dead critter Undercity Rats to come back as pokemon Undercity Rats.\n\nThis could be utter nonsense speculation, but it seems to work pretty well for me.\n\nEdit: This works. Doing this diligently, I got about a rat per minute (rather than one per 10-15 minutes) until finally, however much time this is and 211 Rats later, I got my rare.", "date": "2012-10-11T23:39:17-05:00", "rating": 34, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I tried your technique all along the circular route within the canals and this did seem to make the U.C. Rta type battle pet spawn pretty well. Good Info!", "creationdate": "2012-10-17T20:47:26-05:00", "id": 586700, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1738991, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Siella", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I was killing all critters and battle pets without much luck, then I tried this and it seemed to be much better. I just wanted to say, be sure to check all the areas off the circle. As soon as I killed the 5 maggot battle pets in Sylvanas' room, several rats popped up in the inner circle.", "creationdate": "2012-11-26T00:04:31-06:00", "id": 603098, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1738991, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "piekid", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Worked like a charm! I had been killing all critters, battling everything, been here for a few hours... just a few minutes of your method, and I finally got my rare rat. :)", "creationdate": "2012-12-23T10:23:43-06:00", "id": 615004, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1738991, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "hjp426", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Agreed. This worked a charm.", "creationdate": "2013-02-03T14:00:46-06:00", "id": 629296, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1738991, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Gendou", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Take my upvote! I became the Undercity's unofficial exterminator for a few hours, wreaking havoc among every critter/battle pet I saw in search of my rare rat. Read Wowhead comments during a despairing break, saw your method, tried it out, and it worked. Definitely more rats than I was seeing before! Thanks for posting this!", "creationdate": "2018-02-18T20:26:49-06:00", "id": 1100619, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1738991, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Kemaria", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-10-12T00:47:28-05:00", 1, "Aliandrin"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 1740378, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "803163", "body": "Alliance: Unless you are itching for a challenge, and you really don't have any other horde toon on your account, you can follow these directions to get your Undercity Rat: \r\n\r\n1. Make an Undead toon on any server. \r\n\r\n2. Run your new Level 1 Undead to Brill (stay on the road, and head for the red FP on your map - you may be able to outrun dog attacks).\r\n\r\n3. Take the free FP to Undercity. \r\n\r\n4. Battle the Undercity Rats till you get what you want. Your Battle Pet skill (and all of your battle pets, of course) carries over to even a new level 1 toon.\r\n\r\n5. Log into your main pet-battling toon so your new Undercity Rat shows up in that toon's book.\r\n\r\n6. Delete the Undead toon, if desired.", "date": "2012-10-13T10:51:54-05:00", "rating": 48, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Once you do all that.. take the orb portal over to Silvermoon ;) (it's in the outer courtyard, one of the small rooms up the steps - for those that don't play horde)", "creationdate": "2012-11-18T01:12:10-06:00", "id": 600236, "rating": -5, "commentid": 1740378, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Jarynelle", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 1740834, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Daurr", "body": "yes, battling or killing the other pets about does make the rats spawn, i have a white & a black rare now", "date": "2012-10-13T20:33:14-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 1744720, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "kcartwright856", "body": "If you're like me, you may have had the misfortune of heading to Undercity and finding nothing but maggots and roaches. Even worse, you may have found the elusive Undercity Rat that would not maneuver into a position in which to battle. Infuriating.\n\nFor roughly 30 minutes, I flew around the Undercity in search of rats to capture and call my own. As my patience dwindled, I finally began to slay all of the maggots and roaches in a blind rage. My anger nearly consumed me until I noticed that an Undercity Rat had appeared where my maggot massacre took place. I quickly swept in to capture it and, golly gee, it was a rare. Oh, happy day!\n\nTo make a long story short, just kill innocent creatures until the ones that you want appear.\n\nNote: Plain \"critters\" did not seem to affect the battle pet spawns for me, though your mileage may vary. Restrict your rage to the battle pet creatures. Unless you really just can't control yourself.", "date": "2012-10-18T08:39:08-05:00", "rating": 137, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As for that last, what I found is that in some of these situations, slaying the critters makes a difference, and in some it doesn't seem to. If you watch very carefully, you will notice as I did that once an area gets plastered thick with critter Undercity Rats, the only pokemon produced out of the spawn points near those areas will be Roach and Maggot. Other times, it seems to switch and almost go in cycles, and you'll find yourself flying around the ring with one good run, then one or two runs where you're primarily wiping out Roach and Maggot.", "creationdate": "2012-10-19T17:09:36-05:00", "id": 587777, "rating": -4, "commentid": 1744720, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Aliandrin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Worked for me too!", "creationdate": "2012-10-22T08:13:31-05:00", "id": 589202, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1744720, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "382252", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Consider battling the other pets too with a high end pet in slot 1 & a lowbie in another or Terrible Turnip for when you find the rare undercity rat. You can kill them in battle in like 5 sec. with 1 move & it counts as a win toward the achievements.", "creationdate": "2013-05-26T11:49:47-05:00", "id": 662639, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1744720, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "florhl", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This worked like a charm. Literally two minutes after killing all critters in inner circle, got my undercity rat! great advice!", "creationdate": "2019-07-25T20:10:15-05:00", "id": 1318803, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1744720, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Hirsha", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-10-18T09:52:12-05:00", 3, "kcartwright856"]}
