{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 1789475, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "wowcataryn", "body": "As was posted by Aliandrin, the best way to spawn the rats is to kill all rat critters and the roach and maggot battle-pets. It still takes an ungodly long time to get a rare, but persevere and you will eventually be rewarded. You'll want to go to the throne room periodically and clear out ALL the battle-pets there, including the rats since pet battles do not work in that room at all.\r\n\r\nAs a nice aside, I captured my rare Undercity Rat using a rare Stormwind Rat (which was a LOT easier to get!)", "date": "2012-12-30T05:21:39-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 1799811, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Eccentrica", "body": "After farming for and finally bagging a rare rat, you will have an intimate knowledge of the layout of Undercity.  Unfortunately this knowledge will be utterly useless to you in future, as you will undertake a solemn vow never to return.", "date": "2013-01-16T21:53:28-06:00", "rating": 92, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "On behalf of all other rare rat hunters, thank you for expressing our sentiments so well, my friend. I, too, have undertaken this vow.", "creationdate": "2018-02-18T20:28:00-06:00", "id": 1100620, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1799811, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Kemaria", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 1809255, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Maritas", "body": "Like everyone else, kill everything that moves and repeat several times over.  Make sure to kill the ones in the royal chambers because you can't catch them anyway and they just take up a spawn point.\r\n\r\nThere is a rat that spawns by one of the auctioneers - don't kill it.  With a little patience it can be battled and it just might turn out to be a rare.  It spawned 3x and I got the rare on the 4th try - even though the idiot killed it earlier.", "date": "2013-02-04T21:22:18-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 1816445, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "1062573", "body": "When farming a rare version of this pet, fly circles around the middle and outer ring of the area (the middle ring is much faster and sees most of the city, but it will miss rats along the outer-most edges).  You need to kill any Roaches you find as they share spawns.  There is no spawn timer to the Undercity Rat, it's just a matter of killing all non-rat spawns to force rat spawns (it seems to be about a 50% spawn rate).\r\n\r\nOne other catch.  People tend to grab the ones in the middle of the city over time, making them seem really uncommon, but in reality it's usually that a bunch are spawned in Sylvannas's room to the southwest (finding like 5-6 in there is possible; they tend to pool in there since people never go to her room).  Go in there and kill any Roaches/Rats you find there (you could try battling them, but all areas of the room appear to be \"obstructed\" for pet combat, meaning you probably just need to kill them), and you should find a bunch of spawns throughout the city again.", "date": "2013-02-21T10:29:01-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Sometimes you can battle \"obstructed\" pets by using /target (name of pet) and then your \"interact with target\" key. It also seems to help if you face away from the pet before hitting \"interact with target\". Has worked for me many times.", "creationdate": "2013-06-19T16:27:48-05:00", "id": 670472, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1816445, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Cowina", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Oops I have to correct my last statement. I just went to Sylvannas's Room and my trick didn't work this time. Oh well.....", "creationdate": "2013-06-19T16:52:13-05:00", "id": 670475, "rating": -1, "commentid":