{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 1967297, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheCrosshare", "body": "Not required for the safari achievement for alliance, so unless you want one for collection reasons, it's not mandatory.", "date": "2014-05-23T14:22:44-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I've just collected all pets for the achievement except Undercity Rat. I haven't recieved credit for it though. Is it possible, since I have a horde alt that it becomes a necessity? My account is no longer alliance only so I can't confirm this either way.", "creationdate": "2014-05-24T19:16:39-05:00", "id": 747683, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1967297, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "rentard", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 2219319, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "lionsofmercy", "body": "I found that coming back early in the morning (i.e. 6:15) helped a lot, especially as I'd never been in Undercity before and it took me a while to catch on to the elevators, durr. Less competition=rare rat in ten minutes. (You will know if there's competition if you start coming across dead critters that you didn't kill.)", "date": "2015-07-24T05:28:23-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 2341542, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "cajun06", "body": "Idk what I am doing wrong, but I can only find a Undercity Rat inside the building itself, yet since I'm Alliance, I get attacked like crazy trying to find it. Anyone have any suggestions?", "date": "2016-06-17T13:48:46-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Use a Horde alt. Otherwise, create an Undead alt, run to Undercity from the starting zone and use that character to farm up the pet.", "creationdate": "2016-06-17T14:12:44-05:00", "id": 947309, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2341542, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "SoCalWoWGal", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This worked perfectly for me. I created an Undead alt and began farming for a rat. So I have been able to find many pets in the undercity to fight. So far, I have gotten an uncommon Undercity Rat - but I keep trying to find a Rare. It will be a long farm effort.", "creationdate": "2020-10-24T22:09:41-05:00", "id": 1399937, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2341542, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Goranek", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 2469538, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Marzen", "body": "This may not get up-voted to matter, but my experience was that the green paw that shows up on the map normally [b][i]didn't[/i][/b] while I was farming for this pet in Undercity. I had to mouse over what looked like normal critters to see the cursor change to the green paw to initiate battle. On my mini-map it didn't show as a battle pet.", "date": "2017-02-03T22:25:41-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I'm sure glad I read your post prior to starting my hunt :) ! I had to kill a lot of critters, but after an hour I had three, so thank you, as nothing was showing on the minimap etc as per your OP.", "creationdate": "2020-05-09T02:07:25-05:00", "id": 1367812, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2469538, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Prunes", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I started out this way - no green paws showed up. I ran around clicking on any little creature - maggot, roach, rat.....but then I remembered that I should activate the pets on the mini-map. Sure enough as soon as I updated the mini-map options I started seeing the battle pets. Doh! I was not thinking. :-)", "creationdate": "2020-10-24T22:03:20-05:00", "id": 1399935, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2469538, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Goranek", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 2589304, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Johnsphil", "body": "I had wondered if the post condition of Undercity after the release of battle for lordaeron would permit me to go there and collect one freely. Don't attempt it, the blight will kill you.", "date": "2018-08-08T08:54:26-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Is this still possible to get after Undercity is blighted?", "creationdate": "2019-02-19T15:21:06-06:00", "id": 1220550, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2589304, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "dragontooth", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Horde, Allience, or both?", "creationdate": "2019-03-04T22:28:05-06:00", "id": 1222244, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2589304, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Damonra", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "you have to go with a level 100 or less wich not did the Lordaeron war escenario", "creationdate": "2019-05-15T13:01:41-05:00", "id": 1301893, "rating": -2, "commentid": 2589304, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Valdesca", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can turn it back to the past Undercity by talking to Zidormi in tirisfall glades above undercity. It is west of balnir farmstead, east of undercity, its noted on the map as a little chat bubble.", "creationdate": "2019-06-05T10:41:51-05:00", "id": 1304202, "rating": 6, "commentid": 2589304, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Char", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnviron