{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 3297803, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "foredahorde", "body": "Easiest cave entrance: on the map, to the left of the word Brennadam there is a fork in the road.  At that fork, face north, so the windmill is off to the distance on the left - there is a building to the right.  Just before the building itself there is a cave entrance.  Enter the cave (kill any necessary mobs), and she will be down the small hill.", "date": "2021-02-04T10:35:19-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is perfect", "creationdate": "2021-03-25T08:58:23-05:00", "id": 1460926, "rating": 1, "commentid": 3297803, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Challio", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 5149023, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "craigbenting", "body": "I absolutely couldn't find this NPC using most of the earlier comments.  Looking for some cave within a cave, I ran around the frustrating cave system nearby, where I had leveled in the past, for 20-30 minutes.  Then I started looking around the flight path and found:\r\n\r\nIt's very close to the flight path, where you can almost see the hole leading underground as soon as you land, except it's behind a tipped-over wagon, in the direction of a friendly building with a teal blue-green roof.  Approaching that friendly building, walking past the tipped over wagon, you'll see the big hole in the ground with a big, fiery torch, seemingly saying \"HEY, RIGHT HERE!\"\r\n\r\nYou go down that hole, turn to the left and walk into another hole.  Maybe that's the cave within a cave someone else mentioned?  Either way, this is not complicated, it's a second hole after a first hole, no wandering around looking for it.  You walk straight down that second hole and she's right there, casting the Thornshaping spell, green orbs circling her hands.\r\n\r\nIf you happen to walk down the *other* first hole leading down to the second hole where she is, that second hole is directly in front of you.\r\n\r\nVery easy kill once I actually found her.", "date": "2021-04-10T13:21:19-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
