{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 6627, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "7049", "body": "Razorgore's location is a room filled with 30 large dragon eggs, much like the ones found in UBRS (Leroooooy!, that's right), just that these ones can be destroyed only with Razorgore's help, and in the following you'll see how.\r\n\r\nThe fight starts by aggroing the controllers on the west platform, killing them and triggering the spawn of adds (they appear in about 40 seconds after that). Kill Grethok and his adds and remember that and this\r\nstage one it's all about managing the number of the adds and destroying the eggs, as quickly as possible, as there is a risk that the numbers of the mobs should raise to an incontrolable situation.", "date": "2006-12-05T18:10:34-06:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 6631, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "7049", "body": "On the west end of the room there is an Orb, used to mind control Razorgore through stage 1 of the fight; the ideal situation consists of 2 controllers (paladins -bubble and control- for an alliance raid or anything else suitable, but keep in mind that the controllers must survive during this phase, as the use of Razorogore's abilities is crucial for the success of this stage) taking turns in mind controlling Razorgore.\n\nThe mind controlling process can begin even before the kill of Grethok and should be targeted on destroying the eggs (95% of the time), the only case in which you won't use this ability is when it is on cooldown. Then you might want to use the \"sleep dragonkin\" ability, as the fireball volley usually draws too much aggro on Razorgore, which, as you might guess, must stay alive during phase 1.\n\nThe adds that i've been mentioning so far are of 3 types: melee (legionnaires), dragonkin and mages. As you prolly expect, the melee ones (first 2 types) are hard hitting, heavy armoured etc. kind of mobs, while\nthe mages are more fragile but more dangerous too due to their AOE attacks. The easier way is to keep the adds population mainly consisting of melee and the dps group in your raid should nuke the mages asap; of\ncourse, it's not a piece of cake to tank the melee damagers, but it's preferable to being batch killed by the mages. Healers, heal, tankers, tank and dps-ers, do the dps! It's that simple, isn't it? Now, balance is\neverything. There's no need to keep the orcs alive with any cost, of course you must decimate them to keep a controllable population, but only if the mages are being taken care of, as killing them is the highest\npriority for you. Tip: mind control the orcs and use them to kill the dragonkins, as they have 400% damage bonus against them. If the dragonkin number is too big, use the druids to sleep a part of them, anytime\nrequired (and it is required most of the stage, in fact). Any other classes that can croud control should do so (sleep, sheep, fear, scream), in an organized fashion and if possible by taking turns, in order to keep a\neven threat. During stage 1 also try to kite as much as possible, a horde raid could use the shamans' earth binding totems, everybody can use the hunters' traps etc.\n\nBy the end, the chaos is spreading and the numbers of the adds raises insanely, but do not panic, as all of them will go away when the last egg is destroyed. In order to make it to this final moment of stage\n1,when there's only 3-4 eggs left, use all your CC abilities and chain fear everything, don't focus on killing, but escaping them.\n\nPhase 2: time to kill Razorgore itself.\n\nRazorgore has, beside his melee attack, a hurting fireball volley and a conflagrate attack that gets you out of your control, burning you and the people around you. This is the reason for dps-ing him mainly ranged\nand using more than one tank. The MT is facing Razorgore, the backup tanks are behind him. When the unfortunate conflag event happens, the MT also loses aggro, so a backup tank should take his palce immediately, while the burning ex-MT steps back in order to protect the others of catching fire.\nAs you might have noticed, there's a lot of fire involved, so it's not a bad idea to bring along some fire resistance equipment, but bear in mind that you'll not leave the \"in combat\" state between the 2 stages of\nthe fight, so no gear switching is possible.\n\nTry to take advantage of the large size of the room. In the unfortunate case a healer should die, have a druid rez him in-combat, but as far away as possible from the action. The ressurected healer will be out of\ncombat and will be able to bring back some of the other fallen comrades.\nHowever, it's best not to come to this, as the unpredicted can interfere and mess the things up.\n\n(Strategy from Ana's Lair)", "date": "2006-12-05T18:12:01-06:00", "rating": 23, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Here's the strat our guild uses:  Razorgore is the first boss you meet in BWL. The main boss fight consists of two stages. The first stage is the egg breaking stage, with the second being the part where you actually kill Razorgore. During the first stage you use Razorgore (by using a Mind Control device) to destroy all the eggs around the room. During this stage three different types of mobs spawn. Each time you break an egg, 1 Dragonkin spawns. Every few seconds, a legionnaire or mage will spawn in 1 of the 4 corners around the room. The general strategy is to kite the dragonkin with warriors", "creationdate": "2006-12-05T18:12:02-06:00", "id": 285833, "rating": 1, "commentid": 6631, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "7111", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 12200, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "kreghx", "body": "Razorgore\r\n\r\nSetup\r\n\r\nWe split the raid into 4 teams. Each team occupies one corner. Usually \r\nteam A is groups 1 and 2 who go west \r\nteam B is groups 3 and 4 who go north \r\nteam C is groups 5 and 6 who go east \r\nteam D is groups 7 and 8 who go south \r\n\r\nEach team gets \r\n1 Hunter \r\n1-2 Warriors \r\n2 Priests/Druids \r\n1 Paladin \r\n1 Warlock \r\n1-2 Rogues \r\n1-2 Mages \r\n\r\nA spokesperson for each team on TS announces spawns in the corners. \r\n\r\nPHASE I (EGGS) \r\n\r\nDPS\r\nA mage or rogue in each team is appointed Main Assist, Mages, Hunters and Rogues in the team will help kill his target. His target are all Orc Mages in the corner. They have to die ASAP until eventually only Legionaires and Dragonkin remain) \r\n\r\nWarriors \r\nThe warrior(s) in each corner sunder (build aggro on) each dragonkin and legionaire in their corner and kite it between the two platforms (running up the stairs and jumping down in the middle front exploits the no-jump pathing of the mos and gets distance between warrior and his heat. Piercing Howl helps too. Eventually all 55 mobs will be following the warriors and if all goes fine, they wont even take damage. \r\n\r\nHealers \r\nThe healers in each team keep their warriors always shielded and HoT'ed. Optimal position for them to be is the front corner of the platform on their side. From there they always have a LoS to all team members and especially the warriors roaming their corner currently (usually its 2 tanks you have to keep track of, yours and the one of the team accross the room who follows the same path as your warrior). Also if they get hit, they can easily get some distance by jumping down the edge and running. Priest should use the CTRA aggro-gain announcer to be able to cast fade before the mob hits them. \r\n\r\nPaladins\r\nPaladins are the orb controllers. They place themselves below the orb right from the start and destroy eggs as fast as possible. They should not take damage during the egg phase at all. Once all eggs are down, the primary orb user will have a lot of aggro from Razorgore and he will come straight after him. We use that to position razor immediately in a good spot and to bring him to the MT tag-team. \r\n\r\nPHASE II \r\n\r\nThe MT tag team builds aggro on razorgore. Every now and them Razor casts a frontal AoE conflag that temporarily wipes all aggro on the current tank, swithing it to the offtank. Position of the 2 tanks is 90", "date": "2006-12-09T13:36:03-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 13109, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "8558", "body": "BWL: Razorgore Strategy\r\n\r\n[Razorgore Encounter Overview]:\r\n1. The Pull\r\n2. Kiting &Corner Control\r\n3. Chaos & Razorgore\r\n[Raid Group & Positioning]:\r\n- Each Corner is assigned 2 well-balanced Groups:\r\n- Corner A, Groups 1 & 2\r\n- Corner B, Groups 3 & 4\r\n- Corner C, Groups 5 & 6\r\n- Corner D, Groups 7 & 8\r\n- Odd Groups, High-Aggro Kiters &amp; DPS (Outer Square)\r\n- Even Groups, Low-Aggro Squishies (Inner Square)\r\n\r\n1. [The Pull]:\r\n- Entire Raid carefully stacks and buffs up at the Center of the Room.\r\n- Raid pulls the Controller and Guards to the Center.\r\n- OrbController goes in and takes control of Razorgore.\r\n- Raid Focus Fires on Controller, then the 2x Guards.\r\n- Immediately after 2nd Guard drops, Raid breaks to their assigned corners.\r\n\r\n2. [Kiting &amp; Corner Control]:\r\n- While Razorgore is destroying the eggs, numerous spawns will appear:<BR>- Blackwing Mages: Kill On Sight.\r\n- Blackwing Legionnaires: Kited by 2x Main Tanks.\r\n- Blackwing Dragonkin: CC'ed by Hunters, Warlocks, and Druids.\r\n- Spawns will continue at 1-2 per corner every 15 secs.\r\n[Class Responsibilities]:\r\n\r\nBlackwing Legionnaire Kiting:\r\n- 2x MT Warriors, Spam Demoralizing Shout. Figure 8's.\r\n\r\nBlackwing Mage DPS:\r\n- Mages, NO AOE. Focus Fire. Crowd Control.\r\n- Rogues, Assigned as MTs of Each Corner.\r\n- Warriors (spares), Focus Fire.\r\n\r\nBlackwing Dragonkin CC:\r\n- Hunters, Hunter's Mark &amp; Kite one Dragonkin using Scatter Shot.\r\n-Warlocks, single target fear an unmarked (Hunter's Mark) Dragonkin.\r\n- Druids, hibernate loose (unmarked &amp; unfeared)  Dragonkin.\r\n\r\nRaid Support:\r\n- Priests, shield &amp; renew players. Fade defensively.\r\n- Shaman, drop Totems. Heal. Kite loose Blackwing Legionnaires.\r\n                              \r\n3. [Chaos &amp; Razorgore]:\r\n\r\n- When 4-5 Eggs remain, Orb Controller will use \"Fireball Volley.\"\r\n- Every mob within the instance (40) will immediately aggro Razorgore.\r\n- Fear Rotation to prevent damage on Razorgore. Focus  Heals on Razorgore.\r\n- Stun, Frost Nova, Scatter, Frost Trap -- KEEP THEM OFF RAZORGORE!\r\n- Spawns will disappear and Razorgore will heal himself to full.\r\n- OrbController moves towards Corner A and Vanishes.\r\n[Razorgore Abilities]:\r\n1. Melee Attack & Cleave.\r\n2. Warstomp AOE, Knocks of all melee  Aggro.\r\n3. Conflagration frontal cone AOE, unremovable DoT with confusion.\r\n4. Fireball Volley (every 20 secs), LoS 1k dmg fireball. Max  range / hide!\r\n[Fighting Razorgore]:\r\n- MT & OT must be engaged at all times, facing Razorgore to Corner A.\r\n-  MT = Front, OT = Back.\r\n- When MT is conflag'ed, OT takes and faces Razorgore back towards corner.\r\n- Similar to Onyxia Phase 1, allow Tanks to build sufficient aggro before DPS.\r\n- While Tanks build aggro, Soulstone & Combat  Rez players.\r\n- CONTROLLED RANGED DPS, to kill  Razorgore. Very similar to Onyxia\r\n\r\n>>Just what my guild used", "date": "2006-12-10T21:56:36-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 14844, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chandrialla", "body": "Sometimes it may also be necessary for healers to downrank their spells, in order to avoid the aggro that comes with constant healing. Mileage may vary. Anyone who isn't kiting should have some bandages handy.", "date": "2006-12-13T13:03:09-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 17264, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chaosangel", "body": "This is a tough fight, especially for guilds coming right out of Molten Core/ Ruins of AQ (20- man).  He has been known to cause many a guild to break up, mostly because people coming from MC are used to generic tank n' spank fights (Golemagg, Gehennas, Ragnaros, etc.) with very few twists or deviations in strategy.  This fight is very involved, and everyone is forced to coordinate their actions whether they are kiting, mind- controlling, or even just zerging the mages that spawn.", "date": "2006-12-19T10:11:54-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 284016, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "93865", "body": "Known issue in TBC, unsure if it has been fixed:\r\n\r\nEven after all eggs have been destroyed and Razorgore himself has been killed, the adds will not stop despawning. They will continue to respawn and fill the room into phase three, making it impossible to end the encounter except by wiping. Even so, it is possible to do so, and loot Razorgore and proceed in the instance.", "date": "2008-05-07T12:54:29-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
