{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 809779, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Corenna", "body": "To circumvent his AOE-wipe post 3.2, have someone else spam click the orb when it's about to drop, that will allow you to pick him up again before he kills everyone.", "date": "2009-08-13T01:15:44-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 813252, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "svirve", "body": "Succesfully 2-manned last night by a blood DK (tank) and holy paladin (controller).\r\n\r\nWe got the bug were he would do his doomsday AoE after the first MC twice it would come with a message stating that the Instance was already in progress prompting to Portal to the Graveyard or Joining the instance.\r\n\r\nSeems to be random if it happens though since our fourth try went without a care.", "date": "2009-08-16T07:44:52-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 813837, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "LynMars", "body": "We tried this today and discovered part of the problem is that Razorgore must be in combat with someone when the MC breaks, or it'll trigger his AoE instakill. Trouble was, the adds weren't spawning fast enough. \r\n\r\nWhat we did then was when the MC was about to break, a Death Knight threw a Death and Decay at Razorgore's feet so he'd trigger combat while Razorgore was uncontrolled, until MC could be established again. My Priest was also able to hit him with an instacast to trigger combat before he could AoE.", "date": "2009-08-16T18:23:30-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 819436, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "15184", "body": "We had the same Kaboom bug, combined the two ideas above and it worked perfectly - a second person by the controller spamming the orb, aoe on Razorgore at control end, and we also tryed not killing every single npc as he spawned :P - Worked like a charm", "date": "2009-08-22T08:47:06-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 842223, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "rzzr", "body": "Noticed another bug. After we killed him the adds still kept running into the room. The raid leader said it was because lots of us were not attuned to BWL and we had to leave the instance and get summoned back. I guess this is because, like us, you can be summoned straight into the instance by a lock and you couldn't back in the day. Just wondered if anyone else has seen this \"bug\"?", "date": "2009-09-17T05:55:21-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Just ran this tonight and it was endless wave after wave of adds even after we downed the boss.  There was 8 of us so killing them wasn't an issue and we just decided to proceed to the 2nd boss with them still on us.  After we killed the boss and the remaining adds no longer spawned until I think someone walked back into that first room.  *grammar edit", "creationdate": "2009-09-19T00:06:20-05:00", "id": 425071, "rating": 2, "commentid": 842223, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "fluffy2k", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just ran Blackwing Lair last night.  They have finally seemed to have fixed the \"endless mobs after Razorgore dies\" bug.  This has been happening for years.  Glad to see Blizzard went back and fixed it.  Must have been an undocumented 3.3.3 change.", "creationdate": "2010-03-30T10:51:44-05:00", "id": 446124, "rating": 1, "commentid": 842223, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "KZWings", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed still bugged as of 3.3.3 Went there last night and they just kept spawning after he was down", "creationdate": "2010-04-02T08:59:48-05:00", "id": 446410, "rating": 1, "commentid": 842223, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "569451", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You just have to run out of the instance and wait outside for 1-2 minutes. The adds will stop spawning and will dissapear. I tried it today and it worked. Also I don't think it has anything to do with attunement, since everyone in my group was attuned.", "creationdate": "2010-09-10T18:49:05-05:00", "id": 181388, "rating": 0, "commentid": 842223, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "567509", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I'm actually a little annoyed that they have yet to fix this bug.", "creationdate": "2011-08-22T22:28:29-05:00", "id": 260131, "rating": 1, "commentid": 842223, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "18882", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 921397, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "HarTstaRx", "body": "2 manned with a resto druid 80 and a combat rogue 59 xD, the rogue mind control the boss and the druid tank and heal himself keeping an eye on the rogue.", "date": "2009-12-17T18:50:38-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 975147, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "479989", "body": "Easy boss to solo as 80 just be sure to even be very fast able to heal you self with crazy much hp, get out of stuns (Fireball Voley).. if you are feral druid then go up fight him alittle, then pull back, use Shadowmeld and make the adds fight him for al ittle when you then want then you can go back kill him..\r\nBe aware, when he dies all the eggs will explode and kill you.. anyway i died", "date": "2010-02-13T13:00:12-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "While you [i]can[/i] see him die if you do this, it doesn't allow you to progress further into the instance, nor will you be able to claim any loot.  You'll have to defeat the encounter the proper way to progress further into Blackwing Lair, unless I'm mistaken.", "creationdate": "2010-02-18T13:11:14-06:00", "id": 149904, "rating": 23, "commentid": 975147, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MattimusPrime", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 1010215, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "552719", "body": "2 manned him as arms warrior and feral druid...pretty easy. \r\n\r\nWarrior was on orb MCing and druid tanked everything. Druid was 5.2k+ gs and warrior was 4.8k\r\n\r\nDruid got low at times but he managed to keep himself up.", "date": "2010-04-01T13:35:33-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 1052979, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "562703", "body": "2 Maned this today with a 80 Rogue whom controlled the dragon, and a 80 Feral Tank who collected adds off of dragon. \n\nStrat.\n\nDruid goes in and get first 3 adds. Then Rogue does not run up to Orb, but runs under it and clicks to control. While rogue is destroying the eggs the druid is collecting adds and running up to each platform then jumping down so the adds have to go around and the druid has time to Hot and heal everything that needs it. Once all eggs are down its gg.", "date": "2010-06-05T22:13:01-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-06-05T22:13:18-05:00", 1, "562703"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 1080973, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "bonzai10", "body": "Still bugged. Im on opening AQ gate quest line and im frequently runing BWL. Been there 3 times recently and 3 times got bugged. Will do couple of runs this week and next on main and alts and see how it goes.", "date": "2010-07-15T08:04:47-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 1084510, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "CalaelenDT", "body": "Important to note is that classes that have active pets out will be unable to use the Orb of Domination until they have dismissed their pet.\r\n\r\nWent in there with a Hunter, Paladin and myself (Death Knight) and both the Hunter and myself couldn't control the Orb, while the Paladin could. We had no clue what was up and decided to do it some other time as we thought the encounter was bugged. I finally found out the reason by a post on the Orb of Domination page that stated the pet issue, and since that's not a page people will drop by first I figured I'd post it here too for people having the same issue.", "date": "2010-07-19T16:13:00-05:00", "rating": 281, "indent": 0, "roles": 6408, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thank you so very much for this information...I was thinking it's a bug... ><", "creationdate": "2012-11-03T14:39:36-05:00", "id": 594796, "rating": 9, "commentid": 1084510, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "andrezildo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I can't tell you how much this information means to me. I was just about in tears from clicking the damn orb. <3", "creationdate": "2012-11-29T09:24:50-06:00", "id": 604821, "rating": 6, "commentid": 1084510, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "BlankTH", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This boss is now soloable at max level. The challenge is mechanic, not dps or damage received. You can either bug the boss in such a way that no adds spawn, or you can do it the hard way. Using a HoT before you MC Razorgore to draw aggro to you and away from Razorgore will help a lot. Without bugging or a HoT it requires a lot of practice. The rest of the raid is cake.", "creationdate": "2013-01-03T12:16:19-06:00", "id": 618807, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1084510, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "438040", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Solo as a hunter, using the dismiss often strategy, but also using http://www.wowhead.com/spell=128594 to break control worked perfectly! As a side note, when you break control, drop traps at your feet before re-clicking the orb, this will kill off any adds that aggro to you, for laughs i also used http://www.wowhead.com/item=87780 and http://www.wowhead.com/item=86570 before starting the encounter, they don't count as pets so won't stop you from using the orb and they quickly dispatch any adds that don't die to the traps, Razorgore engaged with me and him at 100% HP, Dead, Easy!", "creationdate": "2013-04-09T18:00:30-05:00", "id": 649802, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1084510, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Smokingshrapnel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "damn and was already thinking of dropping it, thx a lot for info, as was thinking that it is just some kind of bug :D", "creationdate": "2013-05-15T08:19:03-05:00", "id": 658736, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1084510, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "hummmer", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 34, "id": 1098791, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Megalomaniacs", "body": "I've been toying with ideas on how to solo this as a feral druid tank.\n\nI did find something interesting. I would run in and do MC on him from below the platform where Grethok is. Grethok and his guards would attack me (the bear) leaving me to freely crush a few eggs with Razorgore. After the MC ended I used Frenzied Regen to get back to full health, ran to the top of the platform, waited for the mobs to get to me and hopped back to the ground and MC'd again. At this point there were a LOT of extra mobs spawning but virtually all of them were going for me and not Razorgore. I was able to get in almost an entire second MC phase before I was killed. At this point all the mobs despawned except for Grethok and Razorgore. They continued to fight each other.\n\nI wonder if I had a soulstone on if I were to pop up at that point and do start MCing again with Grethok chasing Razorgore around to keep him in combat between MCs, would the extra mobs start spawning again or would I be free to go about soloing the fight?\n\nHas anybody tried this before?\n\n[small]Edit for spelling[/small]", "date": "2010-08-10T19:20:08-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "And when you break the last egg, does Grethok despawn or something? Like I said, he was still alive and physically attacking Razorgore.  I'm not saying somebody just hasn't \"figured it out\" I'm saying that it's possible it may have bugged or that something has changed. Old content breaks semi-often and just doesn't get fixed because it doesn't really matter.  edit: not talking to myself, responded to deleted comment.", "creationdate": "2010-08-14T14:01:38-05:00", "id": 177535, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1098791, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Megalomaniacs", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-08-10T19:21:15-05:00", 1, "Megalomaniacs"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 35, "id": 1147921, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "609114", "body": "Still bugged as of 4.0 (but then, what isn't?). Just get the whole raid to leave the instance then go back in after a few minutes.", "date": "2010-10-19T20:47:53-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 36, "id": 1164284, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Cinnestra", "body": "I just two manned this last night with a feral tank (me) and a warlock. This fight requires a minimum of two people to defeat: one to kite the adds, one to control Razorgore.\n\nI was our designated kiter. We tried several times with my prot pally (because, hey, pallies are unkillable right?), and had a ton of problems since I could not pick up all the adds. With the change to consecrate, you can no longer drop it continuously to help you maintain aggro. This resulted in a lot of hits on my partner, who would then get the debuff and be unable to MC Razorgore. Many wipes happened. \n\nOn my druid tank, this became no problem at all due to healing aggro. Imp. LOTP is crucial here - I faced the adds tanking backwards when able, using every GCD to trigger the heals from LOTP. For my kiting path, I used the good old figure-8, waiting til the adds all gathered on the platform and then jumped off. This gave me time to shift out and pop a rejuv and regrowth on myself, get back to bear form, and kite again.\n\nHealing aggro was always a problem for druids in this encounter - I remember having to downrank as a resto druid in vanilla WoW and STILL getting threat on random mobs. Well, now it's working to keep all the adds trailing after me. It's amazing how fast they would all zone in on me, almost completely ignoring my partner. He took a few hits, but I could easily run up, swipe, and get the adds off of him.\n\nYou could probably do something to maintain healing aggro with a pally, but honestly it was so much easier with my druid. \n\nAfter Razorgore, I swapped back to my prot pally and we easily downed the rest of BWL.\n\nETA: looks like they may have fixed the pet problem with the Orb of Domination. My warlock partner had his felguard out on aggressive to help keep the adds off of himself, and had no issues with the orb other than when he had the debuff.", "date": "2010-11-07T07:13:19-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "it is now currently soloable.", "creationdate": "2013-01-16T09:06:51-06:00", "id": 623267, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1164284, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "lolablerants", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-11-07T07:15:43-06:00", 1, "Cinnestra"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 1172705, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nananea", "body": "Currently Razorgore is despawning after the first mind control fades (at least on Windrunner US). The fight will not reset even through dying until you reset the instance through the portrait menu. This is with 2 people doing the fight.", "date": "2010-11-16T15:33:00-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Despawning confirmed as of patch 4.0.3. Does not seem to be possible to defeat this boss at the moment.", "creationdate": "2010-11-16T16:54:55-06:00", "id": 462948, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1172705, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "439186", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed.  Having difficulty as well.  Although sometimes we are able to get him MC'd for a total of 3 times so perhaps there is some trick to get around the glitch.  Will try again later and see if we can't figure it out.", "creationdate": "2010-11-16T17:45:08-06:00", "id": 462949, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1172705, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "703128", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Noticed that when i had a \"Destroy Egg\" Channeling before the MC was up, he would despawn.  Dont know if thats the culprit, but its something I noticed while controlling him.", "creationdate": "2010-11-16T18:02:16-06:00", "id": 462950, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1172705, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "352550", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Not saying that Blizzard put in a \"trick\" to get around a planned glitch.  Saying that sometimes the glitch is caused by a certain thing happening, which can be avoided in order to get past the glitch.  For example with the recent patch in Headless Horseman you would disconnect only if you moused over the pumpkin.  Turning off tooltips would stop this from happening and allow you to kill the boss.  Anyway, trying again right now to see if the above poster's idea might work.    Edit:   No luck, hopefully it gets fixed soon!  Running out of time for the questline :)", "creationdate": "2010-11-16T20:23:29-06:00", "id": 462962, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1172705, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "703128", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Friends from flavour country on cho'gall said it worked no problem.  trying 3rd time, with solo channeler this time.  still no luck, trying again later tonight.", "creationdate": "2010-11-16T23:44:50-06:00", "id": 462972, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1172705, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "marsbubble", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-11-16T15:56:10-06:00", 1, "Nananea"]}
