{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 1174180, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "703817", "body": "quote from blue:\r\n\r\n[quote]You're absolutely right; a problem was introduced in 4.0.3 where any interruption in the controlling will cause the event to get stuck exactly as you described. Luckily our developers caught onto it pretty quick, and it should hopefully be resolved next time the realm(s) restart. That will either happen as necessary during the cause of the week, or at the very latest, next week during maintenance.\r\n\r\nMy apologies for any trouble this caused you and your friends. :) [/quote]\r\n\r\n[url=http://forums.wow-europe.com/thread.html?topicId=15309284243]http://forums.wow-europe.com/thread.html?topicId=15309284243[/url]", "date": "2010-11-18T09:06:30-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 1325136, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "DrakeLord", "body": "At level 85, Razorgore can be duo'd with any class + a resto druid.  I just did it tonight with a death knight.\r\n\r\nThe second class works on the mind controlling.  Using the mind control orb will allow you to control him for up to 90 seconds.  If you get hit once by mobs, the channel lasts 67.5 seconds.  If you get hit twice, it lasts 45 seconds.  Since the debuff lasts 60 seconds, you can have a 100% uptime with the mind control as long as you only get hit once or not at all.\r\n\r\nThe resto druid simply stacks Lifebloom on himself and runs back and forth around the room.  With Lifebloom rolling, all adds will instantly aggro you from the healing and ignore Razorgore and your partner (ensuring 100% MC uptime).  Simply run up the stairs on one side of the room, wait for the melee dragons to almost reach you, jump off, run to the other side of the room, run up the stairs, wait, jump, repeat.  The mobs run slightly faster than you, so jumping off the platform gives you some breathing time where you're not being attacked while they do a bit of backtracking down the sides of the platforms.  The caster mobs will just fireball you from wherever in the room they are.  They're lousy shots, though.\r\nI would imagine Shamans can also do this easily with Riptide and Ancentral Swiftness/Earthbind (keeping completely ahead of all melee damage) and [i]maybe[/i] Priests with PW:S and Renew.\r\n\r\nAlso, it would seem the add bug as been fixed.  After breaking all the adds, all mobs fled the room, leaving only Razorgore to be DPS'd down.  Piece of cake.  I popped Tree of Life, proc'd Nature's Grace, and enjoyed my 1 sec cast Wrath spam.  ;)\r\n\r\nKeep in mind I had the minor run speed increase at the time.  I'm not sure if it's necessary though.  I never really dropped below 95% mana with a rolling Lifebloom stack and an occasional Rejuv.  I was only ever hit hard when the clump of melee adds caught up to me and all 50 of them smacked me all at once, which dropped me to about 75% health.  I Swiftmended just to be safe.\r\n\r\nI felt accomplished with the strategy, considering we had just wiped on 5 attempts to DPS the adds and desperately try to stay alive and not have Razorgore die prematurely.  =P\r\n\r\nWe were both in iLvl 329 gear.", "date": "2011-02-07T01:55:46-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 42, "id": 1328178, "nreplies": 12, "sticky": 0, "user": "supcat", "body": "Seems bugged after 4.0.6.\n\nTried 3-4 times with a raid today, and he will randomly wipe everyone like he normally will do when you kill him before the eggs are gone.\n\nEdit: I did make a ticket about this after the first raid, and got a response within 10 minutes. The GM cleared all eggs but one for us, and we just had to clear that one to get to P2", "date": "2011-02-09T05:47:24-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed that he's doing random explosions. Seems to mostly be at the end of a channel.   Also, they seem to of un-fixed the continuous spawning bug :(", "creationdate": "2011-02-09T07:55:14-06:00", "id": 223174, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1328178, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "dasquee", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I can confirm, as trying to tame[b] Chromaggus[/b] earlier ended up in 2-3 wipes at this guy.  He 1 shots everyone in the raid at random moments after breaking lose of the beam.  [i]PS. I find it ironic the title this guy has, \"the Untamed\" taunts us hunters for not being able to get to Chromaggus now![/i]  *Edit* Added the title mini rant.", "creationdate": "2011-02-09T20:38:08-06:00", "id": 223383, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1328178, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Jigs", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Happened to me as well.  Took us 6 tries to finally get him to not blow up randomly.  Thought it might have been a bug with shaman totems, but it wasn't.  What I did on the time we successfully killed him is build threat on him for a second or two in between mind control orb usage.  I don't know if that was just coincidence or not, or us just getting lucky.", "creationdate": "2011-02-09T22:38:00-06:00", "id": 223420, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1328178, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "177655", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "same thing here, even trying to finish the channel with him in the opposite side of the room to have time to get MC back he still run to the orb and explodes", "creationdate": "2011-02-10T07:32:34-06:00", "id": 223552, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1328178, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "26774", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I did it with myself as a Prot Warrior and my friend, Marksman Hunter. I tried aggroing him before my friend took over but we still blew up like lvl1's versus Deathwing.", "creationdate": "2011-02-10T19:33:25-06:00", "id": 223785, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1328178, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Jigs", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-02-17T04:58:39-06:00", 1, "supcat"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 1334496, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "92984", "body": "tried the above, even tried various things like swapping people MCing when it expires and making sure no one did anything for the last 20 seconds of each MC, it still bugged out, evaded and blew us up repeatedly, even soft reset it - there were 4 of us in there, myself another hunter and druid / warrior.\r\n\r\nHope blizzard fix it soon", "date": "2011-02-13T10:07:00-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 44, "id": 1334930, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "159788", "body": "As of 4.0.6 I have confirmed that the boss is doable and will not wipe you after control loss if you grab aggro on him as hes running to the orb.", "date": "2011-02-13T16:33:44-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Tried that, didn't work. Everything still exploded :P", "creationdate": "2011-02-14T11:04:57-06:00", "id": 225014, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1334930, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "JudasAnton", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The boss is doable like mentioned, however for me, most of the time it bugs out and everyone dies. That doesn't mean he bugs out all the time, but I would say 2/3 of the times I tried it, he bugged.", "creationdate": "2011-02-14T14:04:36-06:00", "id": 225047, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1334930, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "773571", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 45, "id": 1339180, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "deathtrap", "body": "It's comforting to know I wasn't the only person wiping on this guy... Gave it about 6 attempts before calling it off. Most times we would try right clicking the orb, a blue beam would appear, but no mindcontrol would happen.. boom. There was also one time that he was standing on the other platform across the room from us when mind control broke, he instantly teleported next to us and... boom.\r\n\r\nSo yeah, completely frustrating to say the least. Hoping for a fix sometime soon, my level 60 warrior would like some gear... but why fix old content? >.>", "date": "2011-02-17T00:26:01-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 46, "id": 1339283, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "michielseel", "body": "Bugges out randomly. Sometimes when channeling ends and sometimes you can't  even use the channel device.\r\n\r\n4 Whipes in a row:\r\n\r\nsome at the start and some with like 10 eggs left..\r\n\r\nNot worth trying at the moment", "date": "2011-02-17T02:22:44-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "One possible explanation (from our few attempts) is that the debuff is actually not falling at 60 seconds but rather once the normal channel time (90 seconds) wears off. I also believe it's bugged that getting hit is breaking the channel to easily/early. From our attempts, every time that the channel ended early, we couldn't pick it up again. Every time it ran its full length, we could.  Mind you, we were two manning it, so preventing the channeller from getting hit 100% can be a problem. It never was a problem before 4.06.", "creationdate": "2011-02-17T11:18:20-06:00", "id": 225891, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1339283, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 16384, "username": "789336", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 47, "id": 1340923, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wytebeard", "body": "Possible Solution #2!\r\n\r\nWhen Razorgore has the mindcontrol fall off him, sometimes it causes him to drop out of combat as well, if you try and mind control before putting him back into combat it instant wipes the raid.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Test? : hit him once. THEN mindcontrol\r\n\r\nPlease post if this had success with you all as well.", "date": "2011-02-18T11:23:09-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed. Me and my friend still wiped though because we forgot he runs back to the orb after you kill all the eggs so he wiped us all because of the same issue as above. But, having one of us always next to razorgore when the mind control ended prevented him from insta-killing us.", "creationdate": "2011-02-19T15:42:05-06:00", "id": 226505, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1340923, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Acry", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 48, "id": 1342610, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Lenarth", "body": "My friends and I (a feral druid, an elemental shaman and a blood death knight) decided to troll Blackwing Lair just for kicks, and we were having a problem with this guy evading sometimes as he rushed over to the orb to kill the controller. Naturally, this is a problem when your tank can't taunt him back over and when using the orb again doesn't do anything at all to solve the issue of an instant wipe on wheels careening towards you at high speeds.\n\nRazorgore appears to bug and evade when the controller doesn't have Mind Exhaustion, the debuff that keeps them from using the orb again until it runs out, when he breaks free. Again, this hasn't been confirmed anywhere, and I haven't seen anyone else mention it, but I am almost certain that the lack of the debuff is what causes him to evade. Or at least maintaining the debuff is a workaround to whatever the real issue is. If he does go out of combat like others say he sometimes does (which causes him to evade) then somehow keeping the Mind Exhaustion debuff keeps him in combat when you lose control over him.\n\nSo, cut off possession of Razorgore a few seconds before the debuff runs out. Using /dance was a simple way to lose control (plus, bear dancing makes everything better). Our tank was able to easily pick him up after I danced and kept the debuff, and we didn't have the evading problem for the whole fight. The entire thing is a cakewalk without the evade bug.\n\nAs a side note, you have control over him for 90 seconds by default; if he doesn't get hit by anything, you definitely have to cut off control early, since the Mind Exhaustion debuff only lasts 60 seconds.\n\nEDIT: Just this past Saturday (nearly a month after I initially wrote this comment) I ran Blackwing Lair with a new group and we could still /dance our way through Razorgore without any problems at all. We didn't try anything else (such as changing the placement of the orb controller, putting a dot on Razorgore, etc) and we were fine.\n\n\n\n[i]Edited for great justice and wording problems.[/i]", "date": "2011-02-19T18:49:22-06:00", "rating": 21, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Seconded. This morning, my friend and I did it with no problems using no special strategy, but after the reset, tonight, we were failing due to the bug until I found this method.  /dance for the win.", "creationdate": "2011-02-22T20:41:56-06:00", "id": 227526, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1342610, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "616167", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Worked for me also. Thank you very much for the solution!", "creationdate": "2011-02-23T18:51:04-06:00", "id": 227748, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1342610, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "furiouslupus", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed again to work. Lenarth is pro.", "creationdate": "2011-03-08T14:19:53-06:00", "id": 480904, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1342610, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "616836", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "march 24, patch 4.0.6 Hotfixes  Razorgore does not evade when attacked immediately after being released from the orb. He should also no longer reset when the orb controller is interrupted.  :D", "creationdate": "2011-03-26T10:30:55-05:00", "id": 234468, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1342610, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kromosoide", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-03-22T17:02:31-05:00", 5, "Lenarth"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 49, "id": 1344556, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "coops025", "body": "In order to avoid the \"evade\" bug you must kill most of the mobs or he will bug. \r\n\r\nA new bug my weekly BWL group ran into last night was that no one was able to click on the orb at all, 3 wipes later we gave up.", "date": "2011-02-21T09:09:59-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 50, "id": 1345776, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Widowkiller", "body": "Me and my warrior friend duo'd this place so I could tame Chromaggus. Man, this boss was a real pain in the rear. During the numerous wipes, I noticed that while controlling Razorgore, combat seems to randomly drop and return a second or two later. It also seemed to follow a pattern of every 20 seconds. I'm not sure if this was because of my warrior partner gathering everyone and never letting them hit me or what, but once I noticed the combat thing, I made sure the channel never broke while out of combat, and we downed it that very try. I can't guarantee that this will work for everyone, but just to be prudent, watch your combat state and make sure you are still in combat when you break the MC channel, and make sure the one not controlling the orb grabs aggro.", "date": "2011-02-22T07:26:09-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 51, "id": 1347557, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zyros", "body": "As of 4.0.6 encounter is bugged again.  Read through all the above comments, adjusted accordingly, boss still wipes everyone after a MC break.\n\nEven with sufficient threat built-up ahead of time, AoE being spammed on his location when he breaks, and someone else spam-clicking the orb as MC breaks - still nothing.\n\nEDIT: Yes, we kept mobs up, too, to try and force everything into combat, no go.", "date": "2011-02-23T19:15:30-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-02-23T19:53:31-06:00", 1, "Zyros"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 52, "id": 1347913, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "616167", "body": "For anyone who missed Lenarth's solution on page 2:\r\n\r\nBreak the mind control a couple of seconds before the debuff falls off. /dance works. He'll then aggro onto someone, instead of bugging out and resetting....and exploding.\r\n\r\nAll hail Lenarth, for the glory of the ingots!", "date": "2011-02-24T04:05:54-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yeah, it works. Tried right now. Kinda messy, but all went well.", "creationdate": "2011-02-25T20:33:40-06:00", "id": 228322, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1347913, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Marzabul", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Tried this method. It didn't work. He left combat, began evading, and exploded. Found a working solution based on game mechanics, see below.", "creationdate": "2011-03-02T11:45:42-06:00", "id": 229467, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1347913, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kiruvi", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 53, "id": 1355184, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kiruvi", "body": "Killed this boss last night; was able to diagnose and solve the evade/explode bug. The root cause is the level of people doing this raid; used to be, there would be 40 level 60's splattered all over the room, so Razorgore would aggro onto something when the Mind Control ends. However, with 80s and 85s all grouped together, diminished aggro radii mean he has nothing to grab onto to keep him into combat, resulting in his standard leaving-combat mechanic. This makes since as this bug first began cropping up around 3.0.\r\nThe solution we found was to have a lvl 80 boomkin Druid follow Razorgore around. As soon as the MC ended, they would start spamming Moonfire at the boss. He evades for a few seconds, but then they will start hitting, pulling Razorgore back into combat and allowing you to successfully Mind Control him again. I would assume that any fast, low-damage spammable spell would work the same way- as long as he is put back in combat before reaching the MC orb.\r\nUsing this method, we were able to complete 5 full mind control cycles, destroy all the eggs, and finish the boss.\r\nAs an added bonus, all adds despawned properly before the final phase.", "date": "2011-03-02T11:43:03-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 54, "id": 1361446, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nobbel", "body": "How to duo in Cataclysm:\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VBal4uMCfOk", "date": "2011-03-08T16:05:50-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 1363165, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Darthdavo", "body": "You [b]-HAVE-[/b] to break the mindcontrol when you have the debuff on you. Or else he will bug, and everyone will die.\n\nPersonally, i break it when i have 5 seconds of the debuff left, then i retake him.\n\n[u]Edit[/u]\n\nI haven't tried the tactic in the comment below, next wednesday i will attempt to and see the results.\nBut the tactics i used worked perfectly, and im not saying its better or not, you decide which you think suits you best.\n\n[u]Edit2[/u]\n\nJust tried my method again (On a horde character), i slipped up and let the debuff run out whilst Mind controlling, afterwards the boss ran over to the orb, ignored us all and blew the orb up.\nAfter that, i tried again and canceled it when the 'Mind exaustion' debuff was still up and at 5 seconds. No problems.", "date": "2011-03-10T12:18:21-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-03-16T03:05:57-05:00", 2, "Darthdavo"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 56, "id": 1363318, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "780906", "body": "Like the majority of others, I was also experiencing the bug where Razorgore is unable to be mind-controlled, reaches the orb and explodes.  My group (consisted of a Prot Pally, Demo Lock, and feral kitty) tried EVERYTHING for two weeks.  We attempted to get around the bug by engaging Razorgore himself by AoEing right after he finished channeling his MC, right before his MC ended, we tried the /dance macro to get him to end the MC early, using Razorgore's sleep ability on the dragonkin to attempt to keep him in combat, and none of it worked.\n\nSAVE YOURSELVES THE REPAIR -- after much testing, [b]we have finally figured out a successful way to get this $%^&*!@ down[/b].  The person who will be mind-controlling Razorgore should be [u]BELOW THE PLATFORM[/u], in front of the MC orb.  Whoever is picking up adds to refrain them from reaching and attacking the orb can stay at the top of the platform near the orb. (See screenshot provided below.) When the MC drops and all eggs are dead, Razorgore was on the platform and did not blow us up.  Piece of cake, had no problems.\n\nI hope this saves you guys some GM tickets, repairs, and irritation.  Good luck!\n\n[b]EDIT: We have also found that pets make Razorgore leave combat and explode.  If you are attempting the above method, dismiss all pets before initiating the boss.  This should ultimately cure the bug with the method I have provided.[/b]\n\n[url=http://i54.tinypic.com/2e3bdp4.jpg]CLICK HERE FOR THE PLACEMENT SCREENSHOT![/url]", "date": "2011-03-10T15:22:47-06:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Agreed. On my two tries (and downs) this method worked.", "creationdate": "2011-03-10T19:51:09-06:00", "id": 231381, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1363318, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 768, "username": "Merylyan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I second this, I 3 manned this (Druid, Pally, and Warrior) and we were trying all kinds of different strategies but what we ended up doing was having controller below the orb, warrior up at the orb tanking adds and the pally was taunting boss when ever the druid lost control. So glad I found this.", "creationdate": "2011-03-10T22:01:38-06:00", "id": 231409, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1363318, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "HKRob", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-03-18T19:09:21-05:00", 5, "780906"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 57, "id": 1363711, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Choicecut", "body": "We've never had this issue since Cata launch up until now, but we're having this issue, tried every idea listed in the thread, none of them worked. Put them all together, didn't work.\r\n\r\nBreaked Mc Early via /dance.\r\nHad myself (non-Mindcontroller) with AoE down and attempting to attack Razorgore at the end of an MC.\r\nMindcontroller was located at the button of the stairs.\r\nAttacked Razorgore as a form of pulling to ensure he had a player on his threat table.\r\n\r\nand so on, anyone else been unable to do it, despite using all these suggested (and apparently functional) fixes?", "date": "2011-03-11T01:28:50-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Lets hope it's getting fixed soon. Wiped quite a lot before giving up yesterday xD", "creationdate": "2011-03-24T03:28:50-05:00", "id": 234041, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1363711, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "710951", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Why where both of these down rated? This bug is a real problem. :I", "creationdate": "2011-06-12T04:47:59-05:00", "id": 245474, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1363711, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wiredmana", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 58, "id": 1375296, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Lenarth", "body": "Excellent news, everyone! [url=http://us.battle.net/wow/en/blog/2259389]Razorgore has finally been hotfixed![/url] And I quote:\r\n[quote]\r\nBlackwing Lair[ul]\r\n[li]Razorgore does not evade when attacked immediately after being released from the orb. He should also no longer reset when the orb controller is interrupted.[/li][/quote]\r\n\r\nRejoice and no longer cower in fear of a potential wipe on a level 60 raid boss.", "date": "2011-03-24T21:03:11-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed. Ran BWL tonight for the guild acp and he now works properly. Too bad they didn't fix the adds continuing to spawn after he is dead though. -_-", "creationdate": "2011-03-25T01:18:06-05:00", "id": 482179, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1375296, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nyteyes", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "False! That Hotfix did nothing. Ran this yesterday and he blew up several times due to the bug before we called it.", "creationdate": "2011-03-26T23:05:36-05:00", "id": 234586, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1375296, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "TheHeroOfTheDawn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 59, "id": 1376000, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "104108", "body": "I recently tried this with a total of 3 players, we were a resto shaman, moonkin druid and a protection paladin. Two of us raided BWL back in vanilla, so we tried the kite tactic that we were familiar with, this didn't really work, we also had problems with re-using the orb after the time expired, it would be interrupted right after the click, resulting in a wipe.\r\n\r\nAfter a few unsuccesfull attempts we came up with a foolproof solution.\r\n\r\nWe used the following tactic:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Kill [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12557]Grethok the Controller[/url] and his buddies.[/li]\r\n[li]After this, our paladin and druid positioned themselves under the orb, the resto shaman positioned himself in the middle of the room.[/li]\r\n[li]The paladin and druid control [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untamed[/url] and started on the eggs, alternating turns after the rotation expires. They should stay out of combat.[/li]\r\n[li]Meanwhile, the resto shaman keeps healing [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untamed[/url] (to get the adds off him) and himself while adds spawn, when they stop spawning he focuses healing on himself.[/li] \r\n[li]Now it's just about outlasting the damage while the eggs are taken down, after that the adds flee and you can engage [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untamed[/url].[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nWhen you've succesfully downed [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untamed[/url] you'll find that the rest of [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=2677]Blackwing Lair[/url] is quite pushover and can be done with a tank 'n spank approach. It's still fun to do while reminiscing the old days of WoW Classic :)", "date": "2011-03-25T16:17:56-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
