{"commentv2": 1, "number": 61, "id": 1387122, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mattrip", "body": "I went through this a couple of times recently with a couple of my guild members. We had a great time doing it which you can watch here http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EVVT7gXTqZs. The hunter in our group had tamed Chromaggus the week before, which got a lot of attention once we were back in Stormwind! With 2-3 lvl 85s this is a pretty quick way to grab some old school loot and a good amount of gold.\r\nThere's a little guide to Razorgore at the start too.", "date": "2011-04-08T17:35:01-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 62, "id": 1395427, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "gtadem", "body": "Just duo'ed this and being an AOE tank, it was VERY easy once I figured out the trick. Have your 2nd person stand in front of the platform and use the orb to control the boss while you kill the controller and his entourage. Have them break eggs near the orb at first. When adds start to spawn, pick them up and bring them to the center of the room. AOE.\r\n\r\nIt really is that simple. As long as you're actively adding aggro to mobs, new adds that spawn will quickly forget that they came for the boss and/or the mind controller and instead go to you. I was happy to see this work because it's HIGHLY repeatable and I won't have to waste my guildies' armor anymore.", "date": "2011-04-20T03:46:29-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 63, "id": 1417369, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Winssis", "body": "Just soloed this on my mage.\nThanks to:\n[quote]Now its soloable!\nCheck video guide http://www.warcraftmovies.com/movieview.php?id=180879\nDone by hunter and mage.\n[/quote]\n\nI had to survive 3 waves of adds, so HobbY's comment above ain't actually true.\nWhat you want is to keep the controller alive just in case.", "date": "2011-05-13T01:13:32-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Duo, not solo.", "creationdate": "2011-06-12T04:49:49-05:00", "id": 486278, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1417369, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wiredmana", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-05-13T01:33:25-05:00", 2, "Winssis"]}
