{"commentv2": 1, "number": 67, "id": 1431488, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Iroared", "body": "Couldn't solo it (although maybe I could if I try harder, I do have engineering), but bringing one of my 60 alts on another account makes it quite easy. Pull and kill the controller, position your alt under the orb and control the boss. First couple times I had problems with my alt dying somehow (combat log only showed two 700 hits, not quite enough vs 6k health), perhaps it had something to do with controller getting his MC off. Then just run after the boss pulling adds off of him (divine storm was a great help here, since it healed my alt and aggroed the mobs from across the room) and tabbed every 10 seconds to burn another egg.\r\nFor some reason, after all eggs were gone and I killed the boss, adds started spawning again and never stopped, only fixed by running out of the instance and waiting for ~15 minutes.", "date": "2011-05-31T16:28:55-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 68, "id": 1442507, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Athenia", "body": "How I dual box through BWL with my warrior and priest. (ilvls ~353)\n[b]\nRazorgore the Untamed:[/b]\n\nThe key here is to not waste time with Razorgores \"destroy eggs\" ability, it has a seven second cooldown so use it as soon as it comes off cooldown. Have the warrior pick up the adds from the orb platform and the priest immediately MC Razorgore and destroy the first egg, then kill the adds and warrior moves to the middle of the room. So long as the warrior is around the middle area (the big square between the two platforms) the adds will ignore the player on the orb and attack the warrior in the middle.\nClear out the eggs on Razors platform first, you want to keep him in the middle of the room with the warrior so the adds can be picked up more easily.\nThis is multitask heavy: Kill egg, move razor to next egg while \"destroy egg\" is on cooldown, tab to warrior, pickup/kill adds, tab back to razor to kill next egg, rinse and repeat.\n\nTip: [i]Make sure you have plenty of time remaining on the MC before killing the adds on the orb platform, if it breaks while he is there he may destroy the orb and wipe the encounter.[/i]\n\n[b]\nVaelastrasz the Corrupt[/b]\n\nNothing special here, go dps and nuke the hell out of him - with two toons it should not be all that difficult. You simply have to kill him before Burning Adrenaline kills you.\n\n[b]Broodlord Lashlayer[/b]\n\nTank n spank, keep your back to the door so he doesn't knock you into the adds.\n[b]\nFiremaw[/b]\n\nTank n spank, but kill him quickly.\n[b]\nEbonrok[/b]\n\n[s]This guy is tricky. Warrior as tank, priest as dps. Ebonrok will periodically put a debuff on the current target that heals him for 25,000 every time he hits that target - needless to say unless your dps is godly you will have to target swap each time this happens. Here's how to do it.\nHave your tank stand with his back to the wall up where Ebonrok patrols, have the priest stand about 30 yards away from the tank - the priest will open up as dps until Ebonrok puts the debuff on the priest, the warrior then taunts but [u][b]DOES NOT ATTACK[/b][/u] Ebonrok - this is important. Ebonrok will go to the warrior and and begin attacking him - all you want to do is pull Ebonrok off the priest long enough for the debuff to drop off. If the priest resumes attacking as soon as Ebonrok is over at the warrior he should surpass the warriors threat and Ebonrok will return to the priest right about the time the debuff is put on the warrior.\nIn this way Ebonrok will not hit the target with the debuff to heal himself, or no more than a couple of swings.[/s]\n\nKeep Power Word:Shield up on tank at all times, Ebonrok won't heal as no damage is done. If you don't have a priest, use the above method.\n\n[b]Flamegor[/b]\n\nTank n spank.\n\n[b]Chromaggus[/b]\n\nAnother somewhat tricky fight, firstly make sure both toons have ample amounts of Hourglass Sand to remove Brood Affliction: Bronze - if you have been killing the trash from Broodlord Lashlayer up to this point you will have plenty of it.\nThe key here is never let all five debuffs be up at once, as this will mind control your character - which will then kill your other character, and reset Chromaggus.\nKeeping the priest out of LOS of Chromaggus does not appear to work anymore, they will still receive the debuffs. As soon as a debuff comes up that can be removed, remove it - except Brood Affliction: Red, multiple stacks of this makes it pretty much impossible to keep off and keep dps up on your warrior so concentrate on keeping Brood Afflictions: Blue, and Bronze off your toons and keep dpsing - red will eventually start to hurt a lot so kill Chromaggus as soon as possible but ALWAYS make sure to keep those debuffs off.\n\n[b]Nefarian[/b]\n\nTank n spank, use the alcove* to channel all the adds into one place for easy pickup.\nMake sure your priest is close to your warrior so he doesn't get smashed by the adds later in the fight, they can still kill clothies fairly quickly - even at 85.\n\n*The alcove. When facing the throne turn 90 degrees to the right and you'll see a sort of short tunnel with rubble in it.\n\n\nHappy hunting!\nAth.", "date": "2011-06-16T04:48:04-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This was the best tactic to easily kill Razorgore that I've tried. Keeping the tank in the center will almost always get aggro from the adds away from the mind controller and Razorgore. My tank was an ilvl 400 warrior and I didn't have to worry about any form of healing.", "creationdate": "2012-06-20T11:06:46-05:00", "id": 550976, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1442507, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "raichoo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-06-24T20:01:07-05:00", 1, "Athenia"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 69, "id": 1460883, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "spectrefax", "body": "It's still bugged. Solo, you cannot use the mind control orb at all.", "date": "2011-07-05T00:09:15-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 70, "id": 1461439, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "672820", "body": "Regardless of what people have said about this, it [b]IS [/b]possible to solo right now without being a goblin or engi. I have no idea why some say the mind control orb doesn't work. It did for me.\r\n\r\nUsing my 85 ret (ilvl 358), I began by disposing of the controller and his friends and quickly taking control of Razorgore from below the platform, standing on the little ledge beneath. \r\n\r\nBurst as many eggs as possible before the MC breaks, while making sure Razorgore is nearby when I resume control of my paladin. You then kite him around, spamming AoE's to both heal yourself and dispose of as many adds as possible until it's time to take control of him again.\r\n\r\nThe trick to succeeding here is to reliably be able to evade Razorgore using the platform and ledge below, causing his health to reset. This doesn't reset the encounter. It can be a little difficult to master this part, but it's very possible.\r\n\r\nIt's vital to pick your moments as to when you should go breaking more eggs, I always made sure both Razorgore and myself were on full, or close to full health and preferably there would be few adds around too.\r\nI saved bubble to break the conflag when things looked to be getting a bit hairy, whether pvp trinket would also work I don't know, I didn't test it.\r\n\r\nOnce all the eggs were dealt with, it was fairly trivial to burn Razorgore down and collect my level 60 purples.\r\n\r\nAll in all it took about 15-20 mins to complete.", "date": "2011-07-05T11:45:16-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You cannot trinket conflagration but you can trinket the 5 sec stun  But the most important question is how evade Razorgore? You have to be much more specific than \"using the platform and ledge below\",use a screenshot or a video.", "creationdate": "2011-07-07T21:34:25-05:00", "id": 250886, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1461439, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "686039", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "confirmed, I stumbled onto this too, so I went here to look if someone else had found it and you clearly have. very easily soloable as a prot warr using this tact, the adds goes down when you're controlling the orb and as long as you try to keep the number of adds down his health won't be a problem either :D", "creationdate": "2011-07-14T07:19:24-05:00", "id": 252282, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1461439, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "148123", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This seems to have been patched as of the 8/16/2011 hotfix or so - Razorgore doesn't seem to evade at all now. :(", "creationdate": "2011-08-17T11:58:37-05:00", "id": 259109, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1461439, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "168916", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "yeah, seems some of anti-soloing fixes they did for firelands broke evade bug for razorgore.", "creationdate": "2011-08-17T14:33:55-05:00", "id": 259130, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1461439, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "raivo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This just in, a commenter at mmo-champ appears to have found a way for druids to solo this guy. Post/video are [url=http://www.mmo-champion.com/threads/977435-Glitchless-Razorgore-Solo]here[/url]. Basically the idea is to use [spell=54743] and stay under 50% health, so that regrowth will tick indefinitely and pull the adds onto you while you MC the boss. I've confirmed it works well enough, but it was pretty hairy with feral spec and gear around 365. In another tier or two it should be fairly straightforward.", "creationdate": "2011-09-19T20:49:47-05:00", "id": 265563, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1461439, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "168916", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 71, "id": 1464728, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "672820", "body": "EDIT: As promised here's a video I made tonight of a my paladin soloing Razorgore.\n\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GrfapltZ-K0\n\nIt's not really hard to figure it out. The \"platform\" is the podium-like structure with the mind control orb. The \"little ledge below\" is exactly that, a slightly raised lip at the front of the mind control orb platform.\n-\nI'll try to explain a little better:\n\nI'm using Seal of Righteousness and Righteous Fury.\n\n[b][u]The Pull [/u][/b]- Run in and head up the near ramp towards the MC orb, clear the mobs from the platform and use the orb, Razorgore will probably be pretty close at this point.\n\n[b][u]MC phase[/u][/b] - I usually jump off the front of the MC orb platform, onto the kerb in front. I may choose to use Holy Radiance or Consecration just prior to clicking the orb if necessary (it rarely is). Run around bursting eggs, generally I'll destroy the nearest one to me and then head to the far end of the room until the MC timer is nearly up. At this point I'll start heading back towards the MC orb, continuing to pop eggs on the way.\n\n[u][b]Post-MC phase[/b][/u] - I seem to have trouble manually breaking MC, whether it's a bug, or my UI I don't know. Anyway, once it's broken, I'll launch into a flurry of aoe in order to thin out the adds and \"hopefully\" evade Razorgore...\n\nThe best I can explain it is as follows.\n\nRun up one of the ramps to the MC orb and he'll follow, jump off the front and step onto the ledge below while spamming Divine Storm, Holy Wrath and whatever else you feel like using. If you time it right he'll evade, so will some adds most likely. The basic rules of evading mobs apply here, if you try to hit him when he can't hit you he'll evade. Divine storm from underneath him, hitting a couple of adds that have his attention seems to work. He will figure out how to reach you and run down the ramp a lot of the time, just keep trying.\n\nIt's also possible to do by being on top of the MC platform while he is on the floor below. Using Judgement to gain some distance from him while he's stopped to cast, he will sometimes get stuck just at the corner of the platform, on the ground, near the ramps at either side. When trying to evade him you have to make sure your attacks hit him so he \"notices\" he can't hit you in return and resets. I haven't got either evade technique down to a science yet, but on my latest kill, he didn't come close to dying so I'm getting better at it.\n\nOnce his health has reset, adds are under control and your MC debuff is gone, repeat the process until all the eggs are done.\n\nBubbling the conflag isn't required to complete it, it's just a bit of insurance in case I have trouble resetting his health, or adds are starting to get too much. I'm fairly sure other classes will be capable of using this tactic, providing they can heal themselves well enough.\n\nI've managed to clear the entire instance solo for three weeks running now, since discovering this tactic.\n\nGood Luck.", "date": "2011-07-08T17:32:12-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I don't seem to be able to trigger the evade anymore. I did it a few times in 4.2, but now as of 4.3 I wasn't able to do. Was this fixed?", "creationdate": "2011-12-16T15:10:12-06:00", "id": 497884, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1464728, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "193457", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-07-13T16:55:53-05:00", 1, "672820"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 72, "id": 1482482, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "710718", "body": "Conflagrate is what will get him kill in this fight. He constantly conflagrated me to the point that I was stunned for so long that he died to the adds. This is what always wipes me.", "date": "2011-07-29T13:29:27-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 73, "id": 1509927, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kaldrake", "body": "Razorgore can be two-manned, if you chose your classes carefully. Myself on a Smite-spec Disc Priest, and a Blood Death Knight were able to complete this event. \r\n\r\nYou do not [i]have [/i]to kill the adds. If you are a healer, you can heal Razorgore through the damage the adds cause him (PW:S works on him), while grabbing aggro from the Mind Controller using AoE abilities, and then kiting the adds off the platform (Holy Nova, Consecrate, Hurricane, etc).  If the mind controller gets the debuff, you can easily take over the orb, while they round up and kill adds (This requires an AoE class, or another healer class which has AoE capabilities. Rogues are capable of doing this easily, if they have the Glyph of Fan of Knives). \r\n\r\nRinse and repeat. Once all of the eggs are destroyed, be ready to AoE down any remaining adds, before going all out on the boss. \r\n\r\nThis method does have the highest percent for glitching once Razorgore is dead, from my experience. However, the adds will not (or should not), follow you into the next room. If you trust the person you're with, keep it on Group Loot, so that you can loot on the run. Otherwise, run completely out of the instance (ensure that any dead persons pop their corpses and res outside), and take a fifteen minute break.\r\n\r\nClasses which have pets will find that they are unable to click the orb of control. There is no work-around for this glitch, except for dismissing your pet until Razorgore is killable.", "date": "2011-09-04T06:20:29-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I dismissed my pet (hunter) and was still unable to use the orb.", "creationdate": "2011-09-25T16:16:26-05:00", "id": 266965, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1509927, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Nekrotik", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
