{"commentv2": 1, "number": 79, "id": 1575851, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "kabes", "body": "Is it just me or did they hotfix something here? This week on my weekly BWL solo the adds came out way sooner, I only got to destroy 2 eggs before they came, and when I jumped up to the ledge to reset Razorgore's health I was teleported back down. Anyone else?\n\nEDIT: seems to have been a fluke, but it happened 3 attempts in a row. 4th attempt everything was normal and he went down with ease.", "date": "2011-11-19T12:50:39-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-11-19T13:12:08-06:00", 2, "kabes"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 80, "id": 1582034, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "627078", "body": "He can easily be killed if you have two accounts and are good at window switching. \n\nThe method is quite simple, and has already been explained here: bring two characters on different accounts (85 feral and 70 rogue in my case), have the weakest one control the orb and the other aggro and kill the adds. A dual monitor setup, or two windows slightly overlapping are helpful to keep an eye on the chaneling bar.\n\nIt is easier than doing it with only one character, but still more challenging than bringing a friend. Not everyone will agree that this can still be called \"soloing\", but if you have two accounts and want a bit of fun, it is well worth the try.\n\nNow on to Vael!", "date": "2011-11-27T17:23:37-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I do this every week.", "creationdate": "2012-04-11T02:26:42-05:00", "id": 534887, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1582034, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "dle0105", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-11-27T17:24:54-06:00", 1, "627078"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 81, "id": 1585748, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "rebsten", "body": "While this is still impossible to solo, this is very easy to 2 man for a Prot warrior with any other partner.  Let me elaborate a bit.\r\n\r\nIf you spec prot, throw a few of your extra talents into Blood Craze.  Have your partner MC Razorgore.\r\n\r\nYou will clean the adds off your partner, then off Razorgore.  Avoid killing them.\r\n\r\nBlood Craze will be up almost constantly.  All adds will aggro onto you by default.  Just watch where you stand.  I prefer to stand about 41 yards away from the platform to force the caster adds to run to me and not AOE on my partner, however, you can also run in circles around the pillars if you prefer.\r\n\r\nKeep the melee adds away from Razorgore.  Even if they are aggro'd onto you, they will focus a very hard hitting move called [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=23967#comments:id=1585747]Dragonbane[/url] on Razorgore.\r\n\r\nAside from that, it should be a clean 2 man.  Happy farming.", "date": "2011-12-01T02:59:20-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 82, "id": 1594212, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "NephilimX", "body": "I just ran into something interesting that happened when I was just soloing on my hunter: I had done the first wave and despawned them, and hopped off the platform to engage again. I burned the two guards while making a run for the orb, clicked it, and at the very same time got hit with a rather unlucky conflagrate. The interesting part? The conflagrate didn't break my control. Despite being conflagrated and running about wildly, I was still safely channeling. Needless to say I wasn't expecting that. So if you happen to get hit by a conflagrate right as you're trying to control him, it won't leave you cursing with 30 seconds of a debuff to mess up your attempts.\r\n\r\n[b]tl;dr - if you get off a channel fast enough, an unlucky conflagrate amazingly won't break it and screw up your attempt.[/b]\r\n\r\nJust an interesting thing I felt might be worth mentioning, so someone in a similar situation doesn't just see the conflagrate and assume that control was blown, cause that's exactly what I did for the first few confusing seconds until I realized what happened.", "date": "2011-12-11T04:28:23-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 83, "id": 1616649, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "896952", "body": "looks like they've fixed the balcony issue at least for me. everytime I jump to the balcony to semi-reset, razorgore teleports me to him. Tried him 5 times before I stopped, each time he teleported me whilst on the balcony.", "date": "2012-01-25T08:52:49-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 84, "id": 1639644, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "scpovey", "body": "DUOED, in patch 4.3\r\n 1 prot warrior\r\n1 affliction lock\r\n\r\nStrategy:\r\nProt warrior gathers up all of the ads using regular melee swing so they don't die.\r\nLock kills the eggs while controlling razergore.\r\n\r\nVery simple", "date": "2012-03-14T21:03:37-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 85, "id": 1659133, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "123704", "body": "anyone wondering what syel said its simply this: this boss is not soloable due to the mechanics required to controll the boss and handle the mobs, any claiming to have solo'ed this boss is lying and to solo something it has to be by yourself if you have a friend (which is required to defeat this boss\" its duo'ing not solo'ing", "date": "2012-04-26T17:11:41-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You can solo this boss if you're a Warrior or Druid, who have enough passive healing threat to outaggro the boss and make the adds stick to you instead of the boss. Also, you can use the balcony glitch to reset the encounter and make the adds despawn if you're a Hunter, Goblin or Engineer. Which also allows to solo the boss.", "creationdate": "2012-05-01T04:44:02-05:00", "id": 540123, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1659133, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "193457", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-04-26T17:12:40-05:00", 1, "123704"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 86, "id": 1692211, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kaiokenx", "body": "Soloed legitimately as an arms warrior.\r\n\r\nLike many people have said, the whole strategy relies on the threat generated from blood craze, but it requires some finesse to pull it off. I am in defensive stance the whole time for the extra threat modifier. I spec into second wind as well in case Razorgore gets off a stomp, and as a human I can just racial trinket out of it which refocuses the adds back onto me while getting extra healing/threat. I basically use thunder clap to keep adds on me since it is low damage and I don't have to worry about taking chunks of life away from the boss. When I'm getting overran with adds, I just bladestorm.\r\n\r\nI'll start the pull not killing the three adds at the beginning in hopes of proccing blood craze for the first set of adds that spawn. I try to get the eggs closest to the orb first but I always manage to put Razorgore at the other end of the room to allow time for the orb debuff to fade and by the time he gets back, I can retake control before he can do anything serious. You have to sustain this for about 7-10 minutes without any major mistakes so just be patient because sometimes a bad conflag can ruin a great attempt.\r\n\r\nAfter attempting this 30+ times I can tell you that the game winner was when I started putting Razorgore way in the back of the room before I lost control. I could easily manipulate his path back to me and keep him from getting off a stun or conflag a lot easier.", "date": "2012-07-26T01:31:35-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 87, "id": 1698870, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vice92990", "body": "As far as Soloing as a Hunter / Goblin Doesnt seem to be possible anymore. If you get Razgor's aggro before you jump the the balcony  he will not teleport you to him.However if you have already got rid of some eggs or your jumping to the balcony for the 2nd time, you will notice when the adds reset and run away the eggs Respawn.\r\nAs of right now not able to find anyway around this.", "date": "2012-08-12T01:32:01-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 88, "id": 1703723, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "stasis007", "body": "Just to reiterate: Only click the orb ONCE! I was spam clicking the 1st couple of times and wondering why I always had the exhaustion debuff... \r\n\r\nI dual-boxed it. \r\n\r\nThere's almost no drama involved for the MC toon. All the adds will either be focused on the other Toon (or on Razorgore). Just sit tight if the debuff has a few seconds to go, and click calmly when it's clear. I ignored this toon until the channel (and debuff) were finished, and then switched over to click the Orb.\r\n\r\nThe 'add' Toon just needs to smack Razorgore lightly (or fire off a big heal), when the MC wears off, to get his attention. As a Ret, Divine Storm and the occasional Word of Glory was enough to keep all the Mages focused on me (use Righteous Fury). Cast off a manual heal now and then, if needed, to attract the Mages. Just noticed I passively healed Razorgore 260k with Divine Storm (yay Ret). But he was never in danger of dying. \r\n\r\nOnce I realized not to spam click the orb, it was an extremely easy kill.", "date": "2012-08-24T06:32:16-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 89, "id": 1714065, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "jdevlin7756", "body": "As of 5.0.5 this seems to be no longer soloable.  I've been doing this on my hunter every week for months and now it seems they've made it so that the adds re-appear half way through the second MC of Razorgore.  Had it happen on three attempts in a row (and no, I didn't mess up).  If anyone is still having luck with this, I'd love to know.", "date": "2012-09-15T13:56:50-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I soloed with my hunter today.", "creationdate": "2013-01-03T08:34:13-06:00", "id": 618731, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1714065, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kissji", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Soloed on my monk as well", "creationdate": "2013-01-08T05:05:58-06:00", "id": 620455, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1714065, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "rjosro", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 90, "id": 1736903, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ender111", "body": "As of 5.0.5 this boss is easily soloable by a warlock with the talent Grimoire of Sacrifice.  I used to do this boss by using the rocket jump to the balcony technique, but that is shot now.  The mobs just stand there and keep coming out while the boss attacks you with his ranged attack if you get to close to the edge of the balcony.  \r\nHowever, with Grimoire of Sacrifice (and using Dark Apotheosis), the passive healing is more than enough to draw the aggro of near every mob in the room.  You can push Razorgore to destroy eggs all the way til the timer ends.  Then just hit Immolation Aura and whack at the mobs, bust one of your healing CDs, and hit the orb again.\r\nOnce the eggs are all destroyed the mobs clear out and there's just the boss who goes down easily.", "date": "2012-10-09T19:28:43-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 91, "id": 1744148, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "noah450", "body": "a nice trick for hunters if you have it speced you can use exhilaration while you have him mced to heal him to full life since while he is mced he is considered your pet.this is nice for if adds have been attacking him and you want to make sure he dos not die b4 eggs are destroyed.note that when you use exhilaration however the mc will break.", "date": "2012-10-17T14:43:31-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
