{"commentv2": 1, "number": 93, "id": 1759935, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "warconz", "body": "I can still solo it on my hunter.... You who cant must be doing something very wrong.", "date": "2012-11-09T17:40:10-06:00", "rating": -8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 94, "id": 1760788, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "Brand", "body": "On the 5.1 PTR, Razorgore has a new drop: The [item=93036]. This teaches you to summon an Untamed Hatchling.\r\n\r\nTo help make the fight more solo friendly, a couple changes to the fight have been made. First, taking damage no longer stops you from channeling the orb. This means that even if you are attacked, you can still control Razorgore and kill the eggs.\r\n\r\nSecond, Razorgore's Destroy Egg ability now has a 1.5 second cooldown, down from 7 seconds.\r\n\r\nAs a Paladin, I was able to solo him on the PTR by controlling him and destroying as many eggs as I could, while healing up any damage received between controlling Razorgore himself. It may not be soloable for everyone, but it is definitely more possible than it was before.", "date": "2012-11-11T09:59:30-06:00", "rating": 58, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not sure if its me or not, but when I try to click on the orb, it never lets me control Razorgore.", "creationdate": "2012-11-29T06:38:11-06:00", "id": 604746, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1760788, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Alfa", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "@alfakennyone : If you are using a pet, be sure to dismiss it.", "creationdate": "2012-11-29T08:22:52-06:00", "id": 604794, "rating": 12, "commentid": 1760788, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mamadrood", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "No clue how people are soloing this guy. I can clear about half the eggs in the room before the adds just plain kill him and then his \"retributive strike mechanic\" auto kills me. And when I peel off the orb to take down some of the adds and heal up, he'll just chain stun and conflag me while the adds continue to kill him. It may have been doable on the PTR but don't think it is doable any longer on live.", "creationdate": "2012-12-01T02:29:22-06:00", "id": 605754, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1760788, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Mookosh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "@Mookosh&Lisanette It is hard yes,but if read carefully i am sure there is a working tactic on this very page ;)", "creationdate": "2013-07-06T06:24:48-05:00", "id": 675262, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1760788, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "NescioNetizen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Destroy Egg is now instant cast, making it even more soloable.", "creationdate": "2017-06-21T12:13:40-05:00", "id": 1058623, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1760788, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Foxpaw", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 95, "id": 1761138, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "skypunk", "body": "I must be one of those that's doing something very wrong..\r\nMy warrior can take the hits just fine, but Razorgore aggros very easily during MC' and gets killed off very fast when I try to solo.", "date": "2012-11-12T00:04:33-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "maybe try bring bandages to heal to pull threat on the whole room, or talent into victory rush so it always heals? you would have to break your orb early in other to pull off him regularly though. i also saw another warrior said he planted a mocking banner in the middle of the room to keep adds on him for a while", "creationdate": "2013-01-16T09:02:22-06:00", "id": 623264, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1761138, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "lolablerants", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 96, "id": 1762880, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "link55557", "body": "With the early raid changes on the 5.1 PTR, it SEEMS that taking damage no longer reduces the channel bar on the orb, making this fight easier to solo than ever before.\r\n\r\nBeware that the boss getting aggro will still be an issue, however.", "date": "2012-11-15T14:55:35-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 97, "id": 1767448, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sethala", "body": "Just fought Razorgore on the PTR.  Some thoughts:\r\n\r\nThe boss is a lot more durable than before, and can get beat on quite a bit before dying, but isn't invincible.  You'll need to be quick, and you might need some way to get the adds to go to you instead of him.  I was a mage with the Rune of Power talent and the glyph to make it heal you, but I don't know if that helped me get aggro much, or if they just went for me naturally.\r\n\r\nIf you're a clothie, you'll want to take a moment every so often to AoE the adds down.  It won't take long, but even though most of their attacks miss, they'll eventually wear you down.  Heavier armor types may not need to worry as much, though.\r\n\r\nFor those wanting pets for the achievement, I went on to clear the whole instance and all three pets dropped in the same run.  I don't think it's 100%, as I went on to kill Magmadar in MC and didn't get the pet from him, but the drop rate is definitely high.", "date": "2012-11-25T01:41:04-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 98, "id": 1768918, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "sdkphoenix", "body": "Just a couple tips to help solo this post-5.1. If you have any healing ability, use it between orb conrtolling. This will help to get mobs to aggro onto you and off of Razorgore.\r\n\r\nAlso it is suggested that eggs be destroyed in only 2 phases so Razorgore doesn't die.\r\n\r\nIt can take a little bit of luck to down him, so good luck to all thse who try and good luck getting the pets!", "date": "2012-11-27T15:58:29-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 99, "id": 1769087, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "852804", "body": "Razorgore The Untamed is still unsoloable, despite what the  5.1 patch notes said =/\r\nIf I'm wrong, then I'm having a hell of a time with him.", "date": "2012-11-27T18:36:02-06:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 100, "id": 1769098, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "944920", "body": "So, this boss is indeed solo-able with the recent patch.  After a few frustrating pulls I was able to do it on my 90 rogue.  For those that are having difficulty with getting agro because you don't have any large threat producing spells, I would recommend using [ins][item=86565 domain=www][/ins] after your first round of egg killing is done with.  There is no room for error when it comes to popping eggs, you need to make use of every second.", "date": "2012-11-27T18:50:34-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 101, "id": 1769174, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1058915", "body": "Razorgore is still extremely difficult to solo.  I've gone through a couple hundred gold in repairs and have still been looking at 7-8 eggs left.  There doesn't appear to be any way to break mind control, so either I die(Prot pally, level 90, ilevel 450) or razorgore dies.  I'm sure it's soloable, I'd just like to know what classes blizzard \"tested\" that soloable claim on (if they even tested).", "date": "2012-11-27T19:44:41-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 102, "id": 1769199, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chaosrock", "body": "As of patch 5.1 (when he is allegedly soloable), I am still unable to solo as a 473 elemental shaman. He just dies too fast. There is no way to kill the adds and keep him alive and destroy eggs. Ignore any claims of him being soloable, as they are untrue.", "date": "2012-11-27T20:04:58-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 103, "id": 1769219, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1058915", "body": "As of 5.1 I finally downed him:\n[ul]\n[li]Start the fight below the podium by clicking the orb while standing on the floor(not up on the podium)[/li]\n[li]Stand in place with razorgore until all the eggs on top of his platform are destroyed(you may have to adjust for the one in the back)[/li]\n[li]Clear from back to front one egg at a time (spam the key(4), if you're a mouser, it'll probably take too long)[/li]\n[li]Any dragons that come at you, use the calm mind ability(default 5) to sleep them[/li]\n[li]Halfway through the room, MC will drop.  Spam any AOE's and heal yourself up if you can to draw agro and kill the mobs beating on you[/li]\n[li]Keep working from back to front, destroying the eggs on the orb platform last and sleeping any dragons that come near you. Ignore any other bad guys. you don't have time to use any ability other than \"Destroy egg\" and \"Calm Mind\"[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nIf you're lucky and quick (and have a class that can handle the damage) you should be able to kill all the eggs, from that point, killing him is easy.\n\nGood luck to you and happy hunting.", "date": "2012-11-27T20:25:21-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-27T20:31:28-06:00", 1, "1058915"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 104, "id": 1769264, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chaix", "body": "little tip for ret pallies who are doing this guy: switch your talents so that you have [spell=114163], the hot will bring everything right to you and keep you alive while you're mc'ing the boss", "date": "2012-11-27T21:16:25-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 105, "id": 1769270, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "arty103", "body": "Well you guys must have better luck then me then. Just tried it on my prot pally ilevel 445. Have no probs keeping myself alive but there are just too many non dragonkin adds and razorgore goes down quicker then the eggs do. I agree that they shouldnt make it too easy to solo but come on....would have been better if they added a button to break mind control.\n\n\n\n*edit* just realized that but still no luck. guess im just slow, lol", "date": "2012-11-27T21:23:25-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Casting any of your character's spells/abilities will break the MC. So while your main Action Bar may change to the buttons for Razorgore, your other Action Bar(s) should still have your class abilties, etc... I broke the MC several times to cast Sacred Shield on myself and aoe some.", "creationdate": "2012-11-27T21:28:15-06:00", "id": 603825, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1769270, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kalici", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-27T21:34:19-06:00", 1, "arty103"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 106, "id": 1769293, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "arty103", "body": "i give up. bull$%^&. i've tried everything and got down to having like 5 eggs left. you guys are wayyyy luckier than I", "date": "2012-11-27T21:51:10-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 107, "id": 1769305, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dastank", "body": "5.1 does make razergore easier to solo, just a matter of keeping yourself constantly healed to maintain aggro off razergore, and smashing the eggs out fast enough so you dont fall over", "date": "2012-11-27T22:18:28-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 108, "id": 1769357, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Lancun", "body": "To the massive amount of folks thinking this is still impossible for their class to solo, and need a little bit of help, [item=86572] is awesome.\n \nThe Terracotta Guardian \"pocket tank\" is a really good trinket to bust out as soon as you start the fight.  After the first MC on Razorgore wears off and the adds slowly start pouring in, his aggressive charging and taunting slowly takes him towards the center of the room where he's more viable to pull adds off of Razorgore as you keep taking the eggs out.  Razorgore had about 50% health left by the time I was finished destroying all of the eggs.  This trinket truly kicks ass; it's allowed my Rogue to solo this, Onyxia, and Viscidus (using Elemental Force and spamming AR and Killing Spree wasn't quite enough to shatter him, this guy put me over the top of hits required).\n \nIt's paid off for the grind to get it from the rare in Valley tenfold already.", "date": "2012-11-27T23:24:34-06:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Definitely can help. The nice part is the timer will allow you to use him for Vael which helps those of us with lower iLvl gear to hit the DPS requirement while solo.", "creationdate": "2013-04-05T11:43:27-05:00", "id": 648608, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1769357, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "direpath", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Something EXTREMELY VITAL that needs to be noted is that the Terracotta Fragment MUST BE EQUIPPED. I failed to notice that it was a TRINKET, I thought it was just a usable item. I killed the first mobs guarding the orb, then tried to activate the fragment only to be told \"cannot be used in combat\", so of course I wiped.", "creationdate": "2016-06-29T13:12:46-05:00", "id": 949360, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1769357, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Lucilite", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-27T23:25:24-06:00", 1, "Lancun"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 109, "id": 1769364, "nreplies": 17, "sticky": 0, "user": "928896", "body": "As others have stated, as of patch 5.1 Razorgore is now soloable.\n\nI just finished killing him, and thought I'd post some tips for everyone... since it's still no walk in the park to do so.  The most difficult thing is keeping Razorgore alive.\n\n1. Run in, kill the controller, and click on the orb.\n2. Run Razorgore around, clicking on your \"Destroy Egg\" ability while standing atop (or just behind) the eggs on the ground.\n3. Keep this up until the adds start spawning. Wait until you have 3-5 adds on Razorgore, then click the \"Exit Vehicle\" button.\n4. [b]As soon as you exit the vehicle, most of the adds that WERE on Razorgore will switch to you[/b] (a few might stay on him, but not many). AoE your little heart out atop the platform for a few moments, killing as many as you can before Razorgore gets to you.\n5. Once Razorgore gets to you, you can try single targeting a few more adds around him down if you need to, just try not to hit Razorgore.  These adds will be on you at this point, so they're no longer much of an issue, since Razorgore takes a lot more damage from them than you will.\n6. Click on the orb again, rinse and repeat.\n\n[u][i][b]The key to doing this solo is to exit the \"vehicle\" of Razorgore often[/b][/i][/u].  Each time you do, you will reset the aggro of the mobs that WERE on him to you. This helps keep him alive, which is definitely the most difficult part of this encounter.\n\nEdit: I had stated that ALL of the adds switch to you when you exit the vehicle, which doesn't appear to always be true.  MOST will, however, and if you have a weak AoE that you can run over to Razorgore and do to get the adds off him (it won't take much) - without hurting Razorgore too much - that may help.\n\nHopefully this helps others!  I've tried out this strat on several characters now, and it works for me 100% of the time (even a \"squishy\" mage).", "date": "2012-11-27T23:35:14-06:00", "rating": 241, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I tried this strategy, and it works very well. One thing I noticed is that when I clicked the \"Exit Vehicle\" button, an error popped up, saying \"You cannot do that right now.\" As a remedy, you simply right click on the Razorgore frame attached to yours and \"Dismiss\" him.", "creationdate": "2012-11-28T04:51:38-06:00", "id": 604013, "rating": 40, "commentid": 1769364, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "magnusXcaboose", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "For me the trick was using a hot on myself. Exit vehicle, kill adds place a hot so I can take aggro off of Razorgore.", "creationdate": "2012-11-28T14:52:43-06:00", "id": 604344, "rating": 15, "commentid": 1769364, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "240853", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The order you kill the eggs also helps. Get the ones farthest away first, when you lose (or drop) control, kill adds, heal up, etc... When you resume control, focus on the eggs near the orb and work your way back across. I've noticed adds tend to ignore the boss (and sometimes even switch aggro) when Razorgore and the player are close together.", "creationdate": "2012-11-29T01:36:03-06:00", "id": 604619, "rating": 6, "commentid": 1769364, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "reidsb", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Do not accidentally double click the orb. It will disengage you and the 10 second mind exhaustion debuff can make things difficult with razor running loose for that logn after you've already got adds.", "creationdate": "2012-11-29T02:49:22-06:00", "id": 604642, "rating": 17, "commentid": 1769364, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "teppec", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Razorgore kept dying right before the last couple eggs on the far side of the room, so I found that immediately taking control of the orb (without killing the controller/guardsman) gave me enough time to kill all the eggs on and around Razorgore's platform before any adds spawned... and when the adds begin to spawn you can run closer to the orb to resume the method that everyone seems to be using (destroying eggs near the orb and working your way to the other side of the room), so that more adds run to you instead of Razor. Did as a hunter with no pet (bugged orb) and no healing of any kind.", "creationdate": "2012-12-03T10:12:42-06:00", "id": 607025, "rating": 15, "commentid": 1769364, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "1052070", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-28T00:59:01-06:00", 5, "928896"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 110, "id": 1769391, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Furydeath", "body": "IDk about you but it's unsoloable on my mage the orb doesn't work.", "date": "2012-11-28T00:10:22-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If you are frost and have a pet out you cannot use the orb, dismiss the pet and try again if this was the case.", "creationdate": "2012-11-28T03:09:31-06:00", "id": 603962, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1769391, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Baneleaf", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 111, "id": 1769434, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chromell", "body": "He is soloable by mages under certains conditions.\r\n\r\nMy solo: leave a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=56380]glyphed[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=116011]Rune of Power[/url] right where you'll be standing to control the orb and kill the ads near it, pop [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=11426]Ice Barrier[/url] and begin smashing eggs.\r\n\r\nNow this is where the problem begins, even thought you'll get aggro from some mobs, some other will still go after Razorgore. The boss has around 500k hp and will die fairly quickly so you have to be fast, make sure to put the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12416]dragonkin mobs[/url] to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=19872]sleep[/url] to minimize the damage the boss takes. As soon as the first channeling ends, pop [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=55342]Mirror Image[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=86572]this trinket[/url], they've helped keep many ads away from the boss and it gave me time to destroy the remaining eggs. I did it in Fire spec, but I believe Frost would be ideal with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=31687]another target to get aggro[/url],  considering he doesn't vanish once you touch the orb, just remember to leave it on Defensive so it can attack anything that bothers you regardless of what you're doing.", "date": "2012-11-28T01:00:26-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 112, "id": 1769472, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Danicalo", "body": "Easily soloed by resto shaman.  Start with the eggs on his platform and start working your way back toward you, when razorgore starts to get alot of adds on him and taking heavy damage (i did it around 50-60% health left) exit vehicle, heal yourself up.  When razorgore gets back to you drop healing stream totem and mind control him again, this will pretty much heal him back to full.  Rinse and repeat.", "date": "2012-11-28T01:51:54-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is 100% correct. I also have some additions I noticed for the Shaman soloists out there. If you have an elemental out and helping you (at least the non-talented version), you CANNOT control Razorgore. Also, any instant cast heals will work on him before breaking mind control, so you can riptide him, lose control, drop a healing totem, healing rain, heal self, retake control, and then have him hang out in the healing puddles for a moment before resuming egg destruction. I didn't kill a single add until all eggs were dead, and he finished that task at no less than 90% health.", "creationdate": "2012-11-30T10:04:31-06:00", "id": 605383, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1769472, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "zhixson", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 113, "id": 1769679, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "SINisterWyvern", "body": "For anyone looking to solo this now in 5.1 I wanted to share how I was eventually able to do it (just 3 tries) as a windwalker monk. This may not work specifically for everyone but should help in general.\n\nFirst start with the eggs on the furthest side before the mobs spawn. You can continue to do this probably the first couple of waves but be careful of his HP.\n\nIf he got more than a couple mobs on him at once I would break by healing myself w/ Expel Harm, then AE with Spinning Crane Kick. If you have spells available to heal Razorgore, break the MC with a heal on him, then heal yourself. You should have heal aggro on everything by then. I believe I was getting aggro from [spell=124334] Swift Reflexes killing mobs around me. (I could be wrong on that part however).\n\nWhen you do break, make sure he's far enough away to not get caught in the AE himself. \n\nRepeating this, I was able to break the eggs from furthest to closest before Razorgore himself died.", "date": "2012-11-28T05:51:27-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-28T05:52:20-06:00", 1, "SINisterWyvern"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 114, "id": 1769785, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "roenne", "body": "I finished a quick video via MOP 5.1 on how to solo razorgore: [url=http://tentblogger.com/solo-razorgore/]How to Solo Razorgore[/url]\n\nI'm a level 90 Rogue, sub/PvP spec. Nothing special here... pretty simple!\n\n****************UPDATE****************\n\nI've updated that post on June 21st, 2015, to include another video of me soloing with the same rogue with WoD 6.1.2! Same strategy, same thing.\n\nEasy-peasy!", "date": "2012-11-28T07:15:45-06:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I highly suggest watching this video if you are wanting to solo him. Killing the eggs close to the control orb first was the key and I was able to kill him on my first attempt using this strategy. Thanks for the video! As a 90 elemental shaman I was able to hold up to the adds attacking me, after the first MC ran out I healed and did some AoE to the adds, then used the orb again. His health got a little low towards the end, but not close enough that I was close to wiping. Good luck everyone!", "creationdate": "2012-12-01T21:26:07-06:00", "id": 606217, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1769785, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "tippy7", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Perfect plan...I failed about 10 times before watching this. Beat it the first try after this video!", "creationdate": "2012-12-19T16:41:24-06:00", "id": 613759, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1769785, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "cyzygy06", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Watched the video... he was doing it the same way I had been failing at doing it. I guess a fury warrior just dose not have the self healing needed for this... sucks because I wanted the teir 2 for transmog and no one on my server ever wants to do transmog runs.", "creationdate": "2013-05-15T21:45:55-05:00", "id": 658865, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1769785, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Taenamyr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I have updated that blog post to showcase WoD 6.1.2 solo! Easily done, same strategy!", "creationdate": "2015-06-21T19:46:06-05:00", "id": 876909, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1769785, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "roenne", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Watched the vid after 4 wipes, followed as close as possible, made it through. This worked (this time)! thanks~", "creationdate": "2015-10-02T16:09:24-05:00", "id": 902386, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1769785, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MissVern", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-06-21T19:45:15-05:00", 2, "roenne"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 115, "id": 1769814, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "WStilgar", "body": "It's doable, though not easy, for a warrior. The whole trick is after the first MC runs out, to kill as much of the adds as possible and then:\r\n\r\nDrop a mocking banner in the middle of the room, this will keep pretty much all adds on you, while you kill off the main chunk of the rest of the eggs, by the time your banner runs out, you will be almost done with eggs and the last few adds will not be enough to get Razorgore down if everything went okay.", "date": "2012-11-28T07:36:57-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 116, "id": 1769851, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1059102", "body": "Did this last night as a level 89 Prot warrior (with crappy gear). Took me about 6 or 7 tries. I used Enraged Regeneration to heal myself when i wasn't using the orb, and I used Bladestorm to quickly mow the adds down. \r\n\r\nI've read that threat is supposed to switch from Razorgore to the player automatically once the orb is turned off. This seems to be true, but it's not instantaneous. There were times where I felt the need to leave the platform and kite the adds (and the boss) around the room just to be sure I had aggro on them all. I used heroic leap and charge to stay ahead of the boss and get back to the orb in time to control him again. You can't be too conservative with the boss' health. Once he has 3-4 adds on him, you have to kill them or he won't survive.\r\n\r\nBest of luck! This CAN be done!", "date": "2012-11-28T08:16:49-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 117, "id": 1769908, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Celathien", "body": "How to solo this boss as a Priest. (Lightspring is useful, but any priest spec can do this)\r\n\r\nIf you are Holy, place Lightspring in the middle of the room. (you will have to refresh it midfight)\r\n\r\nGo near the orb, kill the controller and the 2 adds and click on the orb. Start by clearing the eggs near you.\r\nOnce the cast time is about halfway, or if there are too many mobs on the Boss, just move it to the opposite side of the room and use \"dismiss\" on your pet.\r\nImmediately heal yourself to get aggro off Razorgore and kill as many adds as you can before the boss gets to you. [b]Don't ever AoE if the boss gets close to you. Just heal yourself, kite him away while controlling him, dismiss and kill the adds.[/b] Quickly cast Renew/PoM/PW:S on yourself and click on the orb again, rinse and repeat. You might need to dismiss more often if you keep many adds alive since you will take quite a beating near the end.\r\n\r\nI killed the adds just 1 time and by the end of the fight there were a lot up, but I never came close to dying (if you do just dismiss Razorgore and heal/shield yourself).", "date": "2012-11-28T09:11:33-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 118, "id": 1769924, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "whiteraevyn", "body": "I am a Windwalker Monk, pure DPS with low healing abilities.\n\n[i][b]The trick to soloing this fight is, don't kill more than 25% of the adds.  A FIXED amount of adds appear on this fight, I believe it is 40.  If you do wipe out all the adds periodically, more will pour out of the four corners, beating Razorgore to death quickly.[/b] Also, DON'T let Razorgore get near you, as he will Conflagrate you, stunning you and causing the mobs to start beating on him.  He will then aggro some of the mobs to the point where mild healing abilities won't pull them off back to you.[/i] \n\nI stunned the mobs with Leg Sweep when I saw Razorgore's health going down too fast, then used any healing/damage absorbing abilties I had, [b]single-target[/b].  I then quickly mind-controlled Razorgore again before he could conflag me.\n\nTanking adds shouldn't be too bad as a healer, as you can heal yourself up fast and use it as an aggro-pull.\n\nSo to reiterate:\n\n1) DON'T kill all the mobs, tank them, using heal abilities to pull aggro periodically and keep yourself from croaking.\n\n2)  DON'T let Razorgore get too close to you before MC'ing him again.\n\n3)  I found a 75/25 balance of adds on you/him respectively to work okay.\n\nGood Luck!", "date": "2012-11-28T09:26:55-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Best advice for me was not to kill the adds. Ty!", "creationdate": "2012-12-22T00:42:15-06:00", "id": 614534, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1769924, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "tearsofkyrra", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-12-22T02:40:02-06:00", 8, "whiteraevyn"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 119, "id": 1769944, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nanocephalic", "body": "[b]He's easy to beat if you have an instant heal. This system should apply for any class that can target a heal on a friendly pet, which should include [s]hunters[/s], DKs and any healing-capable class.[/b]\n\nEdit: Apparently mend pet doesn't apply to this kind of pet. I seem to recall an instant pet-healing spell that hunters can spec into, other than that one.\n\nAs a melee druid, I was unable to beat Razorgore until I used the following system: \n\n[ul]\n[li]Put a targetable instant heal on a secondary quickbar[/li]\n[li]Add Razorgore as a focus target.[/li]\n[li]Stand on the ground, not the dais. Click on the orb and start the event. Ignore the adds.[/li]\n[li]No, really ignore the adds. I never attacked one of them[/li]\n[li]Keep Razorgore on his side of the room, and spam skill 4 (to destroy the eggs)[/li]\n[li]When there are more than two mobs on him, click on your focus (to target Razorgore) and hit an instant heal. As Guardian, I still have access to Rejuvenation which works fine. I also cast Rejuvenation on myself. (do not cancel the mind control - just cast the spell)[/li]\n[li]I think I needed to cast the heal only three or four times. As far as I can recall, only one tick landed on Razorgore.[/li]\n[li]As soon as possible, click the orb and continue popping eggs. Once the last egg pops, all adds run away and you can quickly dps the boss down.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nAt no point was I attacking anyone. I think the important parts of this system are to have an instant heal ready for casting, and to use it any time the boss has more than one or two adds. This system worked perfectly for me the first time I tried it.", "date": "2012-11-28T09:37:24-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Mend pet does not work for hunters during this encounter, also it is impossible to have a pet out while using the orb so Spirit Mend also was not an option for me.", "creationdate": "2012-11-28T11:03:58-06:00", "id": 604207, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1769944, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Hashupa", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Not sure why this is being downvoted so much; it has been working for all the people I know who've tried it.", "creationdate": "2012-11-28T19:38:24-06:00", "id": 604484, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1769944, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nanocephalic", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-28T19:41:12-06:00", 2, "Nanocephalic"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 120, "id": 1770040, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "jedimas729", "body": "I solo'ed this last night as a Prot pally easily and the way that I did it was:\r\n1. I ran in and killed the mobs at the orb.\r\n2. I mc'ed Razorgore and started killing eggs. I ran him to the farthest eggs, because he was further from me when I dropped the mc and when I finished with eggs he was nearby in melee range.\r\n3. I ignored all the adds beating on Razorgore and kept killing eggs.\r\n4. I let Razorgore get to about 20% health when I ran him close to me and targeted him. I used my lay on hands on him to heal him to full, consecrated, and re-mc'ed him. If I was getting overwhelmed with adds, I would use consecrate and hammer of righteous and holy wrath. That would kill the adds around me.\r\n5. I kept killing eggs and if Razorgore got low on health again, I would run him away from me and drop the mc and build up combo points on the trash, re-mc Razorgore and use Word of Glory on him. This was enough to keep him alive long enough to kill the remaining eggs.\r\n6. Once the eggs were all dead, the mc broke and I went to town on him with my prot dps. He wasn't alive for long.\r\n\r\nIt's important to remember that you can use healing abilities on Razorgore if you have him selected. It will break the MC but it'll heal him before it breaks. This is key because if you don't have any healing abilities, the adds will either overwhelm you or him. Bandages would also work but you'd only get one tick of it before the mc breaks and that's not enough to keep him alive for long. \r\n\r\nAlso remember to drop the MC every now and than to get the adds to agro onto you instead of him. The less you have to heal him, the faster you can kill the eggs. The cooldown on the egg breaker is now 1.5 seconds, down from 7 seconds it used to be. \r\n\r\nYou may be able to kill all the eggs without healing him if you drop the mc often enough to get most of the adds on you. I got lucky and he dropped the new pet for me. Good luck to you all! =D", "date": "2012-11-28T11:15:16-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 121, "id": 1770191, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Therulnig", "body": "I killed Razorgore today as a lvl85 Ret Paladin. After wiping only once due to an addon preventing me from using Destroy Eggs (yea..I know), I found it to be an easy kill.\r\n\r\nChanges I found:\r\n- MC is not lowered/broken by damage, and there was no delay in re-MCing him. \r\n- The adds no longer do extreme damage to him so he can tank some for a good bit, but he is FAR from able to ignore them while he destroys eggs. \r\n- Most importantly, When Razorgore is on your side of the room the adds will almost always go to you instead of Razorgore, and when adds do go to him while he is far away moving closer to your body will make them break from him and go to you most of the time. \r\n\r\nThe last mechanic mentioned basically made \"Adds killing Razorgore\" a non-issue in the fight as long as you are smart about your path in destroying eggs (don't stay on the other side of the room for too long). As others have mentioned if you have an instant heal you can pop it on Razorgore as well, but I did not need to do so in my encounter (He ended the phase with ~80% health). \r\n\r\n[b]I do not suggest trying to kill adds as they stack up, as this appears to only cause MORE adds to start flooding in. [/b] The real trick to the fight is keeping your body alive while you destroy eggs as more and more waves of adds start beating you. Classes with passive regen are easy (Warlocks with sac'ed pet, Warriors with Second Wind), all others will have to break MC ever so often to heal up, even my under leveled Ret spec Paladin with  no shield on kept himself up with Sacred Shield+Flash of Lights though.", "date": "2012-11-28T13:56:33-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As Therulnig said, don't bother with clearing trashes, when your MC finish cast some AoE if You think it's needed to get rid of some trash and click on orb again to regain control on Razorgore.", "creationdate": "2012-11-29T00:13:41-06:00", "id": 604587, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1770191, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sinirlan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Nope. Moving Razorgore to you wont make the adds break from him.", "creationdate": "2012-11-30T08:32:21-06:00", "id": 605351, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1770191, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "pepeu", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Pepeu - I've killed Razorgore every week since the pet was added, there IS a mechanic that causes adds to leave him and come to me without me having to generate any threat (no healing, mocking, etc), the way that always works for me is to step back towards my body as adds are running to him and almost all the time they'll stop in mid-run, do a 180, and come to me instead. I've never had him fall less than 60% health on a successful run like this.", "creationdate": "2012-12-11T14:14:42-06:00", "id": 610604, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1770191, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Therulnig", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 122, "id": 1770430, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dakumah", "body": "[b]Disregard all the comments about \"can't be soloed, Blizzard lie, blah blah\" as they're 100% INCORRECT![/b]\n\nThe fight itself is still the same in regards to kill the 3 on the platform, take control of Razorgore, destroy eggs and waves of adds spawn after 30 secs of the initial pull. Plenty of people have tried to kill him straight away which results in the normal wipe regardless of immunities used (eg Paladin Shield or Mage Ice-block). Also, if the adds kill him it's the same result. The adds spawn still do the same damage, which doesn't do much to a 90 individually but the more you have spawn on you the worse it gets. They'll still do the same damage as before to Razorgore so getting them off him is a priority, especially if he starts taking lots of noticeable damage.\n\n[b]IMPORTANT[/b] - The adds spawn constantly, there is no max number spawned at any time, they're endless and spawn in the 4 corners of the room. Don't let yourself or Razorgore get overwhelmed. These adds run away \\ despawn once Razorgore destroys the last egg. \n\nHOWEVER, and this is a BIG HOWEVER, there are 2 very big changes to this encounter:-\n\n1) No more debuff from using the Orb. This means you can release him at [u]any time[/u] and retake control when ready. Just remember 1 key thing - if Razorgore reaches the orb he destroys it and kills you instantly.\n\n2) Razorgore's Destroy Egg has [u]no cooldown[/u]. This means you can clear all the eggs really fast if you just focus and don't mess around with any of his other abilities.\n\nHe's soloable as I've done so around 10 minutes ago with the greatest of ease.", "date": "2012-11-28T17:00:57-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This post is misleading. First off, there is still a debuff. It is greatly shortened in duration however and should prove to be of no consequence. Don't mash the orb, click once and wait for it to kick in. Second, you do not die if he reaches the orb. I have had him walk right up and conflag me when I do not keep him far enough away. If you died, it was likely because you killed him.", "creationdate": "2013-04-05T11:17:54-05:00", "id": 648601, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1770430, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "direpath", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-28T17:05:07-06:00", 2, "Dakumah"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 123, "id": 1770498, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "296365", "body": "As a Frost DK (regular DPS build and gear) it was easy when I started Razorgore close to me (it seemed to keep much more of the adds on me instead of him.) When I took control of Razor too early/too far away he got way too many adds and died on my 2 tries like that.\r\n\r\nFor my kill I killed the 3 adds at the orb and waited for Razor to get close to the dais with the controlling orb (but MC him before he gets on the dais so he doesn't conflag you.) I then started destroying the eggs on that dais and across the room toward the other side. When the first MC was getting ready to run out I ran him to the opposite dais (destroying eggs up there until it ran out) and then killed all of the adds currently on me (like 2 frost blasts) and then took back Razor and easily finished off the rest of the eggs without either of us getting low HP.\r\n\r\nAfter the last egg is destroyed he goes back to full HP but is an easy kill.", "date": "2012-11-28T18:14:20-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 124, "id": 1771183, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "pengo", "body": "Useful information for soloing in patch 5.1 :\r\n\r\n* The ability to destroy eggs has a 1.5 sec cooldown instead of 6 sec\r\n\r\n\r\n* MC as soon as possible\r\n\r\n* Destroy eggs on the MC platform first, then hug left, destroying eggs along the way, and make sure you can destroy all eggs on the opposite platform in the back. Your MC spell will start running out, so move Razorgore back to the starting platform\r\n\r\n* AoE adds as much as you can, killing as many as you can.\r\n\r\n* MC again, and destroy all remaining eggs\r\n\r\nI had him left with 33% hp before he dismissed adds, so it should hopefully work for you.", "date": "2012-11-29T10:03:00-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I dunno what I'm doing wrong, every time I leave vehicle he still has like 7 adds on him, and I can't AOE without doing serious damage to him to pull them off quickly. So he takes a ton of damage regardless.", "creationdate": "2012-11-29T15:41:12-06:00", "id": 605010, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1771183, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sunfox", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The adds are very sensitive to healing aggro, so any sort of self heal should stick them right to you.", "creationdate": "2012-11-30T10:09:15-06:00", "id": 605388, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1771183, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "zhixson", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 125, "id": 1771449, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Akgis", "body": "As a warlock soloing this for pet farming in 5.1 is easy, \n\nMake sure u have a HS, spec Grimoire of Sacrifice for the HOT, lifetap to low HP so the healing develops threat.\n\nThis way the adds go to you instead of Razergore letting you destroy eggs pacefully as you draw the adds to smack you instead of him.", "date": "2012-11-29T16:07:40-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-29T16:09:07-06:00", 1, "Akgis"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 126, "id": 1771495, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "billimek", "body": "I was able to complete this as a hunter after three attempts:\r\n\r\nI specced into Survival and took the 'Exhiliration' talent for a self-heal thinking that the heal would draw aggro.\r\n\r\nThe first thing I did was kill the three mobs near the orb and then quickly dropped a explosive trap and ice trap near me on the platform.  Then took control of the orb (you can't have an active pet BTW).\r\n\r\nLike others stated, I cleared the eggs on the MC platform first and then made my way along the left wall towards the other platform and cleared there.  The MC dropped just as I had razorgore jump down from the platform.\r\n\r\nNext I quickly hit exhiliration/healing potion/deterrence followed by dropped an explosive trap at my feet and then a quick multishot at the mobs around me and then took control of the orb just as Razorgore was walking up the steps.  I continued to clear eggs and the MC timed out again while Exhiliration was still on cooldown so I popped readiness and then did Exhiliration/multishot (can't remember if I had time to drop another explosive trap).\r\n\r\nRazorgore was down to about 5% health when I destroyed the last egg.  Then it was simply a matter of summoning the pet and DPSing him down.\r\n\r\nI didn't think it was possible to solo as a hunter but turns out that it is.", "date": "2012-11-29T17:24:02-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed, it works. Be sure to spam the number 5 move on Dragonkin to CC them. Helps a bit. I finished the eggs with about 75% on Razorgore.", "creationdate": "2012-12-03T13:18:25-06:00", "id": 607093, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1771495, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ultimakage", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 127, "id": 1771575, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Jeolene", "body": "So, I've been trying this for the past couple of days after 5.1 came out and found that there is no 'leave vehicle' button, the adds can disrupt your channeling and will not come after you even if you do break the channeling.  I also noticed that some of the eggs did not \"die\" when I tried to destroy them, having to do them twice.  Seems things are glitched or blizz put things back they way they were with this new patch to keep us from just walking in and steamrolling the raid.", "date": "2012-11-29T19:41:08-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You can stop channeling by dismissing Razorgore as your pet.", "creationdate": "2012-11-29T20:28:37-06:00", "id": 605127, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1771575, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Professori", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I will have to look into that, everything I read said to use the \"leave vehicle\" button", "creationdate": "2012-11-30T02:11:01-06:00", "id": 605237, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1771575, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Jeolene", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You should still have full access to all of your abilities, so doing anything that isn't Razorgore related should drop control of him.", "creationdate": "2012-11-30T10:08:21-06:00", "id": 605385, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1771575, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "zhixson", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 128, "id": 1771795, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Furydeath", "body": "Ya this sure if soloable minus the 5 eggs you can't get cause the boss dies from only have like 3 mobs on him.", "date": "2012-11-30T01:47:24-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 129, "id": 1772004, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Googla", "body": "Control Razorgore, destroy as many eggs as you can. If you get aggro dismiss him by clicking his frame then heal you own character. This will make you aggro his enemies. Dont kill them with your char it will only spawn more. Keep on doing this, and when you killed all the eggs, kill him slowly otherwise he will whipe the whole raid because of some bug. \r\n\r\nSo to sum it up.\r\n\r\n> [b]Control him[/b]\r\n> [b]Heal yourself to take aggro from him[/b]\r\n> [b]If you kill adds they will respawn[/b]\r\n> Use bearform if you are druid and MCing him. \r\n\r\nEasy stuff.", "date": "2012-11-30T08:11:41-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 130, "id": 1772580, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "RhymeBomb", "body": "I just solo'd him as a monk that's barely geared for LFR. I didn't use any particular strategy other than \"GO REALLY FAST.\" I controlled Razorgore and started destroying the eggs closest to his side of the room and slowly made my way to the other side. As soon as I lost control, I spin-kicked the **** out of the accumulated mobs and then immediately controlled him again. I ended up killing the last egg with only a few seconds to spare, and about 20k health left on my guy.", "date": "2012-11-30T21:51:40-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-30T21:52:11-06:00", 1, "RhymeBomb"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 131, "id": 1772754, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "R2detoo", "body": "I just soloed this as a [b]Shadow Priest[/b] (ilvl 473) on first try, although it was almost a wipe.\r\n\r\nDestroy the eggs as quickly as possible; when the mind control ends or you are too low on health:\r\n  - shield yourself, \r\n  - AOE the adds \r\n  - heal yourself, \r\n  - and start over again.\r\n\r\nOn the last egg, Razorgore was on 1% health... so a very close call!\r\n\r\nHope this helps!", "date": "2012-12-01T02:56:15-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 132, "id": 1772848, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Storsiken", "body": "[item=86565] was extremely helpful. Break eggs until the control runs out the first time, use the horn to get most mobs off Razorgore and use the orb again to finish off the eggs.", "date": "2012-12-01T05:45:23-06:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Sadly, this was converted to a toy that only works in Pandaria.", "creationdate": "2017-01-12T02:00:20-06:00", "id": 1023761, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1772848, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "albinoette", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 133, "id": 1772880, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Yark1y", "body": "Down pretty easily from 1st try.\nRetribution paladin.\n\n[url=http://youtu.be/_Pv0cmLf_d8]Kill video[/url]", "date": "2012-12-01T06:54:28-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "How do u force those small mobs attack your paladin??? I tried as guardian druid and failed. when i loose control, many many mobs are on boss :-\\ but i saw your adds were going straight to your paladin skipping the boss u're controlling.", "creationdate": "2012-12-01T11:48:23-06:00", "id": 605982, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1772880, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "WebDev", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "There is no need. When you \"uncontrol\" them they will autoattack you + i use hot and hammer of light to prevent them attacking Rzorgore.", "creationdate": "2012-12-01T16:52:15-06:00", "id": 606120, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1772880, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Yark1y", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Im interested.. What are downvotings for..", "creationdate": "2012-12-04T06:47:34-06:00", "id": 607465, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1772880, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Yark1y", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-12-01T10:32:51-06:00", 2, "Yark1y"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 134, "id": 1773021, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "thejokernodq", "body": "The worst part of this whole darn new fight is the loooooooooooooong way back if by some chance you wipe or glitch out and die!", "date": "2012-12-01T11:14:03-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "That long fly and then running by foot is indeed very annoying :( i actually quit trying to solo it after like 4 tries just because of that stupid running as a ghost :(", "creationdate": "2012-12-01T19:40:29-06:00", "id": 606179, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1773021, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "WebDev", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 135, "id": 1773053, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "fox436", "body": "So it's still a pretty stupid fight for Warlocks as our pets make up one of our specs and grimoire of sacrifice isnt enough to offset the amount of damage you need to be healing from with siphon life / harvest life (granted its not ticking off on RG). Would like to hear someones' advice for warlock solo'ing of this encounter.", "date": "2012-12-01T12:06:45-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Spec into Soul link and Grimoire of sacrifice. Just sac your blue friend and you will start the fight with 2% hp healing buff and 20% hp buff. Just kill the first 3 npcs and start controlling razorgore asap, and just smash eggs, don't even try to dps coming adds, they will aggro on you with the healing buff. Focus on breaking eggs by going the other side of the room and when you'll lose control, just aoe the adds on you and take control again. Rinse repeat, and I managed to kill him the first try today :)", "creationdate": "2012-12-02T15:32:28-06:00", "id": 606613, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1773053, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "francus", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 136, "id": 1773661, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "blasphemous9", "body": "Just thought I'd add my two cents on how I solo this guy after 5.1.\r\n\r\nAny class with a instant HOT ability, preferably spec'd into your heal spec but I did it on my shadow priest without problems.  IE Renew, Rejuvenation, Riptide, and whatever that pally eternal flame thing is that HOT's.\r\n\r\nIf his health starts to dip just select him while you still have him MC'd then cast your hot.  The MC will end but your super duper high level HOT will be applied and pretty much heal any damage he'll take.  I had to do it twice, along with healing myself up.\r\n\r\nMakes it pretty easy.  Also worth noting that a shaman using Healing tide/stream totems will have their hot applied too.\r\n\r\nI'll come back and let you know how I do this on my non-HOT classes when I figure it out :)", "date": "2012-12-02T05:06:50-06:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Dude - you have no idea how much I love you for this advice:D You saved my sanity. As a paladin I went Prot,got some crappy gear, I chose Eternal Flame as my 3rd tier talent and healed him whenever he lost too much hp. It helped me in two ways - it healed him obviously and second - I could loose control of him whenever I wanted when I cast EF. This helped me clearing out the adds. For some reason I couldn't loose control of him without casting EF - I kept pressing the button for \"Exiting Vehicle:D\" but I was getting a message - you can't do this roght now. Your comment saved my life:D", "creationdate": "2012-12-02T15:48:21-06:00", "id": 606619, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1773661, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bobrock1982", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "@bobrock: If you right-click on Razorgore's portrait, select 'Dismiss' and that will do the trick.", "creationdate": "2012-12-03T04:53:55-06:00", "id": 606914, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1773661, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Unpossible", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I found this method far more difficult than only ever healing myself to keep the adds on me. If you put a hot on Razorgore, he will get agro of a lot of the adds, however only ever healing yourself will keep pretty much all of the adds on you.", "creationdate": "2012-12-03T23:37:10-06:00", "id": 607335, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1773661, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tyranea", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Weird, any hots on Razorgore should count as aggro towards you since you're doing the healing....", "creationdate": "2012-12-08T14:53:24-06:00", "id": 609325, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1773661, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "blasphemous9", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 137, "id": 1774124, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sarolyn", "body": "After 5.1 this fight is pretty simple as a demonology warlock, just grab the grimoire of sacrifice talent.  \r\n\r\nI successfully attempted this earlier today in Dark Apotheosis with grimoire of sacrifice.  It appears that the 2% heal would pull (most) mobs right off Razorgore and straight to me, and because of that I was able get the eggs down pretty quick.  \r\n\r\nThe heal would (for the most part) keep my health in check, I don't think I ever went below 2/3 HP.", "date": "2012-12-02T16:54:22-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 138, "id": 1774476, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Giondi", "body": "A tip for Paladins wanting to solo him: Take Holy Prism and cast it on him while he's MC'd. This will heal him up and deal a good amount of damage to everything near him, which should ensure that you get aggro on everything. Eternal Flame is also a good talent to have for this fight, on the pull, get at least three charges of Holy Power, MC Razorgore, when you want to break the MC, apply a (for the level of content) huge HOT. Both are pretty good since keeping the boss alive is the biggest challenge in the encounter.", "date": "2012-12-03T04:29:43-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If your channeling though, how do you cast HP on him? When you stop channeling he becomes hostile again", "creationdate": "2012-12-03T22:52:51-06:00", "id": 607315, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1774476, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "dlbert2000", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Dilbert - Put him on Focus (target him and type /focus) then make a macro starting with the line /target focus then /use [Whatever instant healing spell] and it will heal him and break your MC at the same time.", "creationdate": "2012-12-11T14:08:09-06:00", "id": 610603, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1774476, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Therulnig", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Casting a spell breaks the MC channel, but at the time that you press the button, Razorgore is considered to be your ally. Either focus him and use a cast to focus macro or just target him when you MC him. This works with any instant cast spell, so LoH will work, SF can be used for the HoT. Other classes like Resto Druids can do lots of stuff. I haven't done it myself to confirm, but I think Resto Shamans can Earth Shield, but I'm still working on the last few levels of mine to try it.", "creationdate": "2013-01-05T05:38:31-06:00", "id": 619387, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1774476, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Giondi", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 139, "id": 1775033, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kiingy", "body": "I had some trouble at first with soloing him as a Hunter.\r\n\r\nFirst up, Mend Pet and Spirit Bond do not work with Razorgore.\r\nYou will also be unable to use any pets with the exception of Stampede.\r\n\r\nI tried as all 3 specs and BM was the easiest.\r\nBefore you start grab a spirit beast pet and [item=43356] if you don't have 5 of them.\r\n\r\nStart the fight as usual, drop an explosive trap (unglyphed) at your feet and start killing the eggs. You should keep aggro until the first MC runs out and the explosive trap will handle everything excluding the dragons. \r\n\r\nKeep dropping explosives and throwing Multi-Shots and Glaive Toss between mind controls.\r\nOnce you're on low HP, pop Stampede on the mobs near you drop an explosive trap if its off cooldown and get back to the eggs while they clean up the trash. All 5 pets should drop their HoT on you getting you back to full HP.\r\n\r\nOnce stampede ends, Razorgores abilities bug and become greyed out, you will have to drop and remind control. \r\n\r\nEach time MC drops most of the adds on Razor will run to you, so do it frequently and keep dropping explosive traps.", "date": "2012-12-03T20:24:41-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 140, "id": 1775221, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "orcsmash", "body": "OK I just soloed this as a Blood DK, it's soloable but not faceroll, I wiped a few times before figuring out that you MUST cancel the MC when ever mobs are running towards Razorgore so they switch aggro to you instead, you can use that oppurtunity to get in a couple of death strikes to keep your health up.\r\n\r\nIf you don't break MC and force mobs to switch aggro to you constantly, Razorgore will die.\r\n\r\nUsing this strat I was able to kill him pretty easily.", "date": "2012-12-04T04:02:09-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 141, "id": 1775392, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "brothernads", "body": "This is how I soloed him as a prot paladin in decent gear (475 ilevel). Before the fight, I made a /tar razorgore macro and bound it to a hotkey.\r\n\r\n-- Killed adds on platform and clicked on MC orb.\r\n\r\n-- Destroyed eggs on platform first, then worked my way along one side of the room, destroying each egg along the way.  I made it to an egg right before the far platform before the adds started spawning.\r\n\r\n-- Dismissed Razorgore and threw down Consecration and a Flash Heal on myself to build a little aggro.  Reclicked orb before Razorgore got to me.\r\n\r\n-- Killed more eggs around the room.  Razorgore can take some pounding, just used the /tar macro to monitor his health.  When he got to about 35%, I moved him toward me, used the /tar macro and cast Lay on Hands to heal him up to full.  Reclicked orb after heal.\r\n\r\n-- Killed the remaining eggs then killed him.  \r\n\r\nYou may have to dismiss Razor and kill adds/build aggro periodically so all the adds don't go directly to him.  Just make sure he doesn't reach you, otherwise he'll cast Conflagration and you will be dazed & unable to click the orb to re-apply MC.", "date": "2012-12-04T11:59:15-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 142, "id": 1775683, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wulfrick", "body": "First time soloing tonight. I BARELY got him.  After several tries, this was the strat that worked for me:\r\n\r\n- Flasked and fed Prot Warrior (for the stamina to take a long beating from a lot of adds)\r\n\r\n- MC Razorgore and get to work on the eggs as fast as possible, starting with the platform you're on and taking the shortest route to the next one.  Get about halfway across the room and start making it trhough the center, always going for the closest egg, until you're at the opposite side of the ramp you went down the platform from. If you take the perfect route you can get the far half of the room in one MC.\r\n\r\n- When first MC breaks, Razorgore should be on the far opposite side of the room, giving you time to take care of some adds before he gets close.  Throw every AOE you've got to eliminate a few adds, then before Razorgore gets over to you (and you start accidentally damaging him), throw down Mocking Banner and re-MC boss right away.\r\n\r\n- Get the closest egg to Razorgore, which should be real close to your body (ie you'll be right on top of the adds but 30 second of Mocking Banner will be keeping them off boss), and work your way around, up and over the platform near the MC orb, ending with the eggs in the middle, again, always going for the nearest one to maximize eggs destroyed.\r\n\r\nI was able to get all the eggs in 2 MCs and that was with my last egg being on the far opposite side of the room from the MC orb (I walked away a split second too early and it cancelled it), but I made it with maybe 3 seconds to spare.\r\n\r\nThen it's just tolerate Razorgore's MCs while you beat the snot out of him (heal as needed but at 417k health, a few Victory Rush's ... should survive). And bonus, he dropped the pet for me.", "date": "2012-12-04T21:04:22-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 143, "id": 1776253, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "938583", "body": "Im trying to solo him but theres no option to \"dismiss\" him or \"leave vehicle\" as others say. While i had on my addons there was a button to \"leave vehicle\" but clicking on it did nothing. When my addons were all turned off there was no such button whatsoever. This is extremely frustrating as towards the end of the fight the adds start ganging up on him and i cant remove control so i can get aggro", "date": "2012-12-05T18:20:01-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This was from before the days of vehicle combat. You need to right click on his portrait frame and select \"Dismiss\" like he was a hunter pet. Then he will drop aggro correctly for you.", "creationdate": "2012-12-05T23:07:09-06:00", "id": 608188, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1776253, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "365880", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "you can use any ability and it will break the mc.", "creationdate": "2012-12-06T04:16:15-06:00", "id": 608269, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1776253, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "icausewipes", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 144, "id": 1776366, "nreplies": 9, "sticky": 0, "user": "365880", "body": "Important note for those solo'ing this boss:\r\n\r\nThis is from before the days of vehicle combat, so there is no actual \"Leave Vehicle\" button.  While you can hit the Esc key to drop out of him, this will cause Razorgore to maintain whatever aggro he had while you were controlling him, and this will make him die rather quickly.\r\n\r\nIn order to get the adds off of him and to focus on you, you need to right click Razorgore's frame and select \"Dismiss\" as if he were a hunter/demon pet.  If you do this, he will drop aggro properly and everything will come running to you.  Do this any time he starts taking noticeable damage.\r\n\r\nAt that point you just heal and AoE down as much as you can, then control the boss again.  Lather, rinse, repeat until all the eggs are down.", "date": "2012-12-05T23:06:04-06:00", "rating": 179, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This...made my day. It doesn't just make it possible to solo...it makes it easy. Very easy. Thanks a lot, I was just pressing esc or AoEing the adds to take me out of mc and wiped sometimes.", "creationdate": "2012-12-06T10:44:14-06:00", "id": 608371, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1776366, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mjinsane", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thank you! This made all the difference!", "creationdate": "2012-12-12T19:26:49-06:00", "id": 611044, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1776366, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "wands46", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This was incredibly helpful. As stated above this made the fight incredibly easy to do.", "creationdate": "2012-12-15T20:10:26-06:00", "id": 612256, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1776366, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Topojijo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Tonight, it appears that even dismissing doesn't cause him to drop aggro even after several attempts.", "creationdate": "2012-12-30T19:26:57-06:00", "id": 617417, "rating": 14, "commentid": 1776366, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "eeedge", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "There is some degree of timing involved. It will drop aggro early on and if you are close to the orb. The farther into the fight you are and the farther away from the orb you get, the less aggro it seems to drop. So start with the eggs near the orb, drop, then power through the last ones. If you're at at least half health on Razorgore by the time you get to the end, you're golden.", "creationdate": "2013-02-06T18:41:50-06:00", "id": 630287, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1776366, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "365880", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 145, "id": 1776666, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Birdyjuice", "body": "Well this was a pain. I don't have MoP so I'm trying on 85 characters.\r\n\r\nMy warrior I go close,  but ended up failing repeatedly. Disaster on my Moonkin. Didn't want to try many of my other characters.\r\n\r\nFeral druid was up next.\r\n\r\nI was able to kill the controller quickly in Bear form. Then got a good amount of eggs down. After that I just dismissed Razor when the timer was low. Put a rejuv on myself, and used a healing touch along with any defensive cooldowns. Maybe swiped a time or 2 and went back to eggs.\r\n\r\nThe first time I let Razor get too low and missed it by 1 freaking egg. The next time I got it easily.\r\n\r\nSo Ferals are a good choice for an annoying freaking boss to solo.", "date": "2012-12-06T12:13:22-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "get mop it will help", "creationdate": "2012-12-07T10:03:26-06:00", "id": 608789, "rating": -2, "commentid": 1776666, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "akilleuss", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed, able to do it in Guardian spec. Don't forget that you can use tranquility as an instant aggro generator to get them mobs off the boss...", "creationdate": "2012-12-07T15:54:01-06:00", "id": 608902, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1776666, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "togahsisoka", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 146, "id": 1777651, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "draenen", "body": "I posted this somewhere else earlier today, but to reiterate here: the trick to soloing Razorgore as a mage is to glyph evocation to regen health and to use Rune of Power, but it's also important to NOT use Ice Barrier - the adds need to do damage to you so that the rune can heal it up so that you generate healing aggro on the adds.\r\n\r\nIf Ice Barrier is active, you aren't taking damage, so your rune isn't healing you, so you're not generating any healing aggro, so the adds stick to Razorgore.\r\n\r\nI went from Razorgore dying with 1-5 eggs left to him destroying all the eggs with half his health left by doing it this way.\r\n\r\nHope this helps.", "date": "2012-12-08T08:21:54-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed. Level 90 mage (ilvl 469, 350k health, 13k armor.) Ran up and clicked the orb. Had Razorgore smash the eggs on the egg platform. Dismissed my Razorgore pet by rightclicking his portrait. Cast Rune of Power under me. Clicked the orb as Razorgore neared the orb platform. Had Razorgore smash all eggs near the orb platform. Ran him to east end of room. Dismissed, Rune of Power, reclicked orb. Smashed the rest of the eggs. Rune of Power, Ice Barrier, Blizzard til win. To hit Greater Invisibility by accident is instant death, unmap it.", "creationdate": "2012-12-10T08:09:27-06:00", "id": 610095, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1777651, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "699483", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "THANK YOU SO much!", "creationdate": "2012-12-18T19:15:06-06:00", "id": 613429, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1777651, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Anarchangel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 147, "id": 1777739, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "365880", "body": "Also note that Razorgore counts as a controllable pet, and WoW will only ever let you have one controllable pet out at a time.  Its already been said, but dismiss your hunter pet and your warlock demon to be able to use the orb.\r\n\r\nHowever, uncontrolled pets may still exist while you control the boss.  Uncontrolled pets are those that you cannot issue orders to.  These include pets summoned from trinkets, shaman elementals/spirit wolves, and warlock demons like wild imps and infernals/abyssals.\r\n\r\nDemo Warlocks especially should have an easy time of this one, as you can mind control for the first round, hit Hand of Gul'dan on the throng around you when the control ends to summon up maximum wild imps, and then drop your infernal/abyssal.  They will continue clearing adds for you while you return to breaking eggs.", "date": "2012-12-08T11:49:43-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 148, "id": 1777773, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "xtinakat", "body": "As an Ele shaman and after many attempts the only way I managed to pull this off is to work from the orb side of the room and making sure I have Razorgore as far away from me at the end of the MC channel as possible. In the few seconds I had before he made it back over to the orb I pop magma totem to make sure Im doing damage to the adds, toss a quick healing surge on myself and put Healing Rain in the middle of the floor. As soon as Razorgore was MCd again Id put him in healing rain for a few seconds because my biggest issue across the board was him dying and the little bit of healing  to him made a huge difference.", "date": "2012-12-08T13:11:00-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 149, "id": 1778278, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Aurorah89", "body": "Just solo'ed  him as a Blood DK. Wiped so many times but realised that killing the adds wasn't the most important thing. I found [spell=108199] was the best thing to use in this fight. It has a one minute cooldown but you can destroy the eggs and keep the aggro off of Razorgore just long enough.\r\n\r\nFirst I destroyed as many eggs as I could before the adds started spawning then removed MC once Razorgore gained aggro, then used [spell=108199] on him which pulled his adds towards me. I aoe'd as many as I could while far away from Razorgore then MC'd him again. Don't worry about killing the adds, just make sure you pull them away from him whenever you release MC and have the spell off cooldown and keep yourself alive. It was a close call but it worked =)", "date": "2012-12-09T08:50:53-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 150, "id": 1778470, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Glaucus", "body": "Tips as a shaman: use your earth/fire elemental (and spirit wolfs if enha).\r\nI think you're not allowed to have the improved elementals talent, because they will despawn then when you MC the boss....I'm not sure about this.\r\n\r\nThis way you'll barely have to keep an eye on the adds, as your pets will just kill and agro them all.\r\nI'd suggest doing this after you lose control the first time (or if there are too many nuking razorgore).", "date": "2012-12-09T15:12:53-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 151, "id": 1778568, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "toppjubei", "body": "Very easy as prot warrior. Get straight onto killing eggs (press 4) and keep Razorgore away from your channeling toon. Kill eggs as fast as possible. Once channeling ends pop CDs to kill all the adds on you, then as Razorgore gets to you (on his own) throw down mocking banner (to get adds back on you and off boss) and continue killing eggs. Once all eggs are gone you can kill everything, including boss.", "date": "2012-12-09T18:00:32-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 152, "id": 1778624, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "both", "body": "For those trying to solo this in 5.1: As any class with heals, simply healing yourself will generate enough aggro to pull mobs off of Razorgore. Any time Razorgore starts taking too much damage (every 20% worked fine for me) just dismiss him, heal yourself, and channel again. No AoE required.", "date": "2012-12-09T20:44:12-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 153, "id": 1778722, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "vampirechickk", "body": "Anyone else having trouble with the first boss in blackwing lair? I kill the mobs to the left and click the orb and it won't control the boss!", "date": "2012-12-10T01:28:37-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If you are a class with a pet I believe you have to first dismiss your pet before you take control. That was the problem I had.", "creationdate": "2012-12-10T13:43:31-06:00", "id": 610189, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1778722, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Evilsean", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yeah, I was on my hunter! Thank You, I will try again! I couldn't find anything anywhere about this bug, that's why I put up this comment!", "creationdate": "2012-12-11T14:24:48-06:00", "id": 610605, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1778722, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "vampirechickk", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 154, "id": 1779129, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "essmene", "body": "Bulding threat by healing does help a lot in this fight.\r\n\r\nYou can end the mc by casting a single - instant spell upon the mc\u00b4d razgore. I focus targeted him and used Power Word: Shield.", "date": "2012-12-10T15:48:31-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 155, "id": 1779401, "nreplies": 11, "sticky": 0, "user": "Eldorell", "body": "After 20 wipes I learned and/or remembered these:\r\n\r\n1. At any given time there can be 40 adds in the room. Was like that in vanilla and is the same now.\r\n\r\n2. Adds spawning tend to aggro you when Razorgore is near you. The farthest away he is (eg. the back of the room) the more possible - if not for sure - they will aggro him.\r\n\r\n3. When the Mind Control breaks Razor will cast some of his abilities on the adds and he will pull some from you for sure. He is aggressive towards both you and the adds. Don't let him too long out of MC.\r\n\r\n4. You cannot have a pet eg. shaman elemental, hunter pet etc. and also try to control Razorgore.\r\n\r\n5. DO NOT SPAM THE MC when it breaks! There might be some delay and some difficulty because of the adds around you but if it finally worked and you press it again you will get the 8 secs debuff making you unable to control Razor for the duration. Click once, wait to see if it worked and if not try again.\r\n\r\nWhat I finally did:\r\n\r\nI DID NOT KILL ANY ADD.\r\n\r\nI started destroying the eggs near the controller and continue destroying the ones near me. This caused all mobs spawning attack me and not Razorgore.\r\n\r\nJust before the MC broke for the first time I tried to have Razor away so to give me some time to cast some healing on me (did the fight as elemental shaman). You can use also a pot.\r\n\r\nI recast MC and continue to break eggs. By now most adds should be on you and only a few on him. Most of the adds should have spawn by now. The rest will not do so much dmg on him. \r\n\r\nOne hard thing is to keep an eye on yourself and time when you break the MC to heal yourself if you need to.\r\n\r\n/my50cents", "date": "2012-12-11T02:40:47-06:00", "rating": 89, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This worked for me last night. Thanks!", "creationdate": "2012-12-11T10:13:03-06:00", "id": 610511, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1779401, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "crimsonshadow150", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This strategy is much better than all those above; worked like a charm. I had about 20 seconds to spare.", "creationdate": "2013-02-02T09:19:42-06:00", "id": 628901, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1779401, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "shadowrune", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Worked Perfectly - best strategy I've seen for this fight", "creationdate": "2013-06-10T16:49:49-05:00", "id": 667835, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1779401, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "tellx", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "BEST STRAT!! sorry for caps just want to make sure people see it. because this is the only way i beat this fight; thanks a ton. BEST STRAT!!", "creationdate": "2013-11-18T07:16:16-06:00", "id": 708944, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1779401, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 16384, "username": "wesleigh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just to add to this unique approach: I wasn't getting rid of enough aggro with just frequently dismissing razor near my character. You can sit your character below the orb platform and still use it so it's easier to click without adds on it. I spent the first few seconds before adds spawn taking care of the eggs near the orb before the adds could pile up and AoE Razor. Once adds started showing up I waited razor on top of the platform so most adds saw my character first. Also, don't forget razor can sleep 1 add! My severely undergeard lvl 90 boomkin in bear form never dropped under 50% health.", "creationdate": "2014-01-28T13:24:59-06:00", "id": 724922, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1779401, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "IBPwNin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 156, "id": 1779835, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "togahsisoka", "body": "I found that as I got better at efficiently destroying eggs (getting the most out of each MC), the harder it got.  Of course the gut reaction is to try to clear eggs even faster...   I finally realized that destroying eggs generates aggro (duh), so naturally destroying them too fast gets too much aggro on Razorgore and he'll get worn down faster.  Don't be afraid to dismiss him early, clear some adds, get some more aggro on you and then send him back to work.  I found if I was trying to pull it off in 3 MC's or less I'd wipe due to Raz dying too fast.", "date": "2012-12-11T22:22:11-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 157, "id": 1780079, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "caltoro", "body": "How To ; [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yfPbEDy1GlY]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yfPbEDy1GlY[/url] as Hunter", "date": "2012-12-12T09:06:04-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 158, "id": 1780754, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Glaucus", "body": "A tip if you are soloing this as a rogue and are about to fail on the eggs, when he dies you get thrown out of the mind control, use Cloak of shadows right away, and you will not die.", "date": "2012-12-13T13:30:46-06:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is simply not true. That attack does not register as any sort of damaging attack, let alone a spell. It's simply an insta-kill, and thus, cloak will not protect you.", "creationdate": "2013-02-27T22:55:15-06:00", "id": 636248, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1780754, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "digitalutopia1", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 159, "id": 1781440, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vorh", "body": "Just did this as a lv88 destro loc with a saced daemon and found something interesting. The passive healing from the sac was drawing all the adds agro away from raz, I was just running around in raz until my loc got low on health, got out poped a health stone and aoed down some the mobs. I usually did this when the mc released naturally.\r\n\r\nAnother point is that mobs attacking you while mced no longer has any significant push back, Having 30+ mobs on me for the entire time gave me less than 1 second of push back.", "date": "2012-12-14T19:48:16-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "i just wrote my own post about this lol, and yeah you are totally right i just did this fight easily because the sac pet's passive heal pulled all threat. as a geared lvl 90 i didnt even need to do any other heal i just sat on the orb and did a few aoes while i had the MC debuff", "creationdate": "2013-01-16T08:58:45-06:00", "id": 623262, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1781440, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "lolablerants", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 160, "id": 1784336, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "822061", "body": "The fight is ninja buffed or bugged. I have soloed him really easily every week since 5.1. Now i tried to kill him many many times with same gear and same spec as usual. You just don\u00b4t generate enough aggro anymore as dps geared prot spec warrior. Second Wind did generate almost zero aggro when there was loads of adds. Im sure it\u00b4s still soloable but but..", "date": "2012-12-19T21:42:50-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Same thing I've experienced as a DK. p2 I can never click the orb again right away (silenced constantly). Then when I do, tons of adds aggro on the boss. Very strange", "creationdate": "2012-12-26T16:30:38-06:00", "id": 616067, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1784336, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "355492", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 161, "id": 1784344, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Avalonia", "body": "It sounds strange, but the key to soloing Razorgore is to NOT kill any adds. Any class with a healing ability should just keep healing themselves while letting all of the adds beat on you. The room can only hold 40 adds, and they aggro very quickly on anyone healing themselves. Once 40 are out, there are none left to beat on Razorgore if they are all beating on you (via the healing aggro). I did this with my Blood DK and a combination of Vampiric Blood + Rune Tap as well as Raise Dead + Death Pact. It might actually help to start this fight about half health so that you can have more room to get healing aggro.", "date": "2012-12-19T21:59:21-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 162, "id": 1786083, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "414577", "body": "5.1 Solo\r\n\r\nFor those classes that do not have a resident AOE you can easily grab full room aggro via Healing yourself.\r\n\r\npop a HoT on yourself and run around the room. mobs that Razorgore has not attacked back should switch to you. \r\n\r\nThe threat Razergore gets from mobs entering the room is close to non existent, the mobs have only a sight aggro to him, You healing yourself should be enough of a taunt to the room to pull mobs that razorgore has not auto attacked back to switch to you, the mobs that wont turn onto you can be easily singled out and picked off, \r\n\r\nCleared as bear tank using this method, \r\n\r\ngl", "date": "2012-12-23T07:39:33-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not sure why it was downvoted...on my 3rd attempt I did just this, except I didn't bother running around the room, I just stayed at the orb. I'd switch to bear form in between MC'ing and swipe a few times, but other than that, I'd just cast Rejuv on myself, and most adds would enter the room and head directly for me. Razorgore was able to handle the few adds that did aggro on him.", "creationdate": "2013-01-05T22:21:48-06:00", "id": 619658, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1786083, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Mathaylla", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 163, "id": 1787473, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Irollpally", "body": "As some have stated above in 5.1 this is now soloable. If you are a tank there a better method of doing this fight and is much simpler. \r\nFirst you kill the adds that are controlling the orb then quickly get the orb of command and destroy as many eggs asap. then whenever you run out of channeling time quickly press the orb again. and continue onto the egg destroying and you should be able to destroy them without you or Razorgore dying.\r\nPhase 2 is easy, by this time i had around 100k-200k health on my pally. i used lay on hands to get back up and finished off razorgore. (all the adds leave the room once phase 2 starts and is a quick 10-20 second burn phase and you killed him. i hope this was helpful and wasn't hard to read. (I tend to make crappy forum posts. so are illegible.)", "date": "2012-12-25T22:45:31-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 164, "id": 1788718, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wahrsager", "body": "He is Soloable, being a tank druid you can start the channel and kill up your eggs. Once the mind control starts to drop get him close and target him to use a Rejuv. It breaks mc and puts a hot on razorgore, hit the orb and watch the mobs swarm you while you finish up the eggs. Gotta keep up the HoTs though, plus side is razorgore stays at max health.", "date": "2012-12-28T17:06:58-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 165, "id": 1789450, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nylers", "body": "5.1 \r\nEasily Soloable as a Prot warrior. \r\nMake sure you have Second Wind. I tried soloing it without that talent and failed several times.\r\nEvery so often dismiss Razergore and kill any adds that are attacking him. Be careful not to kill any adds that you have aggro'd . The reason for this is only 40 adds can spawn and if they are all attacking you, then Razergore will not be attacked.\r\nOnce the eggs are cleared the adds run away and you can then kill Razergore easily.", "date": "2012-12-30T03:53:59-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 166, "id": 1790861, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dalarya", "body": "After multiple failed attempts as a level 90 Unholy Death Knight, I finally downed Razorgore.\r\n\r\nFirst off, once I had him MCed, I started destroying the eggs closest to the orb working toward the opposite wall. I got as far from my toon as I could when the MC broke and then popped Death and Decay and Unholy Blight as well as Army of the Dead (which REALLY helped with aggro) I MCed Razorgore a second time and destroyed the rest of the eggs and then just DPSed him down. \r\n\r\nI didn't need to use any healing, just some food with +200 dodge buff and blood presence was enough.\r\n\r\nRemember as an Unholy DK, DO NOT use your pet. The first few times I tried it, I pulled out my pet in between MCs to use death pact to heal myself and didn't realize until a few tries later that my summoned pet was the reason I couldn't MC the boss again.\r\n\r\nBut once I decided to pop AoD in between MCs, the fight was easy peasy. :)\r\n\r\nGood luck!", "date": "2013-01-01T19:39:09-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 167, "id": 1792031, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "pellmell", "body": "Easily the fastest way to drop control of Razorgore, rather than hitting the exit vehicle button or right-clicking and dismissing, is to simply hit Escape.", "date": "2013-01-03T17:39:50-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 168, "id": 1793399, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "gbergalli", "body": "after several attempts i was able to solo this one with my balance druid.\r\nmy trick was to use rejuvenation on him to leave the vehicule, using aoe to clear the adds on me (mushrooms, starfall, hurricane/astral storm) and get back to him as soon as i could, so the rejuvenation ticks would kick in\r\n\r\nmy reward was the pet that he now drops", "date": "2013-01-06T01:00:43-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 169, "id": 1795183, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "800990", "body": "What I've found works really well is to kill the controller and channel as everyone else has stated, and then start off by killing the eggs closest to the channelling orb first, and work your way back. By the time the channeling timer is up, Razorore should be far away from you and you will have a few seconds to AoE the mobs attacking you. \r\n\r\nThen it's very important to start channelling again before Raz gets to the platform. What I've noticed is that he doesn't take all that much damage from the mobs attacking him; what gets his HP down is when he's on the platform with you, he takes a ton of AoE damage. \r\n\r\nI did it using this method on an 88 rogue with no healing, crappy armour, and moderate HP, and finished all the eggs with about 75% health on Raz.", "date": "2013-01-09T05:23:31-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 170, "id": 1795943, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1074133", "body": "What I have discovered to work best is to immediately aoe the three mobs that are on the platform with the orb. Drop off the front of the platform and stand close enough to it that you can still interact with the orb. After that control Razorgore and work your way back to the side you're on. Start clearing the eggs on the other platform and just snake your way back, completely ignore the adds on Razorgore. When the MC falls off aoe the mobs on you then pick up the MC again and finish it up.", "date": "2013-01-10T12:44:02-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 171, "id": 1796092, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1074558", "body": "I've been trying to solo him and I get to 2 or 3 eggs left and he dies. I offered to run a lowbie through in trade and give them all the loot but the pet drops. Worked out pretty well.", "date": "2013-01-10T16:11:37-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 172, "id": 1797183, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "MetalGenocide", "body": "Hunters are able to heal him to full if they use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=109304]Exhilaration[/url] to end the MC. This will also give you healing aggro.", "date": "2013-01-12T09:23:28-06:00", "rating": 54, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Worked perfectly! Thank you for the tip.", "creationdate": "2013-01-26T16:52:12-06:00", "id": 626768, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1797183, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ponies32", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Also wanh to add, if you are a hunter, DISMISS YOUR PET. Otherwise you wouldn't be able to control the boss", "creationdate": "2013-02-12T04:12:14-06:00", "id": 632003, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1797183, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wolchara", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This also holds for health funnel on locks . .", "creationdate": "2013-05-22T20:23:47-05:00", "id": 660968, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1797183, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "1122264", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Also resto druids can use force of nature then MC him and the treant will heal him up a little and you should use force of nature as much as possible to get him healed up and therefore be able to make this fight a little easier.", "creationdate": "2013-07-01T21:42:14-05:00", "id": 674075, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1797183, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zaron31116", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This made all the difference for me, thank you SO much... I've been struggling with my hunter, but re-speccing and taking [spell=109304] made all the difference.", "creationdate": "2014-01-05T01:46:11-06:00", "id": 719374, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1797183, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tumblestock", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 173, "id": 1799392, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "lolablerants", "body": "I'm not sure if this is a fluke or just how he works now, but i solo'd this as a 90 warlock with ease. i clicked the orb and started destroying the eggs. first few adds attacked me. destroyed a few more. about 3 adds ran at the dragon guy. then they stopped. and turned around. and attacked me. this kept on happening and i finished with him still over 50% because he only took dmg from the first few attacks before they changed target.\r\n\r\ni also was using sacrificed pet so my passive regen was huge so i wasn't dying at all ether", "date": "2013-01-16T08:54:27-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "just saw another warlocks post and realised that of course, its my sac pet passive healing thats pulling the threat too. for warlocks solo'ing this i suggest talenting soul link and sac pet for 20% more max hp and thus a bigger passive heal from sac too.", "creationdate": "2013-01-16T09:08:56-06:00", "id": 623268, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1799392, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "lolablerants", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Finally, someone posts some actually useful information. Everything else is fodder compared to this method, which works flawlessly perfect and is so very easy.", "creationdate": "2013-03-10T20:29:09-05:00", "id": 640238, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1799392, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Dust", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 174, "id": 1804312, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "neopatra", "body": "tips for soloing as a lock:\n*ss yourself before fight.\n*dismiss pet before fight so u can control the orb.\n*from time to time, take boss to far end of room, dismiss orb, then use aoe on the adds around u.\nthen go tag with corruption the adds dpsing the boss and get back to orb.\n*u can use imp swarm and summon abyssal and then click orb to control boss again. u can also use aoe (like immolation aura) and then click orb, the aoe will continue despite that u controlling boss now.\n*when u controlling boss then remember to sleep 1 drgaon add that attacks u, from time to time.", "date": "2013-01-26T04:27:10-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-01-27T11:01:52-06:00", 1, "neopatra"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 175, "id": 1804616, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Bighappykitty", "body": "For those lucky enough to farm up the [item=86572], it is a huge help here.  Pop the trinket before you kill the three mobs on the pedestal with the control orb, and he will aggro any of the adds that come after you.  I've also noticed he'll get bored from time to time and run out to aggro the mobs that go after Razorgore.\r\n\r\nAs for Razorgore himself, pick up control as soon as you can and try to clear one side of the room before you have to release him.  Then just clear out the other side and drop him.  In the two runs I've done since I got the trinket, he's managed to clear the room with over 50% life left.", "date": "2013-01-26T18:01:34-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Great post, helped me immensely.", "creationdate": "2013-02-04T23:14:14-06:00", "id": 629760, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1804616, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Thenalya", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 176, "id": 1807448, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1087660", "body": "Tips for a Monk to solo at level 90: [spell=124081]\n\nStart the fight and go the full portion killing eggs.  After the first timer wears down, [spell=130151] to kill the mobs around you.  I attempted a few times to kill other mobs nearby, but either you accidentally hit Razorgore or he stuns you.  Once the mobs around you are down: [spell=124081]. And regain control on Razorgore.\n\n[spell=124081] creates and keeps up agro on new mobs/current mobs.  A few will still hit Razorgore, but not too many as most will attack you.  After 30-45 seconds [spell=130151] to get the mobs off you again and then [spell=124081] one more time and then let Razorgore get the last few eggs.\n\nYou should be able to get it down within the 3rd control cast.\n\nAs a general rule for other classes, you need something to draw constant agro (like hunter traps) to easily solo this.", "date": "2013-01-31T22:44:55-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-01-31T22:48:27-06:00", 2, "1087660"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 177, "id": 1809002, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "numbersoul", "body": "I was having issues doing this as an enhancement shaman since I wasn't able to generate enough AoE damage to peel the adds of Razorgore and he always died.  I ended up using this strategy:\n\n1. Run in and kill the controller and click the orb\n2. Start destroying eggs on the far side of the room\n3. When the channeling is about to run out move Razorgore onto the platform that you're on\n4. Drop an earth elemental.  You can't be specced into [spell=117013] because the Primal Earth Elemental will take up the pet slot\n5. Click the orb again and destroy the eggs on the orb platform then destroy the rest of the eggs in the room\n\nI was able to do the fight pretty easily with this method without worrying about Razorgore's health through the rest of the fight and without having to drop control of Razorgore to peel the adds off.", "date": "2013-02-04T09:43:31-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-02-04T09:45:16-06:00", 1, "numbersoul"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 178, "id": 1810625, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "Aerozia", "body": "Hunter solo guide:\r\n\r\ntake Exhilaration talent.\r\nby traps i mean, ice trap, snake trap and Explosive trap(unglyphed explosive trap)\r\n\r\nput pet away(cannot control boss with a pet out)\r\n\r\nattack the three mobs by orb. drop all traps and click orb quickly before he makes it up the ramp to you.\r\n\r\nstart taking out the orbs closest to you, keep going until you almost run out of time, IF he is low health(meaning around 1/4) use Exhilaration while still controlling him, it will heal him and end the MC. drop all traps again and pop Stampede, click orb and go back to clearing the room.\r\n\r\n   >I personally did not have to use Exhilaration the first loss of MC, i let it run out, and dropped traps and stampede.<\r\n\r\nIf you did not need to use Exhilaration great! save it for when he gets down to 1/4 health, use it, drop traps and click orb. keep clearing. once all eggs are gone, the mobs run, just attack and kill him.", "date": "2013-02-08T04:07:27-06:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thanks, this worked like a charm!", "creationdate": "2013-02-25T15:32:11-06:00", "id": 635626, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1810625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "65183", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Worked first time. tyvm for the guide.", "creationdate": "2013-06-09T18:36:17-05:00", "id": 667590, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1810625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "insinu8", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Worked for me as well, thanks!", "creationdate": "2013-06-20T04:10:30-05:00", "id": 670572, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1810625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Uuneya", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thanks! I kept trying and trying but nothing worked. Read your comment, and i did it on the first try^^,", "creationdate": "2013-07-22T16:44:35-05:00", "id": 679511, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1810625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Feraltiger", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "470ish ilevel, all I did was drop the explosive trap at my feet then click the orb. No problem destroying eggs, got him to the other side when the MC wore off then dropped another explosive trap, both our HP was fine -- but the second round of tapping eggs, too many mobs would follow him, and I kept wiping. Using Exhilaration when his health was low did the trick.", "creationdate": "2013-07-24T23:00:58-05:00", "id": 680123, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1810625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "drewbster", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 179, "id": 1813487, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Keepertje8", "body": "If you fail soloing this as a mage, you can Iceblock immediately after Razorgore dies, rendering you immune for the blast, and you can try again. \n\nThis boss is actually very easy if you pursue the following strategy:\n\n*Make sure you have changed your [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=12051]Evocation[/url] into [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=116011]Rune of Power[/url], and have it [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=56380]glyphed[/url], so you recover HP constantly. Unequip 4 pieces of your gear (this will make the mobs hit you harder = more heals = more aggro).\n*Clear the opposite end of the room in the beginning, because the aggro mechanic seems to take distance into account. The closer Razorgore is to you, the easier it is to take aggro of him. You will want to take more aggro later on in the fight, as there will be more adds. In the beginning, there are no adds (make sure to use all your dps buffs on the 3 guys around the Orb at the beginning of the fight, as that will allow you to break one or two more eggs without any adds bothering you).\n* Rebuff [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=116011]Rune of Power[/url] whenever it wears off, and try to hit any mobs there are hitting Razorgore. Use AOE to kill all the mobs around you before you re-use the Orb.\n\nUsing this strategy, you should be able to clear all eggs, with Razorgore at 30-40% at the last one. Key is to start at the opposite end of the room.", "date": "2013-02-14T08:41:10-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-02-14T09:07:50-06:00", 8, "Keepertje8"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 180, "id": 1817604, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1094305", "body": "Soloed as a hunter on the third try. Few points: you need only two mind control sessions to destroy all the eggs if you're quick. Start near the orb so that the adds agro yourself. When you lose MC, use an AoE to kill the adds and then start MC again. After the eggs are destroyed you can use self-heal, but that's not strictly necessary.", "date": "2013-02-24T07:45:35-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 181, "id": 1818986, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Goatlegs", "body": "For Warlocks:\r\nDon't use your Flames of Xoroth to bring out one of your demons while you're MC-ing Razorgore. For me it broke MC, caused him to despawn and all the doors were locked, couldn't use the MC orb, had to let the endless adds kill me. When I tried to go back in to give it another go the gate was down. Waited about 20 mins to see if the gate would raise to let me back into the egg room, nothing. \r\n\r\nTL;DR: Flames of Xoroth while MC glitches everything, don't do it.", "date": "2013-02-27T17:57:15-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 182, "id": 1819269, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1098511", "body": "I made a guide on how to solo this as a druid :D\r\nLook up: How to Solo Razorgore - MOP 5.1 - Druid \r\nOn youtube", "date": "2013-02-28T12:58:55-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 183, "id": 1819425, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheZoog", "body": "Trying to solo him?  Here are the two keys: learning how to break MC and learning how to re-MC him even though you have mobs attacking you.  There is no button you can click on to break MC.  You'll notice however, that you have an action bar for Razorgore when he is MC'd.  And you also have your own action bar.  You can click on him or yourself (your icons rather) and cast a spell and this is what breaks the MC.  Don't have pets out or you can't re-MC.  You might want to put him on focus to make it easier to click on him.  Towards the middle-bottom of your screen you will see the \"channel\" bar, which is really slow, but you MUST pay attention to it because this dictates your moves.\n\nEach one of you will have to develop your own method to the madness but the basic strat is this:\n\n(1) There are 30 eggs in total I think.  You need to kill up to 8 eggs on the first MC, starting with all of those on and near your platform first and moving him towards the far platform.  Put every dragon attacking Razorgore to sleep, without exception, because they do the most damage.\n(2) When the first MC wears off, you are now on your platform being attacked by a huge mob.  Pop your CD's and nuke them quick.  Only one or two of your attacks will take HUGE gobs of his health down, so when Razorgore gets close, even if you are still being attacked, clicky on the orb again. You might experience some pushback but you can do eet.  You MUST do eet or you will fail, so keep trying.  Consider popping a heal-potion first, or save it for later when your health starts to get really low.\n(3) Once you have him re-MC'd, go back to clearing out all the eggs, but this time you are watching your health and his health.  You can heal him up, which will break the MC, but he must be within range.  I had to bring him back once and loh, nuke a few adds, then re-MC, and burn more eggs.\n\nOnce I figured out the basic rules of how to break MC and re-MC even though I was being interrupted periodically, the fight became fairly easy, although tense.  With the final egg gone, the adds cleared out by themselves and it was me on him.  He likes to cc you, so make sure your health is up before concentrating on him or you might let it slip through your fingers at the very end.  \n\nGood luck and have fun!", "date": "2013-02-28T21:11:43-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-02-28T21:13:59-06:00", 2, "TheZoog"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 184, "id": 1820371, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Woundwort", "body": "Having perfected foolproof methods of soloing this boss on 2 classes so far I've decided to share my experiences after many experiments :)\r\n\r\nFirst of all, forget about all the comments that suggest killing the channeler first, there's no point in my experience as it saves valuable seconds for egg killing by leaving him, for now. \r\n\r\nFirst method is with my main character Boomkin.\r\n1. First thing I do is plant 3 mushrooms on the main floor below the podium with the orb in a decent spread so as to do max damage/kills. \r\n\r\n2. Next I take the orb from the main floor and get on with the egg killing.\r\nI concentrate on clearing the eggs from furthest end and by time I'm almost half way through the possession drops off.\r\n\r\n3. Just as the first possession ends, I detonate the mushrooms killing all the mobs around me. I take over the orb soon after and carry on with the eggs. There's no definite way to clear eggs at this point as any logical process will work with more than enough time left.\r\n\r\nSecond method is with my warlock. As demo spec I always have Dark Apotheosis on as it seems to attract more mobs away from Razorgore when possessed.\r\n\r\n1. I start the fight in the same way by taking over the orb without touching the summoner.\r\n\r\n2. I work through the eggs in the same manner but just as the first possession finishes, I drop my Abyssal right on top of the position where I'm summoning from.\r\n\r\n3. I take over the orb again and carry on with eggs. In the meantime my Abyssal is causing mayhem killing all the mobs around me and making the whole process trivial.\r\n\r\nOne final note for second boss as lock, make sure you remember to SS yourself before the fight to avoid the corpsewalk back from Thorium point :).\r\n\r\nWhen I've had time to experiment with other classes I'll update my post. In the meantime, good luck with drop rate :)", "date": "2013-03-03T08:16:11-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The warlock strategy worked like a charm for me! Five attempts without dropping abyssal ended in wipe with a third of the eggs left. With the abyssal razorgore had 1/3 health left... Rest of the raid went without any problems.", "creationdate": "2013-03-12T10:07:51-05:00", "id": 640890, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1820371, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Havsoga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The boomkin one worked perfect for me! I was trying to do it before seeing this and I must have failed around 5 times, but then I tried your strategy and bam! First try using your strategy did it. Thank you :)", "creationdate": "2013-05-12T19:10:17-05:00", "id": 658190, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1820371, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Hvitur", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 185, "id": 1823734, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "natassja72", "body": "I'm unable to solo him any longer after 5.2. Right now mobs literally destroy him before I even manage to break 20% of eggs. As if he got some new aggro aura on himself. He dies so fast before I can nuke the mobs one by one since I can't obviously use any AoE. Perhaps a tanking class with AoE taunt can still do it. I've given up after 5 tries today.\n\nJust to add, before 5.2 I always destroyed all eggs without any problems whatsoever and Razorgore was still at roughly 30% hp with only few mobs beating on him, I didn't even bother killing them off him.", "date": "2013-03-07T12:37:38-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-03-07T12:39:51-06:00", 2, "natassja72"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 186, "id": 1825772, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Silverfalkin", "body": "Tip for warriors soloing this boss:\n\nMocking Banner, when placed, continues to work while you're MCing the boss, leading to an extra 30-second window relatively add-free. This provides a huge help when managing adds.\n\nEdit: I was able to solo without too much difficulty as a 90 arms warrior.", "date": "2013-03-10T03:22:27-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-03-10T21:01:06-05:00", 1, "Silverfalkin"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 187, "id": 1827600, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dannardi", "body": "Soloed him yesterday as an 85 fury/prot warrior, though it took me several tries to figure out how to do it:\n\n1. Switch to prot spec and put on tank gear.  I had ~50% combined block/dodge/parry, 60% damage reduction from armor and ~138k health so you don't need any crazy gear.\n\n2.  Have Second Wind talent speced and be in defensive stance.  The healing and damage reduction is just enough to keep me no lower than 1/3 health through all the adds.  Most important: the agro from Second Wind healing is enough to keep the majority of the adds off the boss.  If they pile up on him during mind control move him near your character for a bit and most will switch to you.\n\n3.  When you're about to lose mind control move him to the far side of the room.  This gives you the chance to AOE adds without hitting him.  Soon as he is in range of your AOEs use mind control orb again.\n\n4.  Don't hesitate to right click on his name plate (the one below yours during mind control) and dismiss him before the time is up; I did it a couple times to peel off adds and AOE.\n\nI'll be running it again at next opportunity to confirm I wasn't just lucky.\n\nEdit:  Just did it again, messed up first time, second time went smoothly", "date": "2013-03-12T16:51:03-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-03-12T22:45:14-05:00", 1, "Dannardi"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 188, "id": 1827886, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Magicdealer", "body": "Figured this out tonight on my 90 paladin. First tries were irritating as the mobs just killed Razorgore before the eggs were all destroyed.\r\n\r\nThe winning strategy was to use the Light's Hammer talent on cooldown. The area heals kept me alive, killed the enemies, and pulled aggro from everything so that Razorgore could work relatively unscathed. Just remember to run him to the opposite side of the room before you release to drop the hammer.", "date": "2013-03-13T07:18:08-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 189, "id": 1827966, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "zantrec", "body": "Completed on a 484 Shadowpriest and a 440 Resto Druid in 5.2. Trick for me was to keep killing the adds attacking Razorgore, breaking MC often when too many adds were making his health get low. There is a VERY small margin for error post-5.2. On the two successful attempts, Razorgore's HP was around 2% by the time I broke all the eggs.\n\nAs others have pointed out, I also think that the aggro mechanics have changed since 5.2- the adds are much more likely to attack Razorgore than you, which means you have to either taunt or gain aggro in some way, or dps the adds when you're out of MC.\n\nPerseverance is key! Took me 3 attempts on the druid and about 7-10 on the priest!", "date": "2013-03-13T11:05:06-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-03-13T11:32:24-05:00", 1, "zantrec"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 190, "id": 1829537, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "sk4p", "body": "If anyone can figure out how to do this as a lock post the 5.2 aggro changes, I'd love to hear it ...", "date": "2013-03-16T07:52:01-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "When you first get the MC, head towards the other platform, breaking eggs along the way. The aggro and damage that RG gets during this first MC should be minimal. You should have broken almost all of the eggs on the other platform by the time the MC breaks. AOE some adds around the orb, and MC again. This time, keep a close eye on RG's HP while breaking more eggs. If it gets below around 25%, go back within range of the Orb and break MC, and dps adds for a little while. Pay particular attention to ranged caster adds as they seem to do more damage. Then MC again, and continue with breaking eggs", "creationdate": "2013-03-19T11:33:24-05:00", "id": 643428, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1829537, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "zantrec", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If you dps'd enough adds, you should break the last egg befor RG's HP gets to zero, the adds will leave then you're free to dps him down! Otherwise try again. I don't think that just 2 MCs are possible any more- three at least are necessary imo. This strat works for a hunter, druid, shammy and priest. Should be fine for other classes.", "creationdate": "2013-03-19T11:34:00-05:00", "id": 643429, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1829537, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "zantrec", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Doing this on my DK is typically very, very easy. I'm not sure why Blizz continues to make pointless changes to these encounters. Understanding the mechanic is enough in itself - if it's to favor people who stop lvling at 60 to just do classic WoW content then I think they need to reconsider their pool of activities for the typical lvl 90 player since one done grinding reps and mounts and gear (for the most part) people only have old content to fall back on. Anyway, if you bust a move the moment you click the orb, you shouldn't cut it too close.", "creationdate": "2013-03-19T12:11:12-05:00", "id": 643445, "rating": -6, "commentid": 1829537, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ttbloodlusttt", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 191, "id": 1829841, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Lordplatypus", "body": "The loving parent he is, Razorgore turned his eggs into bombs.", "date": "2013-03-16T19:52:22-05:00", "rating": -7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 192, "id": 1832218, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tekunin", "body": "Killed him quite easily as of 5.2, first time try at level 90 on my Warlock.  Similar to the suggest way of doing it as a Mage above, I took off a few pieces of gear so that I'd take more damage, then talented Grimoir of Sacrifice so that I was regenerating health every five seconds.  I also did it as Destruction so between channels of the Orb of Control I could drop a few Rain of Fires on myself and Razorgore (which in turn generated full Burning Embers so I was able to Ember Tap if I got too low on my HP between channels).\r\n\r\nI also find that destroying eggs from the ramp with the control orb then moving to the other side of the room causes less mobs to aggro onto Razorgore, perhaps because of the fight mechanics.  Any time that his channel was about to break, however, I ran him to the ramp he starts on so I'd have time to cast Rain of Fire in a couple places before he could get to the Orb and stun or conflag me and the mobs, drawing aggro onto himself.", "date": "2013-03-21T08:29:04-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 193, "id": 1843535, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Morbius", "body": "Soloed this with my 85 blood DK. After several attempts I finally got the strategy down. I killed 2 of the 3 starting mobs and let my DOTS finish off the 3rd so I could mind control Razorgore before he got to me. Otherwise he will fireblast you and stun you and you won't be able to do anything for like 10 seconds. \n\nI destroyed the 2 eggs on the platform I was on and then moved towards the other platform destroying eggs along the way. When mind control wears off kill the mobs attacking you and heal up with death strike then reapply mind control. You have to be quick or Razorgore will get too close to you and take a lot of AE damage. \n\nMake sure to spread your DOTS using blood boil with Roiling Blood or with Pestilence. Then before you re-mind control Razorgore use Bone Shield and Icebound Fortitude.\n\nIt was close and I could probably fine tune the route to destroy the eggs. The channeling only broke once so a more efficient route is one way to reduce the damage he takes. I wish I could generate more healing aggro. That would really help.\n\nHere's the video:\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VtifU4PAHkc", "date": "2013-04-15T15:51:59-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This strategy worked for me. It seems like the damage Razorgore takes is random. Sometimes I barely solo it and others he finishes with way more health.", "creationdate": "2013-07-14T15:30:13-05:00", "id": 677464, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1843535, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Leichewow", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thanks for this, it worked for me on my second try. Starting off killing the eggs near the control platform really did seem to result in less aggro on Razorgore.", "creationdate": "2013-09-20T11:52:20-05:00", "id": 694877, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1843535, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Curval", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-07-16T23:19:41-05:00", 2, "Morbius"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 194, "id": 1846370, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "klavier285", "body": "Interestingly I got the achievement \"city defender\" when I wiped on razorgore.", "date": "2013-04-23T21:01:53-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I don't know why this is downvoted, it's completely true.", "creationdate": "2013-08-14T16:50:39-05:00", "id": 684863, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1846370, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "klavier285", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 195, "id": 1846428, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "968833", "body": "Grab [item=86570 domain=ptr] and [item=86572 domain=ptr]\n\nThose 2 trinkets make this boss a complete cake walk \n\nThe puppies and the terracotta warrior really keeps the adds at bay", "date": "2013-04-24T02:52:57-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "two wipes and tried this tactic, easy kill", "creationdate": "2013-06-04T08:13:18-05:00", "id": 665981, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1846428, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "1059959", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "These trinkets are apparently a must-have now - I did this fight easily several times prior to 5.2 as my hunter just by dropping traps under myself before the fight and when MC broke. Tried it again today and Razorgore got owned twice before I went and picked these up. *sigh* Oh well, at least it's still possible.", "creationdate": "2013-06-15T09:45:31-05:00", "id": 669278, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1846428, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "6448", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I didn't even need two trinkets, although I had [item=86572] and [item=86576] equipped, I only popped the Dynasty and that was enough to solo this.", "creationdate": "2013-07-24T12:31:48-05:00", "id": 679979, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1846428, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "JakkFrost", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-04-24T02:54:11-05:00", 1, "968833"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 196, "id": 1860319, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "crimminal", "body": "After a handful of wipes I finally got [npc=12435] down as a level 90 Fury Warrior.  To start the fight, popped [item=86570] and immediately charged the 3 NPCs guarding the orb and killed all 3.  Then I jumped down to just in front of the orb and clicked to MC [npc=12435].\r\n\r\nDestroyed as many eggs as I could.  Once MC fell off, I used [spell=118000] to quickly kill most of them on my body and then clicked the orb again.\r\n\r\nDestroyed as many eggs as I could.  Adds were starting to pile up a bit so this time, when MC fell of I ran to the middle of the room and used [item=86565].  This pulled almost all of them and I quickly ran back and clicked on the orb.\r\n\r\nDestroyed the rest of the eggs and killed [npc=12435].\r\n\r\nHope this helps!", "date": "2013-05-30T19:50:43-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 197, "id": 1861047, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Punchin", "body": "Solo'd as an elemental shaman. After mind control wore off the first time, I just tossed my AOE heal on the ground and went back to MC. Then ran the boss into the healing. All the mobs broke off the boss and went to me so I could clean out the rest of the eggs without the boss dying. VICTORY! But no pet.. :(", "date": "2013-05-31T22:52:13-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 198, "id": 1867736, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vikmourne", "body": "Just solo'd it on my second attempt as a Monk. Switched to Brewmaster spec and dropped a Black Ox statue in the middle of the room. It seemed to taunt off various adds that were attacking the boss onto me. It was out of LOS when the boss was on his starting platform so I destroyed those eggs second after the eggs on my platform. Whenever I needed to taunt more adds off of him, I dropped him next to my statue and then taunted the statue (which taunts all enemies within 8 yards). The boss had roughly 30% hp when I entered phase 2.", "date": "2013-06-17T19:01:51-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 199, "id": 1870382, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "silthania", "body": "At this point, any class can solo him as follows:\r\n\r\n1. Activate the orb\r\n2. Destroy half of the eggs.\r\n3. Activate the orb again.\r\n4. Destroy the remainder of the eggs.\r\n5. Kill Razorgore.\r\n\r\nDon't kill any adds, and don't use any of Razorgore's abilities except \"Destroy Egg\". Any delays or other things you do may lead to Razorgore's premature death.", "date": "2013-06-25T03:06:47-05:00", "rating": -7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 200, "id": 1871738, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "zombiek3nny", "body": "I ran into a wierd glitch on the 5.4 PTR today with this fight. I finished the attunement orb quest on my rogue, then walked in to solo the fight. The second I stepped through the portcullis, the eggs disappeared, along with the mind control orb. Has anyone else had this problem? I soloed the raid on my druid yesterday, so it may just be a rogue glitch...", "date": "2013-06-28T23:56:44-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 201, "id": 1877288, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "luxurybob", "body": "Level 90 Pally, ret spec.\r\nAfter a few attempts, I finally got this right.  Here's what worked for me:\r\n\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Avoid [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=20154]Seal of Righteousness[/url] (or anything else) that may cause splash damage on Razorgore.[/li]\r\n[li]I allowed Razorgore to run closer to me while killing the first three adds (he was just at the bottom of the ramp), then MC'ed and moved him back towards his platform breaking eggs. I had finished one side of the room and his platform when MC broke.[/li]\r\n[li]Go AOE nuts on the mobs around you while he runs back. This ensures a nice clean click of the orb, especially if you use nameplates (I've accidentally clicked mobs before).[/li]\r\n[li]I did not deliberately target any mobs atacking RG.[/li]\r\n[li]Allow RG to get on to your platform, then MC.[/li]\r\n[li]Break your platform eggs, and move him back away from you.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nI got them all the rest on the second MC.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]You [b]must[/b] be stationary to break eggs. [b]Beware of latency[/b] - you've stopped but the server doesn't yet think so. I frequently hit the button twice to get it to work. Stare at the location of the cast bar and ignore everything else.[/li]\r\n[li]Seconds count: if you lose time on an egg break, it may be all over. However, time it right, and you can move just before the cast finishes.[/li]\r\n[li]There may have been some luck with aggro - this time there seemed to be less mobs targeting RG, so he had a fair bit of health left on the last egg.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nAfter that, it's all gravy.\r\n\r\nHope this helps.", "date": "2013-07-15T21:43:27-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 202, "id": 1878019, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "schtinky", "body": "Three words: [item=55055]\n\nKills adds passively and generates threat, pulling adds off the boss.\n\nI failed 5 times (not even close) and then succeeded on my first try with a shield spike. Razorgore had about 20% left, too. So I think it worked.", "date": "2013-07-17T20:22:11-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-07-17T20:22:44-05:00", 1, "schtinky"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 203, "id": 1878489, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1133292", "body": "[url=http://youtu.be/hCZW9jZ7i8A]Lvl 90 Paladin Soloing Razorgore the Untamed[/url]\r\n\r\nHappy farming.", "date": "2013-07-19T06:29:24-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 204, "id": 1884682, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Seahnjin", "body": "Did they recently nerf the adds' attack power ? I keep reading posts about how people had to heal themselves, but as a ilvl 489 Frost Death Knight I never had to worry once about my health. I guess plate armor really does make that much of a difference at lower levels ?\r\n\r\nAnyway, it took me a few tries (including a couple of them where I had just one or two eggs left...), but I did it with absolutely no healing tricks.\r\n1. Kill the 3 guys.\r\n2. Control Razorgore once he gets near your platform (just be quick so he doesn't stun you because every second counts).\r\n3. Start breaking the eggs the closest to the orb (it's the \"4\" key just saying), working your way progressively through the room. Most of the adds that spawn should aggro onto you, not Razorgore, at this point.\r\n4. Keep doing this until the MC is about to automatically break. Break the MC yourself by right clicking Razorgore's pet portrait and select \"Dismiss\". (Apparently this is better than letting the MC break by itself according to many comments ? I didn't try any other way)\r\n5. Now that you're back to yourself, quickly AOE most of the adds hitting you. BE CAREFUL - Razorgore is running back to attack you so don't accidentally hit him !\r\n6. Use the control orb again (quickly before Razorgore stuns you) and don't $%^& up - CLICK IT ONLY ONCE.\r\n7. Destroy the remaining eggs. Just have Razorgore run like hell on his stubby little legs, be quick and efficient with the Destroy Egg ability, and never look back. You can also use his \"5\" ability to put Dragonspawn adds to sleep - it's pretty convenient, it's instant and you don't even have to face the guy. Just make sure to be quick and not delay your precious egg destroying.", "date": "2013-08-07T06:53:05-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 205, "id": 1889484, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "DeaBomb", "body": "If you are a rogue and Razorgore is about to die while you are still destroying eggs, you can avoid the inevitable death if you cast Cloak of Shadows in time.", "date": "2013-08-23T13:20:15-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-06-22T14:13:34-05:00", 1, "DeaBomb"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 206, "id": 1890655, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "782640", "body": "If you are 90 druid having trouble as I was... just go resto and use wild mushrooms.  It will heal razorgore to max hp as long as he is in range of bloom.  Be sure to plant the shrooms before the engagement.", "date": "2013-08-27T07:41:47-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "ty!! i just kill him in my first try", "creationdate": "2013-11-13T12:48:32-06:00", "id": 707824, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1890655, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "JPato01", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 207, "id": 1890817, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "voidfoo", "body": "I don't know if anyone mentions this or not. But for rogues, you will never die when failing the mission, as long as you have Cloak of Shadows on CD.", "date": "2013-08-27T23:47:39-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 208, "id": 1892010, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Bluest", "body": "Shaman can solo Razorgore by healing him to full health with a Healing Stream Totem and/or a Healing Rain after the first MC ends.  Just make sure to keep him in range of HST or in the HR.\n\nI also recommend dropping a Magma Totem before each MC to help with add control.", "date": "2013-09-01T09:19:08-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-09-01T09:31:53-05:00", 1, "Bluest"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 209, "id": 1898032, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1145124", "body": "I've been running BWL to get a transmog bow and had the WORST time with Razorgore.  There are a ton of helpful comments here (such as remembering to dismiss your pet, which is essential for pet classes that are soloing this guy) but one thing I didn't see, and I might have just missed it is, you can TOTALLY use Exhilaration!  Not only will it heal him to full as if he were your pet, it will break the MC and allow you to take care of the absolute ton of mobs you will have acquired.  Kill the bulk of the ones that insist on still attacking him and repeat the process.", "date": "2013-09-14T19:15:14-05:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 210, "id": 1901234, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1146489", "body": "Razorgore the Untamed is soloable by a Paladin, but that's the only class I'm sure of. I read a comment earlier on this same topic that said something about the mechanic of the fight coming before any DPS, damage etc. This is true.\r\n\r\nFirst of all, you want to make sure you can heal yourself in between controlling the orb. Even though you are (most likely) level 90, you will be taking quite a bit of damage. Nothing to worry too much about, but it is still something to watch.\r\n\r\nSecondly, this encounter would be super easy if Razorgore didn't get attacked by other minions. Razorgore doesn't keep your health so the enemies take Razorgore down pretty fast. My tactic here is (as a Paladin) take down half the eggs on the Orb's side so that if any enemy attacks Razorgore they'll go after me instead. Then, I'll take down some of the eggs on the other side of room where mobs will begin to attack me. I have to be careful here. If I can't take down all the eggs in one run, I stop when Razorgore is at half health, when I throw down a few AoE to kill the enemies near me. Then I carefully pick off and tag the enemies that are around Razorgore, killing them all. Of course, Razorgore will run after you and mass stun you if he gets close. Basically I Divine Shield and do one of the following:\r\n\r\n 1) If you can't use the Orb while Immune (I can't remember if this is the way or not), I kite Razorgore to the other side and then run like hell with as much speed buffs as I can back to the orb, but never spam click it.\r\n\r\n 2) If it's not like that, well just use the orb and destroy the remaining eggs. Easily done.\r\n\r\nThe actual fight afterwards is super easy, shouldn't be a problem for level 85s to 90s, and even 80's will be finding him soloable after the egg mechanic.\r\n\r\nI hope this helped all classes in trying to solo this fight. However, non-Paladins should just bring a friend to help them :).", "date": "2013-09-21T18:50:13-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 211, "id": 1906003, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "George14", "body": "Paladins: Sacred Shield and Holy Prism will help you with Razorgore. They are instant and you can cast them on him as he is your MC pet.\n\nPriests: Renew/Power Word: Shield is good,\n\nDownvoted for the truth? Wow.\nGo to your Spellbook while MCing him and use them, they work and it breaks MC. I know who one was, by the way.", "date": "2013-10-06T07:09:14-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-05-27T05:20:26-05:00", 1, "George14"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 212, "id": 1907510, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chaosrex", "body": "Ok this fight is utter bull%^&*.\r\n\r\n6 times i've redone it, and only once, was i able to controle him, all the other times, i'm standing in front of that stupid orb, and i can't control him, nothing happens when i click it, not a !@#$ing thing.\r\n\r\nIts irritating to no end.", "date": "2013-10-10T21:34:17-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Ok found the problem, should've think about it, if you controle a pet you can't use the orb...", "creationdate": "2013-10-11T06:17:47-05:00", "id": 700381, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1907510, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Chaosrex", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "For Dk's, when your first controls comes to end, quickly cast AotD, the ghouls and skemetons, will help you cleaning the adds in the room and buy you time.", "creationdate": "2013-10-11T06:18:57-05:00", "id": 700382, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1907510, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Chaosrex", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yup. 90 mage with 485 gear and I hate farming this raid now. Beat it last time after wiping 3 times, this time I wiped 5 times and just didn't have the patience. Tried using rune of power to heal me and gain aggro *works for a short time* tried releasing him quick and often to take adds off him, tried far end of the room first and orb end of the room first. I think it really is a combination of good strategy + a fair bit of luck on your side. When I have got all the eggs, he's literally been down to 5% health or less each time. Fucker of a boss to solo.", "creationdate": "2013-12-12T13:47:30-06:00", "id": 714084, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1907510, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "deathbydrum", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 213, "id": 1912311, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "annhala", "body": "I just soloed him as a resto druid, but barely. It was at least my 5th or 6th attempt. I tried as feral, in cat form; and as resto, in tree form. I was having a hard time holding aggro on the adds in cat & tree form, but could hold aggro in caster form. I don't know why it worked better for me in caster form, but thought I'd share it here in case it might help someone else.\r\n\r\nSwitching back to feral to finish the place. :)", "date": "2013-10-26T19:32:15-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Good Tip...I tried this on my hunter, mage and pally first then read your tip...resto made it easy. Put down a Wild Mushroom near the back of the main floor in front of the deck and kept Razorgore healed while i took out eggs. Worked my way to the front, when my MC ended so I dropped a new Wild Mushroom to the back, same spot on the floor, next to the platform, blew the adds away with a Typhoon and went back to Razorgore running to the Mushroom for heals when needed. DPS'n in a Resto spec is a little slow at the end but doable.", "creationdate": "2013-11-24T20:06:00-06:00", "id": 710376, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1912311, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mountainmiester", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 214, "id": 1915184, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Roemanish", "body": "Roemanish - Lvl 90 Destruction lock on silvermoon ilvl 538\r\n\r\nI spent the day farming the trinkets that people had recommended and i had no joy after quite a few kills so i decided i would just head to BWL and try to have a go at soloing this for the first time the expansion.\r\n\r\nI just killed the 3 guys by the orb and then clicked it to channel (if your class has pets make sure its dismissed) and started to kill the eggs on the platfrom at the far side of the room working my way towards the end i was with the orb. I got half way down the room in the first channel of the orb and  then used rain of fire till kills adds on me and channeled again to do the other half of the eggs. I was about to do last egg when razorgore died. \r\n\r\nI tried again and this time started at the eggs on same platform as the orb and got half way through the room when the channel finished and again i put rain of fire around me and a quick one on adds attacking razor (did not kill all of them but only left a few on him ) then channeled and did other half. The second time i noticed most the adds attacks on razor were missing him most the time (guess thats to do with my level) but i managed to get all eggs and he still had 25% hp.\r\n\r\nI never lost more than a few % of my hp and never needed any heals or cd's.\r\n\r\nJust just spam key 4 (only key i used the whole time) and in 2 channels of the orb you should have time to clear all the eggs.\r\n\r\nGood luck", "date": "2013-11-05T16:52:45-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Use grimoire of sacrifice, the healing agro generated by the heath regeneration will keep all the adds focused on you and off razorgore.", "creationdate": "2014-01-04T22:24:39-06:00", "id": 719337, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1915184, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "taqman", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Perfect strat, even without Rain of Fire (until they give it to pallies, anyway). The key is to start on your side of the room so most of them get on you; when the channel ran out I used one aoe on everything by me, repossessed him, and did the other side of the room. Most of the orcs got on him then, but he cleared the last egg with about 30% life left. Spam 4, enjoy soloing him in two channels\u2014no trinkets necessary. :)", "creationdate": "2014-06-11T03:03:48-05:00", "id": 750684, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1915184, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Trollee", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 215, "id": 1920940, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "sherrasama", "body": "Warlocks - fun fact: \r\nHealth funnel works for it's full duration of channelling on Razorgore so long as he is still MC'd when you first start the cast and don't get interrupted. It restores about 60-80% of his health if you pull it off", "date": "2013-11-24T15:34:52-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "No need for that. Use grimoire of sacrifice, the healing agro generated by the heath regeneration will keep all the adds focused on you and off razorgore.", "creationdate": "2014-01-04T22:22:45-06:00", "id": 719336, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1920940, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "taqman", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 216, "id": 1924233, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "FullElven", "body": "Just as a warning, if you have Xuen's legendary cloak, you should unequip it for this fight. If you try to single target mobs and it goes off, you will kill everyone around you, and it'll wipe you.", "date": "2013-12-07T16:20:42-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 217, "id": 1925003, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "RazerWolf", "body": "Just discovered today after a couple of attempts where I got to Phase 2 and then wiped anyway and couldn't figure out why... you have to let Razorgore lose agro on the disappearing adds; he will then reset to full HP and come to you. If you do not let him reset then he will \"think\" that he is still in Phase 1 and explode all the eggs even though they're dead. \r\n\r\nTook me a dozen attempts to work that out when I could have killed him on #3.", "date": "2013-12-10T12:25:51-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 218, "id": 1931982, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Gorrath85", "body": "Here's how I solo'd him as an Enhancement Shaman (iLvl 509):\r\n\r\nRun in and killed the controllers, then immediately started smashing eggs on the far side of the room opposite the orb. When the adds ran in, all but one of them started attacking me immediately (didn't have to dismiss Razorgore), so I kept smashing eggs. When Razorgore had a few adds on him, I dismissed, AoE'd adds with Magma Totem and spreading Flame Shocks when I could for Fire Novas. When Razorgore got back to me, I dropped my Earth Elemental and took control of Razorgore immediately after. Be sure to recall your Magma Totem when Razorgore gets you to minimize any accidental damage against him. At this point it was pretty easy, as my Earth Elemental was grabbing most of the aggro. By the time Razorgore had a few more mobs on him, I only had two or three eggs left. Smashed them and done.\r\n\r\nSomething I might try next time is dropping the Earth Elemental in the middle of the room, and I'll see if it picks up more adds that way.", "date": "2014-01-05T17:07:37-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 219, "id": 1933898, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "aprildawn567", "body": "How I solo'd Razorgore on level 90 mage (I relied on Rune of Power talent):\n1. Before killing anyone, take control of orb and kill eggs on platform where Razorgore starts out. \n2. Dismiss Razorgore.\n3. Kill as many adds as you can before Razorgore reaches platform.\n4. Drop Rune of Power (HoT for 60 seconds). This causes adds to damage you, instead of Razorgore, but the damage you take is insignificant.\n5. Kill eggs, starting on far side of room and working towards orb.\n6. When Razorgore gets to 1/2 health, dismiss him, kill adds, then drop Rune of Power again.\n7. When eggs are gone, finish off Razorgore (easy).", "date": "2014-01-12T10:34:36-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-01-12T10:39:26-06:00", 1, "aprildawn567"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 220, "id": 1936793, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "insatiable7", "body": "[b]How to Easily Solo This as Any Class:[/b]\r\n\r\nI did this on my 90 priest and after a few tries to work the kinks out, I am able to regularly clear this encounter alone within just a few minutes.\r\n\r\nThe keys I have found to make this encounter's mechanics a cinch is this:\r\n\r\n1. Run in and kill controller.\r\n2. Wait until Razorgore is walking up the stairs to you before clicking on the orb.\r\n3. Control him and start clearing the eggs on the platform first.\r\n4. Clear eggs starting on that end of room going back and forth as you make your way to the other platform.  (When Razorgore is near to your character most, if not all, of the mobs will agro onto your character instead of Razorgore.\r\n5. When you are about to lose control of him, dismiss, and then reclick the controller orb.  (You will most likely have a giant pack of 40+ mobs on your character at this point.  They barely scratched my priest so you should be just fine.)\r\n6. Work your way to clearing all of the eggs.  If you have an issue with getting too much agro in the form of other dragons, you can pause for a moment to make one of them sleep.\r\n7. Finish clearing the eggs and kill Razorgore.\r\n\r\nI typically end the egg portion with Razorgore having anywhere from 50-75% life still.  Just be patient and methodical.", "date": "2014-01-22T14:32:32-06:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "very good info :D did this on my mage - no probs at all...life as u said ab 75% at the end...but ive started with 75% :)) forgot to heal after ressesed", "creationdate": "2014-02-24T06:08:26-06:00", "id": 731170, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1936793, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Berbe", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "perfect tacs. done the encounter without a problem", "creationdate": "2014-03-16T08:59:30-05:00", "id": 735017, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1936793, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Heffernan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "That's not how the encounter works! They don't agro you if you run him past. The second they hit him they're on his threat table and there isn't a thing you can do about it beside killing the mobs. Obviously some classes are going to have a lot harder to deal with this encounter than others. The best is to STRIP your character naked. This encounter isn't about burning him down but keeping him alive. Once it's over he can't kill you and you shouldn't have a problem killing him. If you do this properly you DISMISS him once you see the first add coming, that'll make them run to YOU and not him!", "creationdate": "2014-04-20T04:07:24-05:00", "id": 741477, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1936793, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "huldu", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "That's a good basic strategy - follow it. One minor addition that can help is to finish clearing the far platform (by now you have a couple of mobs beating on you) and then instead of running down the steps, JUMP off the platform on Razorgore's stubby little legs - the mobs have to run down the steps, and may even drop aggro altogether - it saves a couple of seconds of getting beat on.", "creationdate": "2014-06-17T17:54:33-05:00", "id": 751928, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1936793, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "cefm", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "OMG I can't thank you enough. I thought that it was impossible. After a few tries I was able to kill the first boss solo.", "creationdate": "2014-07-18T21:48:35-05:00", "id": 758442, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1936793, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "yonae123", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 221, "id": 1940508, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Loreya", "body": "Solo'ed him as a 80 Prot Pally with pretty terrible gear. I killed the last egg when I was like at 1.5k HP - *!@#ing INTENSE. But only took like 3-4 tries and in the \"last try\" I killed him.\r\n\r\nIts all about killing the eggs in the msot effective route and getting lucky with the boss-aggro.", "date": "2014-02-03T19:11:46-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 222, "id": 1940682, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Acoleski", "body": "What you can do as a hunter or if you have a hunter with you.\r\n\r\nUse [spell=13159] and tell him to run along with razorgore. You will minimize the time it takes to walk between eggs and also be able to outrun the mobs. Razorgore will NOT be dazed.\r\n\r\nI had [item=43355] glyphed at the time and didn't think of checking if it had any affect.", "date": "2014-02-04T13:36:09-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 223, "id": 1943705, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "GenericNPC", "body": "For Warlock solo in the current patch, spec into Grimoire of Sacrifice for this fight. Sac any pet, the passive heal from the sacrifice buff will keep all the adds on you and you can freely run Razorgore around killing all the eggs.\r\n\r\nWhen the MC is about to wear off, run Razorgore to the back of the room (where he starts) so you don't have to worry about getting conflagged, hit Escape to cancel the MC, drop from Rain of Fires (Destruction), click the orb, repeat.\r\n\r\nRazorgore was pretty much full health when I killed all the eggs.", "date": "2014-02-16T01:48:09-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not sure why you were downvoted, but this strategy worked out perfectly for me. Just to make sure I'd be healed, I started off by also using [spell=111400], but that doesn't seem to be needed.", "creationdate": "2014-07-22T03:07:26-05:00", "id": 759194, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1943705, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "clavicle", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 224, "id": 1943865, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "GenericNPC", "body": "As a Warlock in the current patch, just spec into Grimoire of Sacrifice. The passive heal will keep all the adds on you. Razorgore will take little-to-no damage.", "date": "2014-02-16T10:31:39-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 225, "id": 1950433, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "chrth", "body": "Here's a tip if you're one of the classes unable to heal Razorgore and you're struggling.\r\n\r\nYou don't need to stand in front of the egg or be facing it to destroy it. The game will randomly select an egg within 6-8 yards of your current position. So every time you move, you should be moving to a spot between multiple eggs and destroying eggs until no more are in range.\r\n\r\nThis strategy doesn't guarantee success, but I've found that doing so has shaved off some valuable seconds and allowed me to get to second phase when Razorgore would've died if I had moved to each egg.", "date": "2014-03-12T12:35:20-05:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not sure why this was down voted, after wiping several times on my rogue, this tactic worked perfectly.", "creationdate": "2014-05-16T14:56:07-05:00", "id": 746230, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1950433, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "freegb1", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 226, "id": 1952404, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mascara", "body": "Solo'ed as a 90 Rogue, NO HEALS.\r\n\r\nThe trick is to drop threat on Razorgore so that he doesn't take a constant beating. Clear eggs until you see mobs come from the sides and head towards Razoregore. Then dismiss him(by right clicking his portrait) and kill the adds on you by the orb. Then re-channel and go back to destroying eggs. The mobs that were attacking him should be running towards you now.\r\n\r\nRinse, Repeat.", "date": "2014-03-20T13:57:51-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 227, "id": 1953931, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nocked", "body": "Soloed with 90 warrior.  He was close to death on the last egg but I barely made it.  Doing it solo makes me appreciate 40 manning even more back in vanilla.  It's a chaotic fight.", "date": "2014-03-26T15:40:42-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 228, "id": 1955847, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "m0nstah", "body": "Get http://wowhead.com/item=86565.  It has a pretty decent drop chance and the re-spawn is fairly quick.  After all the mobs are out use that item and all of them will start attacking you.  Then go back and finish the eggs with no mobs on the boss.\n\nWorked first time with that item.", "date": "2014-04-04T12:48:13-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-04-04T12:49:51-05:00", 2, "m0nstah"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 229, "id": 1959151, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tommyboypsp", "body": "If you have a hunter in the group, tell them to keep on the speed boost aspect, because it does increase the boss speed.", "date": "2014-04-17T10:09:25-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 230, "id": 1967126, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Beowolfy", "body": "Okay.  Some one needs to state in plain language what the &*^%$ is going on with this fight.  I am dumber than a post but how do you kill the eggs?  There is no vehicle button that I can see.  I understand from previous posts that this is a two-part boss kill.  But it is totally impossible if you don't understand the basic mechanics of what might be the objective and how to achieve it.  Kind of counter-intuitive that we need to keep the boss alive.  Why? How? Help!", "date": "2014-05-22T19:41:11-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The \"vehicle button\" is the orb on the pedestal at one end of the room. There's an orc there using it as you enter. When you attack and stop his channeling, Razorgore becomes a free enemy and comes for you. You kill the orcs and use the orb yourself. That lets you control Razorgore (he's the vehicle) and he has an ability to destroy the eggs. Afterwards the orcs continue to attack you at the orb (though you can stand a lot of punishment from them) and also attack Razorgore (who is MUCH more fragile). Once you have destroyed all the eggs, THEN you can safely kill the boss.", "creationdate": "2014-05-23T11:55:45-05:00", "id": 747467, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1967126, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Hannibal08", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Here's all you need to do: 1) Dismiss your pet if you are a pet class. 2) Kill orb controller on left platform. Ignore all other orcs during the entire fight. 3) Click on Orb of control...you are now controlling Razorgore 4) Move around room destroying eggs using the 4 button on your keyboard (or clicking icon on your bar). 5) Your control will eventually expire. When it does, just click on the orb again. 6) Finish destroying eggs (it will take you 2 controls to do so). 7) Once the last egg is destroyed Razorgore is essentially free. Orcs will flee. 8) Kill Razorgore.", "creationdate": "2014-05-25T18:22:04-05:00", "id": 747889, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1967126, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nocked", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thank you for this post, I died 4 times before coming here. I didn't understand what was killing me.", "creationdate": "2014-07-17T15:41:14-05:00", "id": 758162, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1967126, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "cwhite419", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 231, "id": 1967750, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wheeljack", "body": "I found that as a druid, in bear form with the [spell=145108] - talent, most of the mobs kept aggroing my character even when I was using the orb. Didn't have to dismiss Razorgore at all, except for when the timer ran out of course. \r\nWhen all the eggs were destroyed, RG was still at 90-95% HP.", "date": "2014-05-25T15:56:14-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 232, "id": 1968967, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "oramac", "body": "Just successfully solo'd this fight.  Level 90 Ret Pally ilvl 496 pvp gear.\n\nBasically, just grab the orb and ignore the adds completely.  Start with the eggs furthest from the orb and work your way back.  Once the channel runs out, again ignore the adds and click the orb.  Rinse and repeat.  \n\nIt did take a few tries.  I think there's an element of chance involved, as on the last try very few of the adds actually attacked Razorgore.  \n\nScreenshot: \nhttp://i1068.photobucket.com/albums/u446/oramac1968/Razorgore_zps1015fffe.png", "date": "2014-05-31T15:46:44-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-05-31T15:51:22-05:00", 1, "oramac"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 233, "id": 1969754, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Yakeshi", "body": "People can say I'm QQ'ing all they want, but I think it would be nice () to have the option to break the eggs yourself. I mean, you can't even scratch them, no matter what level you are, or how good your gear is. And yet we can take on old gods, demons lords, and all sorts of other ridiculously omnipotent beings?", "date": "2014-06-02T18:56:27-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This Boss-fight makes farming more interesting and demanding than simply running and killing everything around. I don't know what is you attitude to old content but i'm bored with rushing from point A to B. If you think in another way for sure you haven't farmed [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=13335]Deathcharger's Reins[/url] in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=2017]Stratholme[/url] yet.", "creationdate": "2014-06-13T05:34:35-05:00", "id": 751036, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1969754, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bagins", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 234, "id": 1971057, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "ibsenrb", "body": "A easy way i've found to do this solo, as a druid Lvl 90, with 2nd spec as a healer, was:\nPut a wild mushroom on orb area.\nTake a form of a bear or cat (I prefer bear)\nKill the mobs\nGet control of Razorgore\nDestroy the far eggs first\nWhen the control ends, kill as much mobs you can, and get control again.\nThe mushroom acts as a agro way to the mobs. When I finished the eggs, Razorgore already had 97% of his life.", "date": "2014-06-08T20:57:34-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "For my run with my Lvl 90 resto druid I put mushroom at orb, just stood there in caster running around destroying eggs. When Razorgore got low on hp I went over to myself and let mushroom heal him up and also this gave me healingaggro. Very easy fight :)", "creationdate": "2014-08-15T15:58:35-05:00", "id": 764955, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1971057, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "akedalmans", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-06-08T20:58:48-05:00", 1, "ibsenrb"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 235, "id": 1973179, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "cefm", "body": "Solo advice on warrior - try using a shield with a spike (low-level spike 70-80 so as not to kill the mobs) to add extra threat.  I had better luck as Fury for better AOE quick-kills between orb uses.\r\n\r\nMocking banner helps pull adds of Razorgore.  I start controlling him on far platform, destroy eggs there, go down one stair and destroy eggs in that corner, then go back up platform and jump off front of it to lose the mobs for a second and work my way back to the orb.  Use sleep button if the dragonkin are on you.  Need to drop control when it runs out or too many are on you.  Back in control of your warrior, whirlwind and dragon roar to clear,drop off platform and drop mocking banner, then click up on orb to regain control.  By now he should be on you, so under control, clear the orb platform and race race back to any un-cleared eggs.", "date": "2014-06-17T18:06:18-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 236, "id": 1973715, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "soneil", "body": "I tried doing this as a medium geared level 85 hunter. Didn't work out too well since I couldn't take the damage. As others have suggested you want to take the heat off razorgore so you need to be able to take the damage instead of him. To start with the mobs were hardly scratching me but by the time I had 15-20 mobs on me my health was dropping fast. I couldn't heal myself other than the small amount of healing from my herbalism lifeblood.\r\nSince I couldn't use my pet I was vulnerable and couldn't survive long enough to get all the eggs. I'll try again after a couple of levels but for people wanting to try it at 85 you probably need pretty good gear to handle the damage.", "date": "2014-06-20T13:01:37-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Now I've done it again as a level 90 with decent gear. I barely take any damage but I need to more very quickly to get the boss to all the eggs before he takes too much damage. I find that if I don't get all the eggs in 2 control phases then it's not quick enough and I wipe. Plan a careful path that will get though through all the eggs quickly. On the first run I try to position myself so that razorgore finishes far away from my position. Gives me more time to control him while I drop some aoe traps to thin out the herd of adds.", "creationdate": "2014-09-16T21:29:27-05:00", "id": 772470, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1973715, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "soneil", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 237, "id": 1975311, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Gnamra", "body": "As a prot warrior, I found it to be easiest to just unequip all gear, go into berserker stance and use the second wind talent. When the boss got too many adds on him I used mocking banner and MCed him again.\r\n\r\nI placed the boss near me so that more of the adds would start attacking me, once the Second Wind talent kicked in, the healing threat was enough to aggro almost all of the adds, the ones that refused to attack me I killed with the boss.\r\n\r\nTo begin with I destroyed the eggs that were on the opposite side of the room, I did this until the adds spawned, after that I switched to the eggs closest to me. I placed the mocking banner when there was ~5 adds on the boss.\r\n\r\nThe goal is to get to 35% as fast as possible, this boss becomes super easy when you do.\r\n\r\nI think this tactic should work for the other specs, but I have not tested this.", "date": "2014-06-26T20:39:49-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 238, "id": 1975826, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "DarkDei7", "body": "It's really easy to solo as a mage.\r\nTake [spell=116011] and use [item=42738] to heal you.\r\nBasically all you need to do is to set your Rune of Power on top of the Orb and control Razorgore,destroying all eggs while the glyph + rune heals you and let you aggro all the mobs.Everytime the Rune expires refresh it and continue destroying eggs.2-3 mindcontrols and you'll be done.", "date": "2014-06-28T09:43:06-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 239, "id": 1984067, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "albinoette", "body": "Soloing post-7.2.5: [b][spell=19873] is now instant cast, making this encounter [i]monumentally[/i] easier to complete.[/b] There is a 1.5 second CD, though, so just make sure the spell triggered before running off to the next egg. It still works better to start near the orb and circle back to the other side of the room, just to give you a chance to hurl attacks at Razorgore before he is able to disorient you.\n[hr]\nBoss can drop a pet: [item=93036] which grants [npc=68661] as criteria for [achievement=7934].\n[ul]\n[li][b]You will be unable to use the mind control orb if you have pets/minions/ghouls/elementals summoned.[/b][/li]\n[li]At present, it's easier to circuit towards the orb and back away so that the AoE from the mobs doesn't kill the boss while you work.[/li]\n[li][b]You no longer need to exit the vehicle to regain control of Razorgore[/b] - just click the orb again while controlling Razorgore and the channel will refresh. You'll also drop aggro from things attacking you. [Edit: this was not working the same for me after 7.1.5.][/li]\n[li]You can stand in one spot between several eggs and be \"in range\" of more than one egg at a time.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nI've edited the original post to reflect the newer information, though ^ pretty much sums it up. Much easier at 100, still doable at 90 (hence the edit of below instead of a full delete).\n[hr]Okay, trying this during 7.1.5 and was dying and dying and dying (and dying). Decided to try some new theories here since all previous methods of \"dropping aggro\" weren't working for me (clicking the orb just gave me a 10s debuff and when I got Razorgore back, adds stayed on him). Hoplowe's more recent comment/strat [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435/razorgore-the-untamed#comments:id=2449287]here[/url] (Nov 28th) is what finally worked for me. The basic gist is that it uses the first 2-3 full channels of mind control to collect the adds that will spawn so that on subsequent mind controls you (character) should keep all the aggro off you (Razorgore). This worked basically well for me except I had one add stay on me that almost killed me as I went through the room.\n[hr]\n[small][u]Key Points:[/u]\n[ol]\n[li]You must dismiss any pets before being able to use the control orb.[/li]\n[li]Adds will spawn and can aggro to you on the orb, or to Razorgore. There is a maximum number of adds that will enter the room. They will respawn to this max if you kill them.[/li]\n[li]Razorgore is not a typical \"vehicle\" in the sense used in later expansions. To dismiss, you must right-click > dismiss from his portrait (under your portrait).[/li]\n[li]It is possible (and, in my opinion, easier) to kill Razorgore [i]without killing any adds[/i].[/li]\n[li]Boss can drop a pet: [item=93036] which grants [npc=68661] as criteria for [achievement=7934][/li]\n[li]Razorgore will randomly attack any egg within 6-8 yards. [b]TIP: That means you can stand in one spot between several eggs and be \"in range\" of more than one egg at a time.[/b][/li]\n[li]When Razorgore is closer to you on the orb, adds are more likely to aggro to you (on orb) instead of him, and will sometimes swap aggro from him to you (on orb).[/li]\n[li]Classes with insta-cast HOTs are able to use them on Razorgore while he is mind-controlled. The heal will break your MC, which you can regain by selecting the control orb again. This has the chance to have Razorgore pull a lot of aggro off of you, so it might not be useful for all HOT classes.[/li]\n[li][b]If Razorgore dies during phase 1, you die, too.[/b][/li]\n[/ol]\n\n[u]Strategy:[/u]\n[ol]\n[li]Dismiss any pets/minions.[/li]\n[li]Run in and kill the 3 guys on the orb. The main controller can detect stealth.[/li]\n[li]Click the orb to gain control of Razorgore.[/li]\n[li]Start killing eggs (\"4\" on your action bar) closest to wherever the boss is when you gain control of him. Ignore adds.[/li]\n[li]Move between clusters of eggs in a pattern that takes you towards [the control orb] [s][i]the far end of the room (opposite the control orb) back through the room. As you circle back towards the control orb, some of the adds attacking the boss will swap to attack you on the orb[/i][/s].[/li]\n[li][s][i]At some point in the fight, your mind control spell will reach the end of its channel and you'll re-enter your body. Kill whatever you want, but the key is to regain mind control on Razorgore asap. Player aoe can kill Razorgore if you spam it and he's too close, so be weary. If you have a [item=86565], this would be a great time to use it. You'll pull the adds off the boss, sparing his health. Remember, if Razorgore dies in phase 1, you die too.[/i][/s][/li]\n[li]Click the control orb [when the mind-control is about to expire], and keep spamming 4 to kill eggs.[/li]\n[li]When all eggs are destroyed, the adds will flee the room, Razorgore will go back to 100% health and he'll come after you. He has a pretty annoying stun, so dots/bubbles/etc. are handy.[/li]\n[/ol][/small]\n[hr]", "date": "2014-07-24T17:11:06-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This worked really fine for me as a rogue, cleaning the far side of the room then coming back to the orb destroying some eggs on the way, each time I broke the MC I did it close to me and the orb and all mobs dropped aggro on Razorgor. I didn't use any AoE or heal, I just let all the adds hit me. Finished with Razorgor at 130k hp.", "creationdate": "2014-10-22T04:30:03-05:00", "id": 781138, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1984067, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kyon92Z", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2017-06-17T03:32:39-05:00", 16, "albinoette"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 240, "id": 1988960, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "irishlord", "body": "i am on my 10th try.  I have read all of this and watched you tube videos.  I made it to the last egg but was too late.\r\n\r\nI even used the captains lost leg and had 3 lvl 90 pirates fighting for me. \r\n\r\nOne thing i noticed is when the channeling expires it is hard to click the globe again , it is like it thinks too long after i click it.  By then the guy is fearing me. \r\n\r\nI need to find a way to get more aggro on me , i even use the battle horn. \r\n\r\nI should just pay someone to help.  Heck i have spent 200 on repairs so far.", "date": "2014-08-06T15:52:46-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 241, "id": 2004013, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "drummer4christ", "body": "For some strange  reason I tried as a combat rogue and died about 6 times. Switch to Subtlety and did it no problems same strategy. For some wierd reason, subtlety generates better aggro.", "date": "2014-09-18T23:02:54-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 242, "id": 2010999, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "midobu", "body": "*** Level 90 hunter solo guide ***\n----------------------------------------------------\nRazorgore the Untamed ... [i]The first boss and the most difficult boss to defeat in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=2677]Blackwing Lair[/url][/i]\n----------------------------------------------------\nThis guide is made for a HUNTER struggling to fight alone and who does not have a max strong gear (based on the idea from the youtube video which will be described in the end). I am a terrible player so you just need to pick up something you like here.\n\n[ul]\n[li][b](1) Set your Talents/Level 45: [url=www.wowhead.com/spell=109304]Exhilaration[/url] - Instantly heals you for 30% and your pet for 100% of total health.[/b] [i]Put [url=www.wowhead.com/spell=109304]Exhilaration[/url] icon into your interface bar [b]where has NO NUMBER KEYS[/b] so you can use it when you need its ability - number keys will be hidden when you start engaging with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url][/i]. ([b]Note: [/b]You need to use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=112883]Tome of the Clear Mind[/url] to change your talent. Buy two if you want to set your ability back after this fight. You can also buy it from [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=44235]Reins of the Traveler's Tundra Mammoth[/url] if you have one).[/li]\n[li][b](2) [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=2641]Dismiss[/url] your pet before or right after going into [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=2677]Blackwing Lair[/url].[/b] (Using the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/object=179879]Orb of Command[/url] will be the shortest way if you have already accessed to Blackwing Lair before.)[/li]\n[li][b](3) [i]<<--- The First Mind Engagement --->>[/i][/b] Run to the left side of the room. Go up to the alter where a green orb is and wipe three enemies there. Put a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=13813]Explosive Trap[/url] under you, then touch the green orb to control [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url]. ([b]Remember:[/b] You need to touch the green orb as soon as possible because [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] is coming to attack you.)[/li]\n[li][b](4) While engaging with him keep on destroying eggs by using #4 key.[/b] (You can stand between two eggs and destroy each egg without moving.) Try to destroy all the eggs on the left half side of the room before the first buff time of engagement with  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] is expired. (Keep a little distance between you and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] so once the mind engagement is over, it takes more time for him to come and attack you.)[/li]\n[li][b](5) [i]<<--- The Second Mind Engagement --->>[/i] Once the buff time is up, you will automatically come back to yourself[/b]. Use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=781]Disengage[/url] to jump back and use Multi-shot to wipe up all the mobs around you. Again put a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=13813]Explosive Trap[/url] under you and touch the green orb to control [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] as soon as possible. (If you don't touch the green orb soon enough,  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] will come to attack you.) [/li]\n[li][b](6) Continue on destroying eggs by using #4 key.[/b] Try to destroy as many eggs as possible (now you should be destroying the right side of the room) and[i] [b]WATCH OUT for [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] health meter is going down FAST (quicker than the buff time of the second mind engagement is going to be over) as he is beaten by many more mobs than before.[/b][/i][/li]\n[li][b](7) [i]<<--- The Third Mind Engagement --->>[/i] Use [url=www.wowhead.com/spell=109304]Exhilaration[/url] ability to heal him back 100% before [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] health meter is reaching to zero[/b] at the same time you will be sent back to yourself. Kill all the mobs around you. Put a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=13813]Explosive Trap[/url] under you and touch the green orb to control [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] again. ([b]Remember:[/b] Use [url=www.wowhead.com/spell=109304]Exhilaration[/url] ability before [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] dies otherwise you will die along with him.)[/li]\n[li][b](8) Destroy all the eggs remaining.[/b] This is the last chance for you to destroy all the eggs inside the room before [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] is killed by mobs. You should have an enough time to destroy all the remaining eggs (after all, you have given a chance for THREE times - normally two times - to destroy all the eggs). When the last egg is destroyed, you will be sent back to yourself. This time, all the mobs are running away from the room.[/li]\n[li][b](9) Call your pet out.[/b] Now confront [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435]Razorgore the Untame[/url] and defeat him as normal. ([b]Congratulation![/b] The rest of [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=2677]Blackwing Lair[/url] will not be difficult as this is and now it is all yours to continue. Have a fun!) [/li]\n[/ul]\n[b]Recommendation: [/b]Use a flight pass to [i]Iron Summit, Searing Gorge[/i], so you can go into [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=25]Blackrock Mountain[/url] from the back entrance.\n\n[quote]#Blackrock Mountain back entrance\n\n/way Searing Gorge 35.00 84.72 Back Entrace[/quote]\n\n[quote]#The shortest way to get to the Blackwing Lair\n\n/way Burning Steppes 23.92 32.27 Orb of Command\n[/quote]\n\n[b]After Note:[/b] I like [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=2677]Blackwing Lair[/url] the most among all other instances in the Blackrock Mountain. And I won't mind visit here every once a week because I discover a new rare item every time I visit here (and if I am a lucky I pick up an extra battle pet as well). \n\n[b]Finally:[/b] I want to give a big thank to Leherp lederp who uploaded the youtube video [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s7W_3kBlxpY]How to solo Razorgore as a hunter! (EASY METHOD) *5.4* [/url] which provided this great idea to us.\n\nGood luck hunting!", "date": "2014-10-08T22:44:31-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-10-20T22:15:45-05:00", 146, "midobu"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 243, "id": 2011911, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TrutusBalnazzar", "body": "Just did this as a blood dk with 550 ilevel (pve), all I had to do was keep right clicking Razorgore's name when more than 5 were on him, then blood boil the trash + conversion to heal myself and get aggro, then MC him again. Finished all the eggs with Razorgore at 250k.", "date": "2014-10-12T09:50:54-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 244, "id": 2015710, "nreplies": 11, "sticky": 0, "user": "Arbron", "body": "Can Blizzard please stop breaking this damn fight and fix it forever?\n\n[b]Remove the damn adds, or let us just kill Razorgore and move on.[/b]\n\nThe recent stat squish which halved the health of everything in the game has left Razorgore with 288k health. It was hard enough before to keep him alive because the adds insist on attacking him even when he's not mind controlled. Plus, for some reason they hit him for 3k a piece - they do [i]extra[/i] damage to him, despite Blizzard's claim that they [b]removed[/b] this extra damage.\n\nIn its current form, with his health halved and the damage not reduced to compensate, it's effectively impossible for certain classes. Only those with a proper heal to generate aggro from the mobs can do it.\n\nOn that note, the fact that Razorgore counts as a pet needs reworking. It's not fair to screw hunters and warlocks out of their own pet (which often factors into their self-healing - the only way they can reliably get aggro off the mobs) on an already hard fight.", "date": "2014-10-19T06:08:16-05:00", "rating": 47, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "totally agree i could solo it before but now that i tried it again after patch 6.0.2 i got my ass handed to me....", "creationdate": "2014-10-25T18:02:23-05:00", "id": 782239, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2015710, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "speedosnelgrove", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Indeed, this is also a problem for me, the adds now hit for alot more damage and the fight became much harder to solo!", "creationdate": "2014-10-26T19:24:38-05:00", "id": 782565, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2015710, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Odracir", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "@Masterbiker: What? I absolutely can not ignore the adds; they'll kill him before the first channeling timer is up.", "creationdate": "2014-11-25T19:16:54-06:00", "id": 799583, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2015710, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Asator", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thanks for the updated info. I was going to give this a try-now I won't waste my time with the frustration. It would be very nice if Blizzard would change this boss to truly be soloable, for anyone, with ease. No reason a raid boss this old should be causing so much annoyance.", "creationdate": "2014-12-14T20:50:53-06:00", "id": 813083, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2015710, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Felyshkaw", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Nice try to lose your money with Repair. Why a boss old like this needs to have a bizarre mechanic? If he lost the aggro, like some guys told here, it will be easy to do, but this way, no way to solo. Shaman ele lvl 100, frustrated with this Raid and Dire Maul too.", "creationdate": "2015-01-25T16:48:10-06:00", "id": 832588, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2015710, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "aluiziofh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-10-19T06:17:05-05:00", 4, "Arbron"]}
