{"commentv2": 1, "number": 247, "id": 2016539, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "attumen", "body": "Just soloed this about 10 minutes ago as a Resto Shaman. To do so I dropped a healing stream totem and then took control of Razorgore. When he takes aggro move him to the middle of the room (or closer to you) and dismiss him then drop another healing stream totem then take control again. If your healing stream totem is on CD drop a healing tide totem, though this has a long CD. Rinse and repeat this until all the eggs are destroyed.\r\n\r\n1) Drop Healing Totem\r\n2) Control\r\n3) Destroy eggs\r\n4) Boss takes aggro\r\n5) Release Control\r\n6) Repeat 1 - 5", "date": "2014-10-20T15:36:05-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 248, "id": 2016695, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Bobbyboy45494", "body": "Hey guys, just finished the fight after the stat squish. After a few trial and error with his new reduced health, I figured out if you kill the eggs in the back first and move up front, the enemies hit you a little, and then move to your character at the summoning stone. Must be a thing where you can take their aggro if they're close. Some will stick with you a bit, but getting rid of the back ones on the pedestal before the adds come out help prevent you having to go back there and getting less on you.\n\nEdit: I'm a rogue too, so I couldn't have the option that most classes do. So if you're stuck like me, this seems to be the best option.", "date": "2014-10-20T22:20:03-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-10-21T20:43:04-05:00", 1, "Bobbyboy45494"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 249, "id": 2016766, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Arxae", "body": "Soloed as 507 windwalker monk. The way i did it was to take control, and just kill as many eggs before the adds spawned. About a second before i did, i casted [spell=124081]. The healing agro it generates is enough to pull off a good amount of them (usually only one or 2 remain). Every now and again i recasted it, cleared the adds in the direct vicinity of the orb and retook control. \r\n\r\nI ended the fight with razorgore at around 55%", "date": "2014-10-21T03:17:32-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 250, "id": 2018098, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "Cascius", "body": "Okay, just did this fight as a 90 hunter, but my strategy should apply to everyone. Dismissed pet, probably didn't have to ([b]edit: I [b]could not click on the orb with my pet summoned. Had to dismiss pet to clicky[/b][/b]) and probably should have kept him there just for the healing buff, but whatever.\n\nDon't even worry about killing the first three mobs, just jump right to the orb.\n\n[s]Start killing eggs near where Razorgore is located.[/s] [b]Move up to the orb side with Razorgore and start destroying those eggs. [/b]\n\nOnce the adds start coming, [s]move up to the front of the room[/s] [b]park your big dragon ass behind your character and the orb, as close to the wall as you can go.[/b], the adds should automatically aggro to your character, if not, dismiss and re-control. There are a limited amount of adds, so once the limit has been reached, they will stop coming and just sit there swinging at you.[b]The adds will continue to come through 2 or 3 channels of controlling Razorgore, just sit back and relax while your character takes the beating.[/b]\n\nKill eggs to your delight, if one or two adds are on Razorgore, don't worry, they won't hurt him enough to kill him.\n\nLet me know if this works. Easy fight this way.", "date": "2014-10-23T16:11:26-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This didn't work for me. The adds seem to path to him no matter where he is, even across the entire room when I'm not destroying any eggs. If I dismiss him, the adds continue to aggro onto him despite me not even controlling him. Even if I get them back onto me, they always seem to end back on him.", "creationdate": "2014-10-27T01:34:38-05:00", "id": 782627, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2018098, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rikoto", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Added an edit. Please try again.", "creationdate": "2014-10-30T16:06:19-05:00", "id": 783694, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2018098, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Cascius", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It works well worth giving it a go", "creationdate": "2014-11-05T04:28:18-06:00", "id": 786103, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2018098, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Evinor", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Impossible. The orb gets too crowded and I can't reach it like this.", "creationdate": "2014-11-08T07:17:40-06:00", "id": 787147, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2018098, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bkrp", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Even with parking him behind me, he still gets aggro from adds and dies before adds stop spawning.", "creationdate": "2014-12-29T01:46:56-06:00", "id": 820122, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2018098, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 16384, "username": "Vickrpg", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-10-30T16:03:42-05:00", 1, "Cascius"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 251, "id": 2018744, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Flagg", "body": "As of patch 6.0.2 he has about 220k hp. Still possible to solo on a paladin, I've destroyed all the eggs with 60k hp left (on razorgore).", "date": "2014-10-25T04:21:33-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 252, "id": 2020452, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "anhsieh", "body": "Great news for soloers: as of 6.0.3, ol' Razorgore is much, much harder to kill with mobs. Still, use the standard attempt-to-aggro-as-many-mobs-as-possible strat, but even with a stack of mobs on me I was able to bump off all the eggs in two channels. Happy hunting, friends!", "date": "2014-10-29T01:54:49-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "He's really not, he's still squishy as all hell. I barely managed to finish the fight on 6.0.3 as a Rogue using the \"move to the front to transfer adds to you\" strategy, one or two more hits and Razorgore would have died.", "creationdate": "2014-10-29T03:40:46-05:00", "id": 783232, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2020452, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "tenterflex", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It's beyond ridiculous. The fight needs a PROPER fix - either remove the BONUS damage the adds to the boss (Blizzard won't admit it, but they hit him a LOT harder than they hit players) or simply make them unable to attack Razorgore. I think that's perfectly fair, seeing as the adds are idiots for attacking him on their own with nothing you can do about it.", "creationdate": "2014-10-29T06:34:21-05:00", "id": 783264, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2020452, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Arbron", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 253, "id": 2020693, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Lysithia", "body": "6.0.3, tried this for about an hour until I found this strat below. Just keep dropping healing stream totems off cooldown. Razorgore had about 60% health or so left over by the time all the eggs were destroyed.\r\n\r\n[quote]By attumen (285 \u2013 6\u00b71) 9 days ago (Patch 6.0.2)\t\t\r\nJust soloed this about 10 minutes ago as a Resto Shaman. To do so I dropped a healing stream totem and then took control of Razorgore. When he takes aggro move him to the middle of the room (or closer to you) and dismiss him then drop another healing stream totem then take control again. If your healing stream totem is on CD drop a healing tide totem, though this has a long CD. Rinse and repeat this until all the eggs are destroyed.\r\n\r\n1) Drop Healing Totem\r\n2) Control\r\n3) Destroy eggs\r\n4) Boss takes aggro\r\n5) Release Control\r\n6) Repeat 1 - 5[/quote]", "date": "2014-10-29T14:56:15-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 254, "id": 2020955, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Onomatopoeia", "body": "Word of advice: After destroying the last egg, do [b]NOT[/b] kill him until after his HP resets to 100%. You'll thank me later.\n\nEDIT: Don't say I didn't warn you!", "date": "2014-10-30T04:40:41-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-10-30T04:41:30-05:00", 1, "Onomatopoeia"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 255, "id": 2021081, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "hawkswin", "body": "Simply put:  If you are a healing class (me), just heal him.  So simple.", "date": "2014-10-30T12:08:06-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
