{"commentv2": 1, "number": 257, "id": 2024378, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Azuuyr", "body": "Long story short, a Brewmaster [class=10]'s [skill=115315] (Summon Black Ox Statue) around the middle of the room will effectively tag every enemy in the room upon spawn, and even Razorgore when mind control breaks; making this fight match every other one in the dungeon for difficulty. \n\nAnother tip with this method is if Razorgore is picking up to many adds, to walk around the Ox Statue and it will quickly taunt the add off.\n\nI think it's safe to say this is the easiest way to solo Razorgore possible now.", "date": "2014-11-04T13:47:03-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-11-04T13:48:57-06:00", 1, "Azuuyr"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 258, "id": 2024628, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Evinor", "body": "I try to solo BWL each week. Razorgore continues to be a random 'lets kill your high level toon a few times' just to make you enjoy the WOW experience. No, Blizzard, this is infuriating beyond belief.  Yes, for some classes its a joy ride but for most of us its so not what we want from WOW. \r\n\r\nPlease adjust it so its relevant danger is at the same level as the rest of the entire raid.\r\n\r\nmy two bits worth", "date": "2014-11-05T04:13:49-06:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yeah, this is absolutely ridiculous. BWL was my favorite raid back in the day but I can't even get past the first boss anymore.", "creationdate": "2014-11-25T19:20:53-06:00", "id": 799585, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2024628, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Asator", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 259, "id": 2046444, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "borcar", "body": "virtually impossible now, something has changed since draenor launched.\r\n\r\nbefore as hunter i could dismiss pet and touch orb killing eggs nearest to orb first in pattern then moving out to far eggs and finish in two mind controls.  every week, week on end no issues.\r\n\r\nnow cannot even do this at all not even close to finished within two mind controls and usually dead by end of second.\r\n\r\nblizz freaking sucks, quit ruining old content for transmog and other items for no damn reason for crying out loud.", "date": "2014-11-23T20:01:39-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 260, "id": 2049281, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "RohkGash", "body": "I just did this fight as a feral druid and I found that if you bring him in range, target him, then cast a HoT ( Rejuv in this case) it will hit him before the control is broken. He went from 30% to 90% in a matter of seconds and the whole fight was much easier", "date": "2014-11-25T23:51:39-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 261, "id": 2050273, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "ErrEff", "body": "Here's how I did it as a level 100 protection warrior. I believe this method should work for [b]every class[/b], with the only requirement being that you're sufficiently high level enough that the enemies' attacks will reliably miss you. If needed, put on some buffs that can help you survive a lot of punishment.\r\n\r\n[ol]\r\n[li]Go straight for the control orb, (killing the channeler and his aides is optional).[/li]\r\n[li]Once in control of Razorgore, feel free to take out some eggs until the enemies start pouring in - personally I cleared the entire platform he starts on.[/li]\r\n[li]As Razorgore, run over to the orb platform and hug the wall behind your character. The enemies should aggro your character and not Razorgore. Some stragglers might get confused and target Razorgore but all threat should eventually transition over to your character.[/li]\r\n[li]Once your mind control stops channeling, quickly use the control orb again. Don't let Razorgore get involved in fighting because his [spell=23023] can be really annoying.[/li]\r\n[li]Wait out this second channeling in the same place as before - at this point the enemies should no longer spawn and they'll all be attacking your character.[/li]\r\n[li]You are now free to destroy the remaining eggs at your leisure. Don't forget to give Razorgore some breathing room before killing him to avoid any unfortunate bugs. Killing the trash enemies first before focusing on him is recommended.[/li]\r\n[/ol]\r\n\r\n[b]No special class abilities needed[/b], this is the simplest method I know.", "date": "2014-11-26T17:49:49-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This sort of works...but- you still aggro a few attackers, occasionally you need to taunt (preferably not kill because they'll respawn) an attacker off Razorgore. After you got them all, go crack the eggs and kill him.", "creationdate": "2014-11-28T12:45:30-06:00", "id": 801798, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2050273, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Dedmeett", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 262, "id": 2054201, "nreplies": 39, "sticky": 0, "user": "twopacalypse", "body": "EASY WAY TO SOLO THIS FOR ANY CLASS FOR DRAENOR\n\n\nJust do the normal routine of running around and destroying eggs.\nWhen you get a crowd of aggro no matter how far you are from the orb as razorgore just right click the orb (it was fairly simple for me to click even with a large crowd around my toon) and it will refill the channel bar and drop the aggro off razorgore and they will automatically go to your toon.\n\nand there you go.", "date": "2014-11-30T07:12:40-06:00", "rating": 767, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This totally works, you Sir are my hero!", "creationdate": "2014-11-30T11:27:01-06:00", "id": 803312, "rating": 26, "commentid": 2054201, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sajtalma", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Perfect! Thanks! After a dozen wipes, this one worked perfectly! MODERATORS - PLEASE MOVE THIS ONE WAY UP ON THIS PAGE!!", "creationdate": "2014-12-18T13:15:24-06:00", "id": 815067, "rating": 7, "commentid": 2054201, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Fitzr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This worked perfectly the first few times. However, when trying it today I had some trouble. Most of the mobs would switch targets to me, but a handful kept sticking to Razorgore. I finally noticed that instead of targeting me when I would refresh the channel, like he had been doing, he would turn to attack the mobs near him and gain aggro. A simple fix was to make sure there were no enemies in front of Razorgore when clicking on the orb.", "creationdate": "2014-12-23T18:40:43-06:00", "id": 817678, "rating": 17, "commentid": 2054201, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zyroes", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "As a Frost Mage you can not control the orb with your pet out. Simply dismiss it and then take control of Razorgore.", "creationdate": "2016-01-24T04:13:09-06:00", "id": 926469, "rating": 9, "commentid": 2054201, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Fedtmule", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "To clarify, you need to run RAZORGORE over to the orb and click on it. Don't dismiss control of him and then click it. Click it while you have control of him. Took me 3 wipes to figure out that's what twopocalypse meant.", "creationdate": "2016-05-13T01:26:32-05:00", "id": 942091, "rating": 27, "commentid": 2054201, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kelborn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-11-30T07:25:09-06:00", 1, "twopacalypse"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 263, "id": 2058893, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "varenne", "body": "how to solo Razorgore as any class guide http://youtu.be/X8WKXuefoMs", "date": "2014-12-04T09:27:56-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Ok I'm a lvl 100 destro lock. Enter the instance and kill the 3 on the platform. Then the sequence starts but I cannot click the orb... What am I doing wrong? It will not let me mind control the boss... :(", "creationdate": "2014-12-09T05:18:30-06:00", "id": 809614, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2058893, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "linz85", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "its because you have your pet out. dismiss pet for whole fight and you will have no problems.", "creationdate": "2014-12-11T10:04:35-06:00", "id": 810969, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2058893, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 16384, "username": "someguychilling", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This didn't work, they still spawn and attack him while he's behind me. ones attacking me also AOE and hit him. he dies by second channel, IF I can even get to the orb to click it. 8 wipes attempting to follow the video,.", "creationdate": "2014-12-29T01:49:03-06:00", "id": 820124, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2058893, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 16384, "username": "Vickrpg", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It doesnt works. Mobs still hits Razorgore. I tried to stay near my char, to lose aggro, but mobs still hits Razorgore. Tired to try this again. 8 wipes and a consider cost of repair...", "creationdate": "2015-01-25T17:19:11-06:00", "id": 832602, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2058893, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "aluiziofh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 264, "id": 2067374, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kaiva", "body": "It seems as though the damage output by adds has changed since 6.0 dropped, and many people are having trouble solo'ing this guy since MoP, despite being level 100.  Razorgore simply dies too quickly to the adds.\r\n\r\nAfter failing my attempts against him several times, here is the method that finally let me solo him.\r\n\r\n[ol]\r\n[li][b](This is the most important step)[/b] Do not use the mind control orb from on top of the elevated platform.  Instead, stand as close to the middle of the room as possible, while still being in range of the orb.  This way a lot more of the adds will attract to you, instead of Razorgore.  Using this method, by the time I had about 8 eggs remaining, Razorgore had taken almost no damage at all.[/li]\r\n[li][/li]\r\n\r\n[li]As mentioned by other people, clear the eggs nearest the mindcontrol orb first, working your way away from it.  This way near the end Razorgore wont have to take AoE damage from the adds as he clears the final eggs.[/li]\r\n[/ol]", "date": "2014-12-12T15:04:45-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 265, "id": 2069126, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "Cierona", "body": "I read the other suggestions and just ended up dying a lot, because cancelling the channel does not make all the aggro switch to your character.  Following the video in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=12435#comments:id=2058893]varenne's post[/url] worked (if you like this post please upvote that one too), although I think it would help to clarify exactly what is being done and why:\n\n[ul]\n[li]Run up to the platform with the orcs.[/li]\n[li]Position youself slightly back from the orb, so that when you end up covered in mobs you can still see it, and when they run up the stairs you are right in front of them.[/li]\n[li]Kill the orcs and activate the orb.[/li]\n[li]Bring Razorgore up onto the orb platform and destroy the eggs up there to start mobs spawning.[/li]\n[li]Move him right up against the wall behind you, and have him facing outwards (he seems to aggro a few mobs with his tail stuck out).[/li]\n[li]Don't wait for the possession to end before clicking on the orb, as it can be hard to hit when the camera jumps back to your character, and there are a lot of mobs around it.  If Razorgore is not possessed he will cast stuns on you making it even harder to reactivate the orb.  Luckily you can click it while the possessed Razorgore is stood anywhere in the room to restart the channel (one click restarts, you don't need to click twice to stop then restart) because your character is stood next to it and [i]is[/i] in range.[/li]\n[li]Keep reactivating the orb before the possesion ends until no more mobs are arriving.[/li]\n[li]When you're sure all the mobs have arrived and are busy attacking your character run Razorgore around and destroy eggs, but keep an eye on the possess bar, and reclick the orb to refill it when needed.[/li]\n[li]Destroy the eggs furthest from you last.[/li]\n[li]When all the eggs have been destroyed AoE the mobs on top of you, then wait for razorgore to start attacking you before attacking back.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n\n\n[edit] Couple more tips (I'm having no luck getting the pet off the 3rd boss, so I'm running this dungeon a lot):\n\n[ul]\n[li]If you kill any of the mobs, more will enter the room to replace them (wondered why they wouldn't stop coming with my shaman.  Had lightning shield on).  This method has to be the easiest because once everything is on you, you aren't dealing with any aggro issues, just reactivating the channel.[/li]\n[li]You do occasionally get one or two mobs aggroing Razorgore while he's sat at the back of the alcove.  I haven't worked out what causes this, but after 3 flawless runs on my other characters my priest had a couple of mobs attacking Razorgore, one of which was a caster sitting right in the middle of the pack, so I couldn't easily click on it to target it.  I had to tab-target through all the mobs until I found the one targetting him, cast an instant damage spell to kill it, then reactivate the orb before Razorgore could stun me (why we're activating the orb from max distance, so it isn't in the middle of all those mobs).[/li]\n[/ul]", "date": "2014-12-14T18:52:45-06:00", "rating": 39, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Tried this strategy today, it worked perfectly and was absolutley easy. Cleared BWL with my ilvl 635 prot pally in less then 15min.", "creationdate": "2014-12-15T07:13:24-06:00", "id": 813245, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2069126, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Akira2007", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Of all the strategies provided here, this is the only one that, so far, has a 100% success rate for me.", "creationdate": "2014-12-23T01:34:47-06:00", "id": 817303, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2069126, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kerluna", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Wish I could up-vote this more than once. HEY, EVERYONE UP THERE! COME DOWN HERE AND READ THE STRATEGY THAT ACTUALLY WORKS!", "creationdate": "2015-01-02T00:06:04-06:00", "id": 821923, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2069126, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "BaltarAvarian", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I created an account to come here and say this method works flawlessly. Granted I didn't get the Untamed Blade I wanted, but, the kill itself was a snap :)", "creationdate": "2015-01-05T19:17:47-06:00", "id": 823837, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2069126, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 16384, "username": "NayukiWar", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Standing at the bottom of the platform to activate the orb perfects this strategy.", "creationdate": "2015-01-12T07:37:37-06:00", "id": 826950, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2069126, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ElevenX", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-12-18T08:48:02-06:00", 10, "Cierona"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 266, "id": 2070139, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "plokmijn12", "body": "Trick for Paladins! [i](and possibly other classes with instant heals)[/i]\r\n\r\n[b]Lay on Hands![/b]\r\n\r\nAs soon as Razorgore gets low (~50%) get within range and use LoH. You'll break MC, but LoH will heal him before that happens and you'll grab aggro of all the mobs!\r\n\r\nI'm assuming other instant heals would work as well.", "date": "2014-12-16T01:22:00-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Worked for my Draenei mage with [spell=121093] ;)", "creationdate": "2014-12-18T17:06:53-06:00", "id": 815150, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2070139, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "AntidotE", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 267, "id": 2070544, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ladyluna", "body": "My guide to soloing post 6.0.2 stat squish (Did it on a 100 feral druid (640), 100 combat rogue (620ish), 92 fury warrior, and 93 shadow priest). I dunno if they hotfixed him or if the above post was wrong -- but on all my attempts he had 448k health\r\n\r\n1) Go up on the platform and grab ye olde orb.\r\n\r\n2) Start QUICKLY killing eggs, starting with whatever eggs are nearest. You can get through a good quarter of the room by doing this.\r\n\r\n3) When the adds come out watch Razorgore's health like a hawk. When he starts to lose oh, 10-20k health (from the last benchmark) dismiss him. MAKE SURE HE IS ON THE OTHER SIDE OF THE ROOM WHEN YOU DISMISS HIM. \r\n\r\n4) While Razorgore is running towards you regrab the orb. Maybe do a round of AoE if you have a -quick- AoE.\r\n\r\nRepeat this OFTEN. The fight takes a while but you will get all the eggs down. It took a few wipes on my druid to get the pattern down but got it in two shots on my rogue, one shot on my warrior (though it was close -- he was down to 20k health) and 2 attempts on my priest (When I stopped trying to AoE down the adds. It wasn't necessary and it was wasting time I could spend destroying eggs. Frequent dismissals are the key. You want as much aggro on you as possible because they won't be hitting you at all hard (with my priest I AoE'd nothing and they managed to take off maybe 5% of my health at level 92 in shadowform).\r\n\r\nHappy attempts!", "date": "2014-12-16T16:16:31-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 268, "id": 2070842, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Grimeggz", "body": "[b]Another trick for paladins! ~~[/b]\n\nWhenever you use Righteous Fury you get the all the mobs on Razorgore. \n\nHowever,make sure that you don't use it during Destroy Egg casting,because if you do,sometimes the egg gets bugged and after you destroy all other eggs,Razorgore will still suicide and take you out.", "date": "2014-12-17T03:16:12-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-12-17T04:05:18-06:00", 11, "Grimeggz"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 269, "id": 2072520, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "NckEU", "body": "A nice trick I found doing this boss is every time you click the orb as Razorgore (you can do it from any point in the room, since the distance that matters is between the orb and your character, not Razorgore) your character gets the aggro of EVERY mob in the room. So, do this every time you want to reset the aggro. ezpz!\n\nYou don't have to dismiss, just click the orb as Razorgore and you start the mind control again AND your character gets the aggro of everyone.", "date": "2014-12-19T17:50:30-06:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Brilliant suggestion! Wiped a few times before I read this due to his death mechanic but this makes it a walk in the park at lv100", "creationdate": "2014-12-21T13:19:17-06:00", "id": 816594, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2072520, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Valqaen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This doesn't seem to help with the axe wielding ones, who stick to him even after clicking the orb.", "creationdate": "2014-12-23T00:59:56-06:00", "id": 817294, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2072520, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kerluna", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Actually, I just did this, and it does work. You don't dismiss anyone. You just click on the orb, as Razorgore, and it renews the control meter. You can do it as much as you want.", "creationdate": "2014-12-26T13:52:42-06:00", "id": 818896, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2072520, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "nsmith6401", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I just registered only to upvote this. Saves me from buying a new mouse / keyboard every time I tried to solo this.", "creationdate": "2015-01-04T03:23:09-06:00", "id": 822972, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2072520, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "uusipaska", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Fantastic trick! Thank you so much for posting this. Key thing here is that you NEVER dismiss. Just click on the orb, from anywhere, while you are Razorgore.", "creationdate": "2015-01-04T19:15:48-06:00", "id": 823374, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2072520, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Dulahey", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-01-15T11:37:55-06:00", 2, "NckEU"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 270, "id": 2076536, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Oldblood", "body": "This fight is a total nightmare, it should've been nerfed into oblivion ages ago. I have used several strategies now. Clicking the orb to reset aggro, even putting the dragons to sleep, nothing has worked so far. I've solo'ed lots of raids now including ICC and Trail of the Crusader 25 man. Should doing Wrath raids be easier than Vanilla ones? Maybe it's just me.", "date": "2014-12-26T08:59:59-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 271, "id": 2076685, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kwhenn", "body": "Just soloed him with a lvl 98 monk (ilvl 585).\r\nBefore starting the fight I've read useful comments @ the instance's topic: http://www.wowhead.com/zone=2677#comments\r\nMy tactics was breaking eggs and nothing more! I paid no attention on the adds. He can do two cycles like this which is just enough to destroy all the eggs.", "date": "2014-12-26T13:08:27-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 272, "id": 2081733, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wamakaska", "body": "I have made an attempt on this multiple times using multiple classes and as of today I can no longer solo him.  There seems to be a serious issue with the lack of breaking the aggro from the boss to the adds now.  Prior to this I was able to solo this on almost every toon I had as the adds all dropped and came to me when I selected 'dismiss'.  Now a majority of them stay on the boss and I can't get them off him and to me without the dang boss dying (and as you know that means me as well).  My pally's righteous fury doesn't do it, nor any of my tank classes taunts. Something has changed....  \r\n\r\nBring a friend and save yourself the hassle.  \r\n\r\nOnce again... Blizzard, thanks for screwing up yet another part of the game by 'fixing' something that wasn't broken.", "date": "2015-01-03T13:44:47-06:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Agree. It's impossible to solo now. The add spawn rate is ridiculous and they no longer aggro your character but swarm Razorgore. Out of 5 tries tonight closest could get still had 6 or 7 eggs left.", "creationdate": "2015-01-14T02:44:21-06:00", "id": 827702, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2081733, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rakkasan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 273, "id": 2082323, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "robertalexstorm", "body": "For hunters attempting to solo, if you have the talent Exhilaration, use it while Razorgore is almost dead from adds and he will gain full health because the encounter treats him as a pet while he is under your control. You will lose control by doing this but he will have full health. I found it very helpful to solo.", "date": "2015-01-04T08:56:50-06:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 274, "id": 2083718, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Whisperwinds", "body": "As a [b] LV 75 Hunter[/b], I realized i needed to dismiss my pet otherwise I couldn't use the orb with Razorgore. \r\n\r\nI would kill everything around me, drop an explosive trap and control Razorgore. Everytime I saw a big group around me, i would hit escape to let go of Razorgore, then I would multishot everything around me down and place another explosive trap. \r\n\r\nIf Razorgore got aggro, I would multishot towards him and pull whatever was on him and repear while not aiming at Razorgore directly. \r\n\r\nHe came close to dying, but I did finished it. Don't be afraid to use Razorgores Soothe Dragonkin ability to deal with a few dragonkin.", "date": "2015-01-06T14:27:40-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 275, "id": 2087408, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "cefm", "body": "Anyone tried the Manual of Void-Calling [item=118936] yet?", "date": "2015-01-12T18:25:57-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 276, "id": 2090857, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Xiberion", "body": "Don't one shot him after the last egg dies. He dies and it still blows up the raid.", "date": "2015-01-18T13:48:30-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 277, "id": 2092938, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "usulnet", "body": "There's a lot of great information here but a lot of it isn't current.\n\nSimply go in, kill the 3 adds at the orb.  Use the orb to control him and start with the eggs furthest from the orb.  Spam the kill egg command (4) and do nothing else with him.\n\nEvery other egg you click the orb, you can target it across the room.  There is a 10 second debuff that'll make you fail to control him if you do it every egg but once every other egg is sufficient.  This will cause all the adds to attack you, at level 100 they don't do damage to you.\n\nKeep all of this up until you get up to the orb platform and kill the last egg.  The adds run away and you lose control of him.  At this point DO NOT kill him immediately as he'll still \"take you with him\".  Just white damage him or use slower killing spells and try not to kill him within 10 seconds.\n\nSo far this has worked on all of my alts and made this a breeze, yes he isn't a one shot boss like everything else but if you just stick to the mechanic you'll have him dead within 2 minutes.", "date": "2015-01-22T14:53:38-06:00", "rating": 29, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "upvoted, because now my chances of finishing Ten Storms, Judgement and Bloodfang by myself just increased! (oh and because the clicking the orb every other egg info helped 100%) As well as getting the pet from Chromaggus!", "creationdate": "2015-01-27T13:50:33-06:00", "id": 833272, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2092938, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tegre", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Worked like a charm. My usual MO is to toss Sacred Shield or an instant heal at Razorgore every so often, but my warrior obviously has no such move. Cleared my first attempt with Razorgore at ~90% upon the last egg... then I wiped on Vael because I went AFK to type this. Smooth.", "creationdate": "2015-02-01T08:00:11-06:00", "id": 835094, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2092938, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Porrim", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I like this idea, but because the mobs are swarming my toon while I'm MC'ing RG, it gets hard to click the orb from across the room. Once the orb gets too crowded to click on, I right-click RG's portrait, say Dismiss, do a quick thunderclap to kill all the mobs, then re-MC him.", "creationdate": "2015-02-28T23:55:44-06:00", "id": 849029, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2092938, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "unclevinny", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This needs to be noted at the top... best comment on this page.", "creationdate": "2016-01-17T23:31:38-06:00", "id": 925506, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2092938, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nondeth", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-02-25T15:03:04-06:00", 1, "usulnet"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 278, "id": 2098354, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "incognitoasdf", "body": "After watching old solo videos before WOD because there seemed to not be any for this expansion, just Cata and MOP, I read this forum section and read some disgustingly long detailed boring explanation that made me want to say f' it, i'll forget this transmog but took a little bit from Cierona's post and made it simpler:\n\nRun up to the orb platform.\nKill 3 guys.\nUse orb to possess Razorgore.\nStart by clearing the eggs on the platform where Razorgore starts.\nAfter NPCs start spawning and 3 are aggrod on you, run to the orb platform and stand against the back wall and dismiss him.\nJust an fyi, there is no longer a dismiss button for Razorgore; you have to right click his portrait and click on dismiss.\nLet mobs aggro on you for about 2 seconds then reclick the orb to possesss Razorgore again.\nContinue clearing the room on one side gradually and when you get aggrod by 3 or 4 NPCs  run him back to the wall like earlier and dismiss him.\nAs more NPCs spawn and aggro onto your actual character, it appears that their spawn rate does slow down slightly making it a little easier.\nRinse.\nRepeat until all eggs destroyed.\n\nTook me 8 miserably failed tries this morning but finished with half Razorgore's life left after doing it this way the first time.", "date": "2015-02-02T09:59:47-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-02-02T10:00:50-06:00", 1, "incognitoasdf"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 279, "id": 2121825, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wheeljack", "body": "With the recent stat-squish changes, and having leveled to 100, I found that I had to adjust tactics slightly. \r\nI used to be able to simply run around destroying eggs starting at the rightmost one as you enter the room and working my way back to the orb while every so often, dismiss and let mobs aggro me. This used to work flawlessly.\r\n\r\nHowever, after having wiped no less than 6 times on this today, due to the fact that mobs didn't aggro my character anymore (they even kept attacking RG after I had dismissed), I tried a different approach than earlier. \r\n\r\nThis is a tactic I found to work better. \r\n[b]First MC:[/b] Destroy as many eggs you can at the furthermost platform from the orb. \r\n[b]Second MC:[/b] As adds spawn, run to where the orb is and destroy eggs around there. I found that the adds aggro you more then. \r\n[b]Third MC:[/b] Destroy the eggs in the middle, dismissing and re-controlling RG if adds should overwhelm him.", "date": "2015-02-24T15:30:52-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If you click on the orb instead of dismissing you can get the mobs to attack you instead of RG. You can click the orb from anywhere in the room. Don't click it too often as there is a debuff that prevents you from spamming it but every other egg is fine.", "creationdate": "2015-02-25T15:04:36-06:00", "id": 847043, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2121825, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "usulnet", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Really? I did not know that. Thanks for the tips.", "creationdate": "2015-03-05T00:19:35-06:00", "id": 851104, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2121825, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wheeljack", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 280, "id": 2123745, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "DanteStrauss", "body": "As of patch 6.1 this encounter is really easy to solo, as long as you follow the mechanics.\nOne in particular is the fact that in this encounter, as mentioned in other comments, there can only be 40 adds up at a time and you can use this to your advantage:\n\nAs soon as you kill the 3 orcs and MC the boss destroy both eggs near the orb and move the boss towards the wall behind the orb until you can only see his tail/wings... Now wait until all the 40 adds are up (takes about 2 to 3 minutes, usually) then after you get aggro on all of them on your toon start killing the remaining eggs with the MC'd boss.\nOf course, don't forget to MC him again by clicking the orb when the timer is about to expire. Since there will be 40 adds on top of you, try to MC him again when there's still around 20 seconds remaining on the MC in case it takes a bit long for you to manage to click the orb. By following this you usually never need to worry about the adds attacking him.\n\nJust one thing to watch out for: When you kill the last egg the adds will run away and the boss will start attacking you, but in one of my killings the last egg was the one to the left of the orb and as soon as I destroyed the egg I killed the boss (around 1-2 seconds timeframe between both) this caused the encounter not to counter as being done properly and the room still exploded as if there was still eggs on it. On the next try I waited ~5 seconds after the adds ran away to finally attack the boss and I managed to kill it successfully! This is most likely a bug, so just wait a bit before finishing him up and you should be good.\n\nDid this as an 670 Hunter and by the end of it my health had dropped only to 99,1% so its doable with a much low ilvl than that.", "date": "2015-02-26T02:52:56-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Very much this for me; before doing this, adds killed Razorgore each time. A few addendums/clarifications: 1/ the wall is the curved wall; just park him *in* the wall as much as possible (tail first, head sticking out may be easier, see point 2); 2/ you can reclick the orb halfway a MC from Razorgore's point of view. If you put yourself down in front of the stage (adds far away from Razorgore), it's very easy to renew the MC directly from Razorgore's pov; 3/ it takes about 1.5 MCs for all the adds to appear. After that, you have free reign breaking eggs.", "creationdate": "2015-03-20T10:44:51-05:00", "id": 856394, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2123745, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "nirish", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If you have trouble with clicking the orb you can jump down. The NPCs will follow you and you have enought space for clicking the orb comfortable.", "creationdate": "2015-03-27T17:39:21-05:00", "id": 858284, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2123745, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Cilenco", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Having a bug where the adds all go to him no matter what I do, even when I'm close to my body..", "creationdate": "2015-10-02T15:34:16-05:00", "id": 902379, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2123745, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MissVern", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-02-26T02:54:30-06:00", 1, "DanteStrauss"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 281, "id": 2130103, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "traugdor", "body": "As of the current patch of this posting Razorgore and the entire raid can be soloed by a level 70 BM Hunter as I have just done.\r\n\r\nI didn't record video or I'd link to it, but it can still be done.", "date": "2015-03-04T23:29:55-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 282, "id": 2130817, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "NoOneImportnt", "body": "When soloing this as a paladin, Divine Shield can be used directly after Razorgore dies to prevent the instant death.", "date": "2015-03-05T13:41:41-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 283, "id": 2130847, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "NoOneImportnt", "body": "After wiping numerous times, I figured out through a comment that re clicking the orb will drop all aggro from Razorgore, and place back on the character. This also resets the MC timer.\r\n\r\nI completed all of the eggs through this method without killing any adds. I am a level 100 ret paladin at ilvl 650, and my health got down to 70%.", "date": "2015-03-05T13:54:36-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 284, "id": 2132512, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nufire", "body": "A 3+ minute video shows you all you need to know to solo Razorgore (in my case it was with a level 100 Mage)\n\n[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zst5zuh2D1Q]\n\nafter several wipes, I followed Zeet's method and did it first time.\n\nCheers Zeet :)", "date": "2015-03-07T09:34:23-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-03-07T09:39:49-06:00", 2, "Nufire"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 285, "id": 2135770, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Drax13", "body": "To sum up the best advice on this page, just re-click the orb when too many adds get on Razorgore. This will cause them to drop aggro on the boss and come after you. You can target and click it from anywhere in the room.", "date": "2015-03-12T11:29:25-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is the best way to solo (only way?), Basically every time I got adds on me as razergore I clicked the orb as razergore and they all left razergore for my toon.", "creationdate": "2015-04-07T22:30:19-05:00", "id": 861232, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2135770, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Quesenek", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Wish your post was at the top, would save a lot of time for everyone.", "creationdate": "2015-05-02T20:42:06-05:00", "id": 867087, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2135770, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Cynical1", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-03-12T11:30:13-05:00", 1, "Drax13"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 286, "id": 2137351, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Anyanka", "body": "As Ret Pally I was able to solo this by dismissing him when adds started attacking him then cast Lights Hammer at my feet and click the orb again.  I did this rotation about 3 times before all eggs were dead.  Be sure to wait for ALL adds to leave the room before killing Razorgore or it will still be in first phase and you will explode.\n\np.s. Also be sure he is all the way on the other side of the room before casting Lights Hammer, because it will one shot him and then game over.", "date": "2015-03-14T07:04:57-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-03-14T07:05:43-05:00", 1, "Anyanka"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 287, "id": 2140530, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "icheat", "body": "If you kill the boss prior to breaking all the eggs, you die. If you have an instance cast HoT/heal, move the boss close to you while it is still under your control, then cast your HoT/heal on the boss, breaking the MC, but healing the boss. Don't bother killing adds, just wait your time until you can reclick the orb, and continue to break eggs.", "date": "2015-03-19T22:46:02-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 288, "id": 2152562, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Grogg", "body": "All you need to do to solo it is to keep clicking on the orb again before it falls off, do not \"exit\" the vehicle that is the dragon you are controlling. When you click the orb it seems the dragon drops aggro and you get the aggro again. There is no need to hide the dragon away in a corner.", "date": "2015-04-03T15:14:21-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-04-03T15:32:23-05:00", 2, "Grogg"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 289, "id": 2157750, "nreplies": 32, "sticky": 0, "user": "Fraudulent", "body": "Too much old, worthless info. Here is truly THE only thing that has ever worked for me, and has worked EVERY time flawlessly as of April 8, 2015. I will be very detailed just so that there is no question, but once you do this, you'll see how easy it is:\n\n[ol]\n\n[li]Kill the mobs around the orb.[/li]\n\n[li]Jump down to the floor below and click the orb from max range. Face outwards.[/li]\n\n[li]Walk Razorgore over to you, and first destroy the egg in front of your toon, then the two eggs up on the platform with the orb.[/li]\n\n[li]Then, move Razorgore to the back of the platform, turn around and back him into the wall, tail first as far as you can go, so that he is facing outwards towards the orb. You will not be able to see your toon, but if you cleared the 2 eggs on the platform, you will be able to see the orb, and also beyond it, you can see the mobs spawning from the other side of the room, running towards the platform.[/li]\n\n[li]Wait a while... until all ~40 mobs spawn. If you did this all correctly so far, you will observe how all mobs run up to the platform and up to the orb, but they then turn around, walk down to the floor, and attack your toon instead. This is because your toon is closest aggro.[/li]\n\n[li]This is critical to success: Before the timer expires, say, with about 5 sec left, [u]reclick the orb while it is still channeling[/u], but also [u]only click it only once[/u] every time you are recasting the mind control. Reclicking the orb as it is still channeling instantly starts the timer over, and Razorgore will not move at all since he is only released for just a microsecond. If you don't do this, Razorgore being free even 1 second can allow him to move close enough to draw aggro from the mobs running up to the orb before they can aggro on you. Clicking the orb just once to re-channel is also important because it has a cooldown of about 8 seconds. So if you spam click it out of paranoia, you'll incur the cooldown, Razorgore will walk down the platform and you lose.[/li]\n\n[li]After a while, you'll see that no more mobs are spawning and they are all attacking you. Any level 100 will easily auto-regen the damage they do. You are now free to take Razorgore around the room and destroy all the eggs. First, destroy the eggs at the other side of the room, and then work your way to the ones closest to your toon last, to avoid any aggro. As with #6, always reclick the orb [u]before[/u] the timer expires so that you retain constant control. Remember, it doesn't matter how far Razorgore is from the orb. Your toon is always right by it, so you can reclick the orb from anywhere in the room you are playing with Razorgore.[/li]\n\n[li]After all eggs are destroyed, the mobs will start to run away. Do NOT attack Razorgore yet. Wait until the mobs are gone, and then mouseover the orb. If the orb is NOT clickable anymore, then the egg event has completed and you can now 1-shot Razorgore with your most furious graphics-card shattering attack.[/li]\n\n\nEDIT: This strat works due to two key aspects of this encounter:\na) There are a limited number of mobs that can be active at one time - about 40\nb) If they are not attacked, the mobs aggro the nearest creature and stay there until something else comes closer", "date": "2015-04-08T22:41:48-05:00", "rating": 259, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Wish I could up vote this more than once. Worked perfectly!", "creationdate": "2015-04-28T18:49:21-05:00", "id": 866297, "rating": 10, "commentid": 2157750, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ThePast", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Genius! I never knew you could click the orb so far away as Razorgore. I didn't have to worry about second-guessing how much time was left on channeling. When it got to about the halfway mark and I was at the far side, I just turned around and clicked it. And again about 20 seconds later just because I could. Razorgore never got agro, and my toon at level 100 never saw his health dip. Thank you, thank you, thank you!", "creationdate": "2015-05-06T18:02:53-05:00", "id": 868040, "rating": 8, "commentid": 2157750, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sleepless", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This needs to be upvoted more/stickied. As a class that doesn't have any instant heals that can be used on [i]others[/i] (warrior, rogue etc) this is the only strategy that has worked for me.", "creationdate": "2015-05-25T18:27:10-05:00", "id": 871644, "rating": 6, "commentid": 2157750, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "plokmijn12", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "the ONLY strategy that works now from what i can tell/have tried over the last few days til i finally saw this one :D AND Untamed Hatchling dropped, now named Fraudulents Legacy!", "creationdate": "2015-07-02T20:50:00-05:00", "id": 880919, "rating": 7, "commentid": 2157750, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "rothmus", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "So much this comment. Back to being cake again", "creationdate": "2015-07-12T04:13:23-05:00", "id": 883813, "rating": 7, "commentid": 2157750, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "stuie382", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-04-08T22:53:36-05:00", 3, "Fraudulent"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 290, "id": 2170859, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Svenskazzinoth", "body": "I just did it on 6.1 and read through these comments for help, only to find out that none of them work since Razorgore is a weakling who takes damage like crazy. Instead I used another tactic where I ran around to the eggs and when I got 4+ mobs on razorgore I reclicked the orb across the room to get aggro to me. And since I was level 100 I took 0 damage from them. Razorgore will survive, he had 50-ish % left when I was done with the orbs. \r\n\r\nDefinitely the easiest tactic as none of the others seem to work in 6.1.", "date": "2015-04-23T14:43:43-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thanks, this helped alot. Easiest tactic indeed.", "creationdate": "2015-05-24T21:39:53-05:00", "id": 871468, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2170859, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Chryzt", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You are a friggin' genius!! I would hug you if I could!! /HUG", "creationdate": "2015-05-30T04:02:44-05:00", "id": 872387, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2170859, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Missbhavin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 291, "id": 2190619, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "rmalheiros", "body": "I did this guy today as a [class=11] (Guardian, Bear Form).\r\nWhat I did:\r\n\r\nI killed guys close to Orb and start MC.\r\nWhen MC broke I spammed [spell=106832] to kill adds on me.\r\n\r\nMC again\r\n\r\nWhen it had under 200k health I brought it at casting range and casted [spell=774].\r\n I spammed [spell=106832] again until it was close to me.\r\n\r\nMC again\r\n\r\nKept doing this until all eggs were broken.\r\n\r\nHoTs and other Instant cast spell may heal it as it is still you pet for a short time after MC is broken.\r\nHard cast heal will rather heal you as it will be hostile.", "date": "2015-06-06T02:52:55-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 292, "id": 2196807, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "roenne", "body": "Solo... [i]COMPLETE[/i]! [b]6/21/2015[/b] ~~~> WoD 6.1 with a Sub-Rogue iLVL616 (yeah, I just got back into the game for 6.2 which is dropping in a few days...).\r\n\r\nhttp://john.do/solo-razorgore/ \r\n\r\nNot too difficult... same thing that I've done before. Get it done! Every other class shouldn't have a problem I imagine... I really don't understand all the people who are complaining... I mean, I described the video years ago and the methodology hasn't changed [b]ONE SINGLE BIT[/b]...", "date": "2015-06-21T19:42:26-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 293, "id": 2198151, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tantrevalles", "body": "OK - through trial and error I put the somewhat confusing variety of instructions below to work. Because I'm an idiot, it took me a while to learn the following:\r\n\r\n[1] When I have control over Razorgore, most if not all of the aggro is directed towards my toon on the stand. Depending on how much damage you can take, you only have to return control from Razorgore back to your toon when the timer times out or when your health gets dangerously low, whichever comes first. \r\n\r\n[2] Heal yourself if necessary after control returns to your toon, then quickly use the orb to get control over Razorgore again and resume angrily destroying your precious eggs.\r\n\r\n[3] I kept trying to get all fancy, but, no, it turns out that Razorgore can just get right on down to the egg-destroyin' business while you monitor your own toon's health as all of the orcs and dragonkin from the immediate Tri-State area pounds on it up there on the stand.\r\n\r\nI'm a 78-level somewhat twinked Ret Pally, so I had to do one Lay On Hands heal halfway through and then some \"whew, in the nick of time\" flash heals after Razorgore destroyed the last egg, and then it was just a matter of being able to hit Razorgore in-between bouts of the confusion spell or what annoying thing is used.\r\n\r\nThere you go; you're fine if you have access at least one large, fast heal. If you're a high enough level you don't need that.", "date": "2015-06-23T21:10:55-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
