{"commentv2": 1, "number": 296, "id": 2217224, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Cheryl", "body": "Was having trouble with this as a hunter, so I looked into my bags for something that might help.\r\nIn between channeling, to get the mobs off of him I used this: [item=86565]\r\n\r\nThat seemed to make the whole thing much easier.", "date": "2015-07-19T23:03:19-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "yeah i was having issues today as well. so i went and got the horn.... didn't do shit for me, mobs did't come after me, continued attacking Razorgore and killed him -.- Edit: Yeah horn does not a damn thing, I just died again after using the horn and not ONE add came after me. dont bother wasting time to get this it apparently doesnt do anything in here. Edit 2: Yup definitely does not work here or is broken because three times now and nothing happens.", "creationdate": "2015-08-27T10:54:51-05:00", "id": 894815, "rating": -2, "commentid": 2217224, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LordRahl19", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 297, "id": 2230487, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Buffeninc", "body": "I have made a video regarding this encounter - I've tested out most of the tactics on this page and found that the simplest way for me to deal with Razorgore is to dismiss him after he gets aggro from ads. \r\n\r\nFrom what i found, the key element is not to stress out when there's a lot of ads on Razorgore, but just simply to take it easy and repeatedly dismiss and control him until you get the ads to aggro the player. \r\n\r\nCheck out the video here if you have problems with the encounter:\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TEV3AEB6p64", "date": "2015-08-13T06:14:11-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 298, "id": 2232656, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "piszozo", "body": "As if we could not think to refresh orb to get all aggro... But it is bugged or not working. Mobs are attacking to Razorgore directly even if i dont touch orb let alone refreshing it...", "date": "2015-08-15T14:20:57-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 299, "id": 2236373, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "silkfire", "body": "It's important to start destroying the eggs closest to the orb and then moving towards the other side. This allows you to keep as greatest distance from you and Razorgore as possible, allowing you to AoE down the adds without accidentally killing Razorgore. You have to use AoE everytime you let go of MC or the entire crowd of adds will obscure the orb and you'll never be able to re-click it.\n\nTook me three times to master the strategy properly. I finished all eggs with Razorgore at 5% HP.\nGood luck!", "date": "2015-08-21T17:52:06-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-08-21T17:52:51-05:00", 1, "silkfire"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 300, "id": 2247898, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "mijlen", "body": "lvl 90 BM Hunter, been struggling trying to solo this jerk for my Battle Pet cheev, but finally found the right combo of strats in case anyone else is still scratching their head:\r\n\r\n1. do not have a pet with you, first of all. Easy peasy. \r\n\r\n2. Click the orb while you're on the floor, in front of the platform. This is because you'll need to click it to channel again and, like others have said, that's impossible to do when you have every single add in the encounter piled on top of you/it. \r\n\r\n3. On the first channel of Razorgore, destroy the eggs on the ground closest to the platform. The first four or five. This will ensure that you've cleared out a good aggro-free area around the eventual mob of adds.\r\n\r\n4. Go up onto the orb platform, destroy that egg, hug the wall sideways so you're mostly clipping into it, and WAIT. \r\n\r\n5. Wait through the end of the first channel, click the orb again, wait through the end of the second channel. Your toon can take it if you're decent level/gear enough to solo anything in old world raiding, so no worries whatsoever. \r\n\r\n5 1/2. When Razorgore gets the inevitable three/four adds aggroed to him up on the platform while half-clipped into the wall, you're far enough from the action to Cleave them down without pulling more. \r\n\r\n6. After the second channel is totally finished, that's it. You're done with adds. They've all spawned and they should all be pounding on your toon. Click the orb again. \r\n\r\n7. Come down off the platform making a pretty wide circle around the adds that are concentrated under the platform, and start egg-destroying. \r\n\r\n8. The rest is self-explanatory. Should only take a channel and a half to get all of 'em, tops. Razorgore will still have most of his health and then finishing the encounter is just a spank away! \r\n\r\nHave fun cheev/mog hunting!", "date": "2015-09-07T13:50:00-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Mijlen says it, but let's get some caps: DON'T KILL ADDS!!! I flunked a few times because I had forgotten about that. Don't kill them. Let them all gather on your toon, while you keep Razorgore safe. After second channel, go pop eggs.", "creationdate": "2015-10-07T16:36:35-05:00", "id": 903261, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2247898, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kalamath", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "That is actually the key point. I wiped a few times as i was killing adds (just cause i can) :P, and they wouldn't stop spawning.", "creationdate": "2015-10-17T11:34:28-05:00", "id": 905026, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2247898, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "niqushortz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "COMPLETELY flawless info, Mijlen! Tried other solo methods as a 693 Tankadin, but with how you say to position your toon beneath the platform BUT within range of clicking the orb made this work 100% on my first try! Thnx for the solid job!", "creationdate": "2015-11-12T09:03:43-06:00", "id": 910546, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2247898, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "patriknashnl", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 301, "id": 2248973, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Shadowwhelp", "body": "Warlocks:\r\n\r\nTake off Demonic Servitude and cast Infernal after the first cast of the orb finishes. He'll be able to kill enough of them that they get off of Razorgore and don't murder him.\r\n\r\nIt's worked for me every time I've tried.\r\n\r\n(PS: You have to \"dismiss\" Razorgore like you would your imp or voidwalker or what have you if you want to get out of orb control, not use the button.)", "date": "2015-09-09T16:47:27-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Can't the infernal damage the boss too though?", "creationdate": "2016-05-29T03:00:23-05:00", "id": 944487, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2248973, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "gbunkz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
