{"commentv2": 1, "number": 303, "id": 2269191, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "desius", "body": "For those of you completing this [b]SOLO:[/b]\n\nThis method works for [u][b]all[/b][/u] classes without issue (I have done this on Warrior, Druid, Rogue, Mage, Hunter, and Shaman)\n\n[b]1.  When a mob has aggro/begins to attack Razorgore, click orb ONCE while STILL controlling Razorgore (NOTE: this can be done anywhere inside the room!).  This will refresh your channeling, but also allows you to drop aggro.\n\n2.  Once mob drops aggro from Razorgore, continue using \"Destroy Egg\".\n\n3.  Use \"Calm Dragonkin\" if a dragonkin does not leave Razorgore immediately.\n\n4.  Once last egg is destroyed, you will leave Razorgore.  Kill him for phat BWL lootz![/b]\n\nYou will be able to wipe the whole room without leaving Razorgore.  I have never failed using this method.\n\n[b]NOTE:[/b]  If you accidently hit the orb twice while controlling Razorgore, you will return to your character.  You will have to wait 10 seconds before you can hit the orb again.  Just AoE down the mobs at the orb, then take control of Razorgore again.", "date": "2015-10-28T00:33:19-05:00", "rating": 22, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thanks! This worked like a charm :)", "creationdate": "2015-11-18T08:51:23-06:00", "id": 911902, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2269191, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Skatha", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "thanks, that helped a lot", "creationdate": "2015-11-22T15:12:10-06:00", "id": 912974, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2269191, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "vandyke", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This was easier for me than Wolfenstein3000's method. Although the wait-for-mobs-to-stop-spawning worked, it required finding the gearwheel in all those mobs with Razorgore very close. Clicking from across the room to drop aggro was easier for me. Thanks for the advice!", "creationdate": "2015-11-26T11:24:03-06:00", "id": 914048, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2269191, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "love45acp", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I have heard the horror stories with this boss, watched your video and one shotted this encounter on my first attempt. Thank you!", "creationdate": "2015-12-02T00:27:44-06:00", "id": 915198, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2269191, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Shagerty", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This is by far the best method for doing this. Thanks alot!", "creationdate": "2015-12-12T19:32:31-06:00", "id": 917681, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2269191, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "FlipFlopFantasy", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2018-02-21T12:52:02-06:00", 12, "desius"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 304, "id": 2270884, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wolfenstein3000", "body": "Here is by far the very easiest way to do this boss solo by any class - no more silly mechanics:\n\n1. Kill the 3 guys at the orb and then use the orb to mind control (MC) Razoregore\n\n2. Bring Razorgore onto your platform and get him to kill the two eggs there. \n\n3. Park Razorgore at the back of the curved wall on your platform - at the very back so his head is buried in the wall. \n\n4. Mobs will start spawning, but they will run to you, not Razorgore\n\n5. Let the mobs pile up on you - at 100 they will all miss you anyway - and when MC runs out re-MC immediately but do not kill any of the mobs. ([i]this is the only \"tricky part\" due to the game camera shifting point of view from Razorgore to yourself when MC channeling ends. However, don't panic, you will have a second or two to click again on the orb and re-establish MC. If you wait too long, Razorgore will enter the pile of mobs on you and the risk is one of them will attack him too.[/i])\n\n6. The mob spawns have a limit and you will see that no more run out after a while.\n\n7. When no more mobs are running out - but are still piled on you at the orb - walk Razorgore around and kill the eggs. The mobs won't touch him.\n\n8. You won't be able to kill all the eggs in one MC so when the MC runs out, make sure Razorgore is at the opposite end of the room and then re-MC.\n\n9. When the last egg is killed, the mobs will vanish/run out of room and you can fight Razorgore.\n\n[b]NOTE: do not kill any of the mobs or they start re-spawning and will attack Razoregore.[/b]\n\nIt took me about 15 attempts following all the other advice methods here and then by chance I read about this method on battlenet forums. It works like a charm - until Blizzard nerf it I guess. After that every other boss/mob in BWL is very easy to solo.", "date": "2015-11-01T21:43:39-06:00", "rating": 35, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Did this method again last night. Works perfectly.", "creationdate": "2015-11-05T16:46:41-06:00", "id": 909291, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2270884, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wolfenstein3000", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This works great. Much easier than anything else I've tried. Two things I'd add: park yourself [b]in front of the Orb[/b] (on the edge of the platform, or even right in front of it) before you click on it and also [b]turn off nameplates[/b] (V on your keyboard if you have the standard bindings). This makes finding the orb to re-click it a lot easier.", "creationdate": "2015-11-13T13:51:37-06:00", "id": 910829, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2270884, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Flannags", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "good call Flannags. I did BWL again last night and I got greedy at the start and had Razorgore destroy a few of the egss in front of the platform before parking him as above. A mob attacked him and I had to wipe and reset.", "creationdate": "2015-11-16T17:49:46-06:00", "id": 911536, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2270884, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wolfenstein3000", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "THANK YOU!!!! Just a side note, it takes 2 mind controls for the mobs to reach their max. (you might want to wait a bit longer though just in case you killed any mobs while trying to click the orb) So on your third mind control you should be good to start breaking eggs. Also helps if you change your view to a top-down look when you are about to lose MC. It makes it easier to click the orb. Good Luck :)", "creationdate": "2015-12-20T18:32:25-06:00", "id": 919831, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2270884, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "grundge", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Works great. I had two mobs that ended up attacking Razorgore. One was a dragonkin so I just kept putting him to sleep.", "creationdate": "2016-04-23T14:23:30-05:00", "id": 939501, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2270884, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "purenrgy", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-11-03T20:48:22-06:00", 3, "Wolfenstein3000"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 305, "id": 2295296, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "rezzax", "body": "If you don't want to read all these long posts ill sum it up quickly. \r\n\r\nWhen the mobs go on Razorgore, simply click the MC orb and the mobs go to your character instead of Razorgore, just repeat this.", "date": "2016-01-05T17:42:23-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 306, "id": 2295989, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Caylindra", "body": "Solo Completion:\r\n\r\n0) Send any pets away.\r\n1) Kill the three mobs and click the orb\r\n2) Kill all the eggs (Hotkey = 4) - never use any other skills.\r\n3) Get rid of attacking mobs / aggro by clicking the orb. You are able to \"range-click\" the orb when you control Razorgore.\r\n4) After killing all of the eggs, wait until all mobs have despawned. Do not immediately kill Razorgore, this can result in resetting the encounter.\r\n5) Kill Razorgore and do not forget to loot.", "date": "2016-01-08T06:26:15-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "\"4) After killing all of the eggs, wait until all mobs have despawned. Do not immediately kill Razorgore, this can result in resetting the encounter.\" This has never happened to me ever, I destroy the eggs and then kill him straight away, it has never reset the encounter.", "creationdate": "2016-01-31T12:27:48-06:00", "id": 927617, "rating": -1, "commentid": 2295989, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "biggaz69", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 307, "id": 2316401, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Almachai", "body": "Running Blackwing Lair has become a routine for me because it is one of the vanilla dungeons/raids left untouched by Cataclysm level scaling and subsequent item removal.\r\n\r\nBlackwing Lair is the only way to get most dragonscales anymore, especially [item=15416], which some choose to make some nice transmog items with. This scarcity of scales is because Upper Blackrock Spire's black dragons were removed, and most remaining dragons in Azeroth have had their levels altered so that they no can longer drop scales adequately.\r\n\r\nThe pets in this raid are also good for collecting, pet battles, and selling.\r\n\r\nLastly, Nefarian drops some incredible recipes, and not too uncommonly either. I have had a huge variety of these loot-list items drop, and they are even more difficult to come by in the world anymore because of aforementioned level scaling. He can also drop [item=1973], which have upped in value since they became a toy.\r\n\r\nHere is a list of recipes he has personally dropped [i][b]at least[/b][/i] once for me:\r\n\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][item=12720][/li]\r\n[li][item=14510][/li]\r\n[li][item=14497][/li]\r\n[li][item=14507][/li]\r\n[li][item=14501][/li]\r\n[li][item=12716]*** from mobs in BWL[/li]\r\n[li][item=7976]*** This is arguably the least valuable, most common plan Nefarian drops[/li]\r\n[li][item=8028][/li]\r\n[li][item=11226][/li]\r\n[li][item=12692][/li]\r\n[li][item=13518]*** A guildie friend found this from him[/li]\r\n[li][item=13488][/li]\r\n[li][item=13487][/li]\r\n[li][item=16055][/li]\r\n[li][item=16044][/li]\r\n[li][item=15742][/li]\r\n[/ul] \r\n\r\nThe biggest issue I've seen people have is getting past the first boss. It definitely is a strategy one needs to get accustomed to. Here are my tips for soloing:\r\n\r\n1.) Grab the orb to start, take out all the eggs and make your way slowly to your character\r\n2.) When you get a dragonkin on you, lull it to sleep with spell \"5\"\r\n3.) Let go of the boss with escape or the red arrow and AoE the mobs around you. And depending on your character, throw a HoT on yourself. That will help aggro stay on you\r\n4.) Don't let go of Razorgore near the end. The aggro shift won't do much after you've gotten to a certain point\r\n5.) [b]DO NOT[/b] attack him until he heals himself. If you do, he will reset and kill everybody.\r\n\r\nI hope this helps. Good luck farming!", "date": "2016-03-23T16:28:16-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 308, "id": 2316807, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ipic909", "body": "if you're hunter or warlock you need to disable you pets or else you cannot mind control razogore and that means you screwed", "date": "2016-03-25T10:30:11-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 309, "id": 2328920, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "6rad", "body": "If you're soloing him as lvl 100 Pally, Do not be afraid to make him tank some damage. You can keep him in Focus and the Target him and cast Lay on Hands, You'll get a lot of threat and give him that hp boost that makes the egg destroying so much easier.", "date": "2016-05-08T12:39:22-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 310, "id": 2334055, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "scrazzy", "body": "Easily soloable by this:\n1. Position self on platform close to middle of room\n2. Mind control him and immediately clear eggs on his platform\n3. Run on platform with orb before first adds spawn\n4. Adds will aggro your character so you can clear eggs around your character\n5. Clear eggs under platform and when mind control is about to expire run to middle of room\n6. With Razorgore in middle, cancel mind control, cast ONE AOE spell and immediately mind control him again\n7. Return to your character and continue clearing eggs \n8. Anytime you have 4-5+ mobs on Razorgore, bring him to middle of room, so your aoe will not hit him\n9. Cancel mind control, cast aoe and immediately mind control him\n\nIt looks like hitting adds with aoe, in my case [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=1449/arcane-explosion]Arcane Explosion[/url], and mind controling him takes all aggro and adds from him.", "date": "2016-05-25T10:44:32-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-05-25T10:45:40-05:00", 3, "scrazzy"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 311, "id": 2336199, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "nittles", "body": "This is very easy to do as a druid, doesn't matter which spec, just go into bear form, take control of him, destroy some eggs, dismiss him, Thrash + Rejuvenation for aggro, rinse and repeat.", "date": "2016-06-01T12:50:17-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
