{"commentv2": 1, "number": 317, "id": 2352683, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Bandeeto", "body": "Really easy to solo him as a Brewmaster Monk, just summon a Black Ox Statue in the middle of the room, and whenever he starts taking any damage just run to the middle of the room and the statue will pick up the adds. The mobs can't even hurt the statue, I finished this with Razorgore at 80% and my statue had a small army on him and he never left 100%.", "date": "2016-07-19T01:00:08-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "How? My statue just disappears whenever I take control of Razorgore", "creationdate": "2016-07-24T09:13:18-05:00", "id": 954076, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2352683, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "srwaan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Same happens with statue, just disappears.", "creationdate": "2016-07-25T22:38:25-05:00", "id": 954642, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2352683, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "nookbk", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 318, "id": 2354327, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Snoddas76", "body": "Has anyone else noticed that now in Legion pre-patch (7.0.3), Razorgore mechanics have changed so it's to me at least not soloable anymore? I used to go up against the wall on the platform were the orb is, let my toon take all mobs and just refresh the control orb until all mobs were out and attacking my toon. \r\n\r\nNow however, clicking the orb to refresh the control, instead turns off the control and then it takes a few seconds before i can click it again to regain control of Razorgore at which point he is already among the mobs getting hurt. :(", "date": "2016-07-21T08:21:08-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The same thing for me ;( Also refreshing the orb doesn't completely reset Razorgore's aggro, some mobs keep attacking him.", "creationdate": "2016-07-22T07:35:25-05:00", "id": 953451, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2354327, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Mirielle", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 319, "id": 2355272, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Grim32", "body": "Still soloable in 7.0.3 - but it's now down more to luck. Threat doesn't drop properly, but as long as you do the tricks of standing far from the orb on the lower floor. You may get a little lucky with aggro. Still took me 8 tries.", "date": "2016-07-22T14:40:36-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "had the same problem with exiting razorgore but clicking the orb while controlling razorgore always dropped the aggro", "creationdate": "2016-09-17T16:58:50-05:00", "id": 980264, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2355272, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "TheShadowX", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 320, "id": 2355430, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheRunningback0", "body": "As of 7.0.3 Mind Control cancels after destroying one egg until adds spawn. I'm unsure if this is intentional or not. \r\n\r\nSee below video on how to mitigate this as Razorgore might not live long enough to destroy all of the eggs.\r\n\r\n[url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w2-t2gB5sVE]Razorgore the Untamed Legion 7.0.3[/url]", "date": "2016-07-22T23:11:15-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 321, "id": 2356326, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "bettergame", "body": "Just solo'd this as a holy priest(7/24). As stated in earlier posts, the easiest way to solo this is to mc Razorgore and have him stand at the back of the platform the MC orb is on. Have your toon grab all of the agro from the mobs. And then go about your business destroying eggs.\r\n\r\nSo long as you can do some passive agro generation, you will be able to drag all mobs onto yourself. Also I do not remember being able to click on the mc orb, before Razorgore dropped mc to be able to refresh it, I always waited till it dropped and then just clicked on the orb to regain mc . \r\n\r\nThe runningback- I did not have any problems of the mc dropping after I destroy any eggs. But I only destroyed like 2 eggs before the adds started to spawn.", "date": "2016-07-24T15:32:27-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Is there a limit on the number of adds that come in? As a hunter, I am running into serious issues doing this fight, as I really have no passive threat generation beyond killing stuff.", "creationdate": "2016-07-25T09:14:12-05:00", "id": 954413, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2356326, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "serra2", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "There is a limit, but if you kill any of them they continue to spawn till that number is reached. I tested this by allowing them to spawn, and then released Razorgore and Holy Light the adds. It killed them all, but then they started to spawn all over again. I tried to do this as a hunter, and could not passively generate agro. Since Razorgore does not drop agro when not mc'd, it is near impossible to keep him alive.", "creationdate": "2016-08-01T13:59:43-05:00", "id": 956373, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2356326, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bettergame", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "you really don't need passive threat gen, you just need to be patient and wait with Razorgore at the back of the room until you don't see anymore mobs coming out.", "creationdate": "2016-08-21T12:30:50-05:00", "id": 962279, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2356326, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nschneid", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 322, "id": 2358081, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hoplowe", "body": "Easy way to solo at 100:\n\n1. Kill the three guys next to the control orb\n\n2. Take control of Razorgore and make your way to the platform your character is on - do NOT destroy any of the eggs on the way\n\n3. Destroy the two eggs on the platform your character is standing on\n\n4. After destroying those eggs, quickly get as far into the back of the wall as you can with him on that platform, like full on wall clipping\n\n5. [b]Tilt the camera until you have a top down view[/b] - this will make the next step SO MUCH EASIER, because the camera angle stays the same between your character and Razorgore. It's way faster and easier to find the control orb within the sea of mobs that spawn when you're looking directly down rather than from the side\n\n6. Take control of Razorgore and let the mind control spell channel complete at least four times. This will draw out all the mobs that spawn and concentrate them around your character. You have a second or two to click the orb and restart the mind control before Razorgore is in aggro range of the mobs. Be sure to move him back to the back after each channel.\n\n7. After four complete channels, all the mobs should have spawned. On the fifth channel, take Razorgore around them and begin destroying eggs, but keep an eye on the duration of the spell\n\n8. Before the channel runs out, be sure to tilt the camera directly overhead to take over again faster, then keep destroying eggs as Razorgore\n\n9. Once all the eggs are destroyed, run around the room and wait for all the spawned mobs to vanish before one-shotting Razorgore, or there's a chance he'll despawn IIRC\n\n10. Despair that that mog you wanted hasn't dropped\n\n- There's a hard limit of how many mobs get spawned, but they spawn to replace each other on death. [b]Don't kill any spawning mobs[/b], it's a pointless exercise and they don't even drop loot\n- One or two mobs following you is fine, you'll kill all the eggs long before they kill you. More than four, consider forcing a wipe rather than suffer through dying as you walk to the last egg \n- If you screw up, it takes about a minute or two for the eggs and Razorgore to respawn\n- Keep calm; the most difficult part of this whole thing is finding the control orb when you're surrounded by 40-ish angry enemies. Once you have a grip on the timing you'll be just fine", "date": "2016-07-28T07:01:47-05:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I've been clicking on the orb from below and it makes it much easier when the channel drops to pick it back up again and it's usually only taking two channeling sessions to get all the adds out to begin egg smashing.", "creationdate": "2016-07-29T08:51:52-05:00", "id": 955534, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2358081, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Thunderpu55", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This strategy worked like a charm! Thanks for posting it.", "creationdate": "2016-08-03T15:31:57-05:00", "id": 956884, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2358081, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ghostduckie", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Platinum level hint!!!", "creationdate": "2016-08-06T01:06:13-05:00", "id": 957397, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2358081, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ASN85692", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just in case you're a doofus like me, the platform you want to park Razorgore on is the SAME one with the orb. I misinterpreted the instructions above and was running him all the way back across the room to the other platform, where he kept drawing aggro. After an hour and a 200g repair bill, I watched a YouTube video and saw my mistake. It was smooth like butter after that.", "creationdate": "2016-08-07T22:10:59-05:00", "id": 957916, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2358081, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mrkorb", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This was amazingly helpful. Just like to add that you probably don't have to wait four full channels. Just keep an eye on the spawn locations and wait until mobs stop coming. Also, you can destroy a few eggs before the mobs start spawning and its ok. Just high-tail to the sweet spot when they start spawning.", "creationdate": "2016-08-21T12:38:44-05:00", "id": 962282, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2358081, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nschneid", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-07-28T07:03:45-05:00", 1, "Hoplowe"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 323, "id": 2363235, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "pat33", "body": "[b]7.03 Easy way ever.[/b]\r\n\r\n1) Kill the 3 mobs on the platform [b]then jump down[/b] and activate the orb from downstairs.\r\n\r\n2) Destroy [b]7 eggs around[/b] (special button) your character [b]THEN kill the 2 eggs on the platform[/b] don't aggro any mobs in boss form.\r\n\r\n3)Get the [b]boss head[/b] into the [b]wall [/b]alcove on the plaform where there is the orb AND WAIT about 2 mindcontrols (MC) [b]until mobs stop spwaning[/b].\r\n3.1) don't aggro any mobs , \r\n3.2)after each mindcontrol [b]click the orb ASAP[/b] and get the boss at the same position very fast so he doesn't aggro mobs.\r\n\r\n4) [b]Start killing all eggs[/b]: if the Mindcontrol end be sure to get the boss very far from mobs so you retake MC with no aggro from boss.\r\n\r\n(Killing 7 eggs at the start is easy because mobs don't spawn in this time frame)", "date": "2016-08-08T13:21:41-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Worth to mention: Do NOT actively break the orb channeling to renew the cast. Wait until the cast runs out and then click again. This will always reset the aggro from mobs attacking the boss.", "creationdate": "2016-08-26T05:38:48-05:00", "id": 963355, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2363235, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Caylindra", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Over-complicating matters with this strategy... ignore what Pat33 says... it may work but completely takes too long and is unnecessary. Simply put, kill 3 adds up top and jump down, take control of Razorgore, start killing eggs... as you get adds, you can now click on the orb while in Razorgore from anywhere in the room and it De-Aggros all mobs on Razorgore... this can be done every 6 seconds... so no need for the above strategy, just take over Razorgore, kill eggs as you please, click on the orb and de-aggro mobs as needed (it refreshes control timer too)... its too easy now...", "creationdate": "2016-11-11T18:04:49-06:00", "id": 1007735, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2363235, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wolfshanze", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 324, "id": 2374612, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "rexxan", "body": "[b]Solo any class 7.0.3 easiest and fastest way[/b]\n\n1. Go to the mindcontrolling orb from underneath the platform and click it.\n2. When you get control of Razor, start destroying eggs immediately at the opposite platform.\n3. Continue destroying eggs near the walls (where adds spawn).\n4. When you get too many mobs on Razor and you notice him dropping HP fast, right-click razor's icon, dismiss him and mindcontrol after 3-4 seconds to make him lose aggro.\n\nI finished all eggs with 60% hp left on razor, pretty calm. Good luck!", "date": "2016-08-28T12:08:10-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-08-28T12:09:36-05:00", 3, "rexxan"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 325, "id": 2380926, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zityrian", "body": "The guides here don't apply anymore.\r\n\r\nRazorgore gets aggro and keeps aggro no matter what you do. Died 4 times today.\r\n\r\nIf Blizz doesn't fix this, it won't be possible to anymore solo for non-healing classes.", "date": "2016-09-01T17:55:57-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "never exit razorgore, just click the orb while youre controlling him after adds start attacking you", "creationdate": "2016-09-11T06:10:27-05:00", "id": 974881, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2380926, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "TheShadowX", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If i clicked Razorgore orb while in Razorgore he would take mob aggro but attack me but i'd still be in his body. The adds come out faster it seems, so just as they were coming out i redid orb and then let it die out and clicked it again before he got close. Once the last couple adds came out and were attacking me i started crushing eggs and i would let the channel run out before clicking it again.", "creationdate": "2016-09-30T17:13:24-05:00", "id": 989183, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2380926, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "smaugington", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The new post-Legion strategy is pretty simple... 1) Kill three adds on platform near orb, jump down... 2) click on orb, start killing eggs... 3) as adds start to get on Razorgore, turn around and click on the orb FROM ANYWHERE IN THE ROOM while you're still in Razorgore... this does two things... one it de-aggro's all adds currently on you, and two, it refreshes the control timer on Razorgore... there's about a 6-second countdown on when you can do this again, so basically, every 6 seconds or so, you can get rid of any adds on Razorgore and never lose control... its super easy now!", "creationdate": "2016-11-11T18:02:27-06:00", "id": 1007734, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2380926, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wolfshanze", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 326, "id": 2389650, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "greycobalt", "body": "If you happen to be a Pally, this is trivial now. Switch to Holy and spec in Aura of Mercy. Anytime you have more than a mob or two on Razor, run near your character. The heal will pull everyone off you.", "date": "2016-09-06T18:50:15-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 327, "id": 2399355, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "plethorex", "body": "This is incredibly simple if you know one trick: [b]you can click the orb of control while controlling Razorgore from anywhere in the room.[/b]  Pan your camera so you can see the orb, if Razorgore gets aggro on anything, click the orb.  It'll drop aggro onto your character and you can go back to destroying eggs.", "date": "2016-09-12T16:33:16-05:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I just tried this I found it tricky Razorgore had 11% health left on the last egg you will have to kill the adds at the orb from time to time and dismiss often once adds start attacking Razorgore....good luck!!", "creationdate": "2016-09-18T08:07:10-05:00", "id": 980699, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2399355, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "darkanimeangel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "What plethorex says works great. Just click on the orb from anywhere in the room while controlling Razorgore. It will pulse the mind control very quickly, and all the mobs that have run to attack Razorgore, will run off to attack you. It's impossible for the mobs to do damage to your character due to the huge level disparity.", "creationdate": "2016-09-18T15:33:09-05:00", "id": 980971, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2399355, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Das3", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I don't know if this trick has always been possible, but thanks so much for bringing it to my attention.", "creationdate": "2016-09-25T17:32:33-05:00", "id": 985973, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2399355, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "codeytherhino", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "To add to this, make sure to turn off enemy healthbars!", "creationdate": "2016-10-01T00:22:23-05:00", "id": 989362, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2399355, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rybin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This needs to be the top comment for this fight. Worked like a dream!!!", "creationdate": "2017-01-30T14:03:57-06:00", "id": 1029222, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2399355, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "VSUReaper", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 328, "id": 2407024, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ArchironDW", "body": "Not sure what people saying the orb thing is tricky or doesn't work are talking about. Solo'd this just now on my 108 outlaw rogue, it's pretty much impossible to not solo this unless you go and purposefully 1-shot Razorgore.\r\n\r\n-Take control of Razorgore\r\n-I worked from left (my platform with the orb) to right, clearing the outside edges then in the middle\r\n-If you get aggro on Razor, click the orb from a distance and everything drops off. Just make sure not to try and click it again before the 7 second debuff has elapsed.", "date": "2016-09-18T16:07:33-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 329, "id": 2407312, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Killerzeus", "body": "I see there's already plenty of video solo guides on this boss, but a lot of people have said that my guide have helped them when others haven't, and that it's by far the easiest solo guide they have seen, so here it goes: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KoA3rBluI8A\r\n\r\nIn short my strategy is to kill the orb mobs, stand under the platform, and reset his aggro by clicking the orb while still channeling the mind-control orb. Using this strategy, Razorgore's health should never get to lower than 70-90% HP, and is one of the easiest bosses in BWL rather than the hardest. I hope this will help those who have a problem with this boss and needed to see a quick and easy understandable guide.", "date": "2016-09-18T21:46:17-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This it the way to go... do this strategy, ignore all others... super fast, super easy, no tricks, no certain classes... just use this strategy, its now easier than prior to Legion.", "creationdate": "2016-11-11T18:06:36-06:00", "id": 1007736, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2407312, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wolfshanze", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Finally. Give this hero more kudos, please!", "creationdate": "2016-12-29T16:08:28-06:00", "id": 1019841, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2407312, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Teebee2010", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 330, "id": 2425232, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Astrielyn", "body": "A little tip for druid players and a fun fact: when you get close to your character while controlling the boss, your Ysera's Gift will heal it if your health bar is full(it is for most of the time at level 110). Saved me from a wipe, otherwise I'd have died just before last two eggs", "date": "2016-10-09T19:37:40-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Awesome. Worked 100%! :D Started with the eggs furthest away, worked my way towards the summoning rod thingy. Boss never dropped below 50% while he was close-ish to me, made the fight just a boring chore with guaranteed victory instead of a frustrating gamble. :P Thanks so much for this!", "creationdate": "2016-10-10T16:07:56-05:00", "id": 994649, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2425232, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Hexatomon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 331, "id": 2435461, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "nagi603", "body": "The encounter seems to have changed a bit: some adds will not fall off Razorgore, and when you click on the MC orb, it sometimes removes the MC and while you try to reclick it, Razorgore will continue to attack the adds remaining on him, gaining aggro and losing health.", "date": "2016-10-27T02:16:07-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 332, "id": 2438315, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "IMissThottbot", "body": "This appears impossible for Fire Mages to solo now, as of Legion.\n\n1. Razorgore continously gets aggro even when not MC'd.\n2. Ignite passively spreads, which kills him.\n\nThe issue I'm having is that I'll MC him, clear about half the eggs, then clear the adds. However, I CANNOT AoE anything even remotely near him. I have to stand there casting scorch over and over, and at that point mobs are spawning faster than I can cast, and aggroing onto Razorgore instead of me. It's extremely frustrating, because 90% of the time if I try anything to kill the adds I'll accidentally kill Razorgore, too.", "date": "2016-10-31T19:40:25-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This was driving me crazy. Switched to frost and suddenly the orb click method worked.", "creationdate": "2016-11-02T00:28:50-05:00", "id": 1004265, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2438315, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Starlin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-10-31T19:40:59-05:00", 1, "IMissThottbot"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 333, "id": 2439581, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Bejorgen", "body": "After struggling with the back-of-the-wall method that worked in 7.0.3, I had much better luck when I simply ran up to the orb (from below) and grabbed control instantly, without bothering to kill the three adds there. Thereafter, re-clicking the orb to refresh the MC worked consistently; mobs would instantly drop off Razorgore and attack me. Possibly just coincidence, but I'll try it again next week and see.", "date": "2016-11-03T11:43:30-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This worked for me as well. Killing the three adds seemed to break the way aggro worked for the rest of the encounter. Leaving them alive made almost all the other mobs that spawn aggro straight onto me instead of Razorgore.", "creationdate": "2016-11-03T14:34:22-05:00", "id": 1004902, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2439581, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "njdss4", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed, this method worked very well for me too!", "creationdate": "2017-02-08T19:09:33-06:00", "id": 1031282, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2439581, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "jhml", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 334, "id": 2441648, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "968833", "body": "Tried to solo as a Ret and i got wrecked but when i switched to Prot the adds seems to race towards me instead of Razorgore which meant i could kill all the eggs with ease.\r\n\r\nNot sure if tanks have some aura that makes adds instinctively run to them cause it sure as hell helped!", "date": "2016-11-07T17:28:02-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Tried this just now with zero success (about 10 wipes), less than 24 hours after your post, and before the scheduled server restarts. In protection paladin spec and finding it virtually impossible to pull aggro off the boss without individually targetting the mobs attacking him (which becomes impractical as the swarm builds). Add to that the old trick of using trinkets that spawn temporary pets no longer seems to work, either, and I am super frustrated at the moment \ud83d\ude24", "creationdate": "2016-11-08T06:07:48-06:00", "id": 1006604, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2441648, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "trest", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 335, "id": 2449287, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hoplowe", "body": "So my old comment's had a few people saying it didn't work and I've since refined my method so I figured I'd post an updated version. Literally just finished soloing this guy, his body hasn't even despawned yet. \n\n1. Kill the three mobs by the orb. (edit, or don't. Your choice. I do it out of habit)\n2. Click the orb, taking control of Razorgore.\n3. Take Razorgore across the room to the platform your character is on with the orb. Attack only the two eggs that are on this platform with you.[u] Do not attack any eggs on the way there. [/u]\n4. Park Razorgore so close to the wall at the back of that platform that he clips through it. \n5. When the timer runs out the first time, quickly leap off the platform. You can still reach the orb, so click on it again and put Razorgore back in the wall. This drags the mobs who've spawned down with you and away from Razorgore.\n6. After two/three full channels, all the mobs that are going to spawn should have spawned. [u]Do not attack them at all, as yourself or as Razorgore. [/u]\n7. Start destroying eggs, reclicking the control orb as needed. \n8. When all the eggs are destroyed, allow all the spawned mobs to leave the room before engaging Razorgore, because IIRC there's a chance his kill will not count if you kill him before the final phase of the encounter officially starts on their exit. \n9. Collect your loot, dying a little inside as the mog you wanted didn't drop again. \n\nYou should only kill a few things in this room - the three mobs at the start possibly and Razorgore. There is [u]no[/u] point in killing the summoned mobs and if you're 110 you have literally nothing to worry about. You'll just summon more.\n\nDoing this method, half-assed as I was on youtube in the other window, I ended up with only a single mage following me around, which left me at a comfortable 75% HP on Razorgore. Practicing this method - especially the jump - might give you more. Save yourself time and force a wipe at three by attacking Razorgore. \n\nIf you screw up, it takes about a minute for everything to respawn. \n\nOnce again - [i][u][b]DO NOT KILL THE SUMMONED MOBS. [/b][/u][/i]", "date": "2016-11-28T14:48:22-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "After wiping countless times trying to kill the adds to get them off Razorgore I tried this and got done in one try. Note that if you get a few adds on Razor up on the platform you can hit esc to stop the orb channel to dump agro and quickly reclick the orb.", "creationdate": "2017-03-18T09:01:44-05:00", "id": 1037950, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2449287, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Laconia", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This is the best, most fail-proof method. I've had success with the standard \"click the orb to drop aggro\" method before, but I've also not been able to always drop all the mobs aggro leading to a wipe. This method is a bit longer, but it's failproof.", "creationdate": "2017-04-24T09:43:50-05:00", "id": 1047505, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2449287, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wownomo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-11-28T14:49:23-06:00", 1, "Hoplowe"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 336, "id": 2453801, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Elentil", "body": "To solo this\r\n\r\n1.Kill the adds around the orb\r\n2. [b][u]Jump down[/u][/b] from the balcony\r\n3. Use the orb\r\n\r\nNow whnever you get adds on Razorgore reuse the orb and the adds will atk you char, and cos of step 2 all the adds will be down and wont obstruct the orb :)", "date": "2016-12-14T20:43:25-06:00", "rating": 47, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thank you a lot!", "creationdate": "2016-12-16T15:40:42-06:00", "id": 1016906, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2453801, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "r0estir0bbe", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Best guide ever!", "creationdate": "2017-06-11T20:51:22-05:00", "id": 1056372, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2453801, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Ejde", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thanks! I also destroyed all of the eggs. When I did that all the adds despawned and I could simply kill the boss without dying myself.", "creationdate": "2018-05-13T05:23:33-05:00", "id": 1112163, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2453801, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Vlaeko", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You sir, deserve a lot more upvotes! Thank you)", "creationdate": "2018-10-18T06:38:45-05:00", "id": 1151144, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2453801, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Slipkorn7", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 337, "id": 2454747, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "ilostmahbucket", "body": "For any class to solo with ease, you can reclick the Orb of Domination [b]from anywhere in the room[/b] once you control Razorgore, removing aggro from him. Simply watch your 10s debuff.", "date": "2016-12-18T11:57:57-06:00", "rating": 28, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The part I wasn't getting from the other comments is that you can click on the orb when you are Razorgore from anywhere in the room. The fight was absolutely trivial at that point.", "creationdate": "2017-03-14T14:37:52-05:00", "id": 1037369, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2454747, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Elysoun", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 338, "id": 2468337, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dawnrider", "body": "This is no longer easy to do with 7.1.5. About half way through you have to click the orb pretty much right when your debuff wears off, you get 2 maybe 3 eggs per click. He doesn't drop full aggro on the adds, and if you don't to it so often he will die before all the eggs do.", "date": "2017-01-30T05:04:16-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not true. It's absolutely trivial if you only click the orb to drop aggro as detailed in some of the other comments.", "creationdate": "2017-01-31T02:06:15-06:00", "id": 1029371, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2468337, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Cakechart", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 339, "id": 2468930, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "grootiez", "body": "I wish there was an option to skip this boss.", "date": "2017-02-01T11:25:59-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "or for him to not kill everyone if he dies before the eggs are destroyed. Literally every other pre-Draenor boss is soloable. (even ones like Galakras that required two people). Some of us want the transmog off this bastard. And sometimes a girl just wants to run-shoot-loot-move on", "creationdate": "2017-04-01T00:45:09-05:00", "id": 1040626, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2468930, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "NinjaFlibble", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 340, "id": 2479651, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "BriannahHunt", "body": "This fight is definitely more difficult, however this method works like a charm! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fnUd6aAgTHs It takes advantage of placement and spawn cap. I just tried it and walked around with zero aggro destroying eggs!", "date": "2017-03-26T18:35:45-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 341, "id": 2482480, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nevermoor", "body": "It was [i]incredibly [/i]easy to do this today (2 April 2017).  I was playing my 110 Arcane Mage, but class and spec don't matter.  Just kill the adds on the platform near the orb, jump down from the platform, click on the orb to control Razorgore, and start destroying eggs.  Eventually, adds will start attacking him, but all you have to do is click on the orb again (and [i]you can do this from anywhere in the room, without losing control of the boss[/i]).  This transfers aggro back to you.  Continue destroying eggs.  Rinse and repeat as necessary.", "date": "2017-04-02T20:01:21-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Worked for me, finally can solo this.", "creationdate": "2017-04-03T08:42:50-05:00", "id": 1041386, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2482480, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Quorgyle", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Works sometimes, but not all the time. They key to winning this boss is to transfer agro from your pet back to yourself once you have three or four adds on you. Your pet just can't soak the damage. But if you click on the orb and it doesn't transfer agro, you're gonna have a bad time. Only fix i could find was to die and try again.", "creationdate": "2017-04-15T20:17:22-05:00", "id": 1045418, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2482480, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "colarama", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thank you so much for this comment ! i was getting so irritated dying on the last 2 eggs because i couldn't get the aggro to drop off of him! This worked great ! i got all of the eggs taken care of and he had over 50% health left.", "creationdate": "2017-05-24T12:10:52-05:00", "id": 1053016, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2482480, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Selinai", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thanks, very good strat!", "creationdate": "2017-06-10T16:52:04-05:00", "id": 1056163, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2482480, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "BowWow", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 342, "id": 2486648, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Malachi68", "body": "I often wonder why people continuously write comments along the lines of \"it was easy to solo for my level 110 mage\".\r\n\r\nOf course it's easy to solo a Tier 2 raid! You're freakin' level 110! No strategy needed...\r\n\r\nI'm trying to do this as a level 70 Warlock and it was very easy to kill Razorgore and then get killed myself. Why? Because I had my demon pet active and that makes it impossible to complete this task. There are approximately one gazillion comments about how easily a level 110 character can solo Blackwing Lair and only one comment (way down the bottom, thanks ipic909) about the pet problem. So:\r\n\r\n[b]Hunters and Warlocks[/b]: you need to dismiss your pets in order to kill Razorgore.", "date": "2017-04-13T14:23:43-05:00", "rating": 23, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Also counts for frost mages if you have a water elemental.", "creationdate": "2017-04-17T05:38:20-05:00", "id": 1045817, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2486648, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Darkoli1987", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 343, "id": 2496399, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Shardsy", "body": "Solo at 7.1.5\nGetting tired of dying I searched for an other way and found this video = fail safe\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fnUd6aAgTHs\n\nAs he says, wait till all adds has spawned. I didn't count them but wowwiki says it's 52 in all.\nWhen I had destroyed all eggs Razorgore was at 71%. (Edit: bad rng with mobs can make it a close call)\nIf you want to break the mc (to have control of when it happens), don't click the orb. Do /dance or so, in that way you don't get the debuff and can retake control immediately.\n\nIf it's hard to see the orb, take the mobs name plates away.", "date": "2017-05-25T07:04:45-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2017-06-01T14:06:38-05:00", 3, "Shardsy"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 344, "id": 2497404, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "PlainWhiteSocks", "body": "Here's how I do it.  \nKill the mobs on the platform. \nClick on the orb.\nControl Razorgore and destroy the eggs.\nWhen Razorgore's health gets low move him next to your character.\nTarget Razorgore and use a bandage on him.  This breaks your control of Razorgore.\nHe will be healed and agro goes to you.\nClick on the orb again to control Razorgore and destroy eggs.\n\n\nIf you're a class with a HoT then you won't need the bandage.", "date": "2017-05-30T01:52:43-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2017-05-30T02:38:29-05:00", 1, "PlainWhiteSocks"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 345, "id": 2498339, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Altiera", "body": "Ok hunters if you want to solo this with absolutely no problem and no hassle with reading all these previous instructions I have the perfect, easiest solo out there. I just did it. Go up to the orb. kill the 3 ads there then click the orb. soon as you have razorgore hit play dead. save the eggs and then kill razorgore. I finally tried this after dying 25 million times! It worked first time like a charm. He doesn't take any damage.", "date": "2017-06-04T21:29:27-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "FOR HUNTERS: Dismiss pets. Kill three adds on platform on left. Click orb, which takes control of Razorgore. While controlling Razorgore, run around the room and destroy all the eggs. As adds spawn, reclick the orb to shed the adds off Razorgore. When all the eggs are destroyed, kill Razorgore.", "creationdate": "2017-09-10T17:16:23-05:00", "id": 1073447, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2498339, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Chilcoot", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 346, "id": 2500676, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "blademage727", "body": "Just did the encounter. Looks like there was a stealth change in today's patch (7.2.5) that made [spell=19873] an instant cast spell now, not a 3 second cast. Makes the encounter absurdly easier to solo. Yay for stealth quality of life changes! =D", "date": "2017-06-13T20:03:43-05:00", "rating": 29, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It really is one of the undocumented changes in 7.2.5 patch: http://www.wowhead.com/news=265858/patch-7-2-5-undocumented-changes", "creationdate": "2017-06-14T12:56:41-05:00", "id": 1056931, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2500676, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "minduim0", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can also cast this while moving.", "creationdate": "2017-08-21T05:23:37-05:00", "id": 1067949, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2500676, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Raa007", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2017-06-13T20:04:55-05:00", 1, "blademage727"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 347, "id": 2500866, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Bonyfoot", "body": "NEW IN 7.2.5: Razorgore the Untamed now destroys all the eggs at once.", "date": "2017-06-14T10:59:16-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not quite - you still have to go around and destroy every egg, one at a time, but as Arhippa's comment says, there is no cooldown on the egg destruction ability, so you can go from egg to egg without pause and get it done without worrying about anything else.", "creationdate": "2017-06-15T13:48:39-05:00", "id": 1057197, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2500866, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Martika", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
