{"commentv2": 1, "number": 353, "id": 2502616, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mehetabel", "body": "As of patch 7.2.5, Razorgore's \"Destroy Egg\" ability is an instant cast. You can solo this quickly now, destroying all the eggs in less than a minute. I did still follow the strat of jumping down from the platform before clicking the orb, just to keep all the mobs in a neat pile, but I didn't need to kill any of them as the eggs were gone within one round of MC. Much easier!", "date": "2017-06-20T12:17:36-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 354, "id": 2503029, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Foxpaw", "body": "I believe this fight has been patched in 7.2.5 to be [i]dramatically[/i] simpler, with just one tiny change; Destroy Egg is now instant cast instead of a 3 second cast, meaning not only is the cooldown half of what it effectively was when it was a 3 second cast time, but it can also be used while moving, and I believe will even destroy multiple eggs if they're closely grouped. I'd been using the 'jump down and click then run him into the wall' method but this week, found that now it's no longer necessary. You can clear 70% or so of the eggs before the adds even spawn and destroy the rest of them before they do close to lethal damage to him.", "date": "2017-06-21T12:16:04-05:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "yes I can confirm this also, old strats are gone for sure.", "creationdate": "2017-06-26T10:15:30-05:00", "id": 1059686, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2503029, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "pat33", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 355, "id": 2504657, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zaphiroc53", "body": "Patch 7.2.5 changed his 'Destroy Egg' ability to be instant cast which trivialises the encounter.", "date": "2017-06-28T06:38:10-05:00", "rating": 47, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "And can be used while moving.", "creationdate": "2017-08-21T05:22:59-05:00", "id": 1067948, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2504657, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Raa007", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 356, "id": 2520316, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "cisconetdude", "body": "I tryed to solo this dungeon this morning and the Orb of Domination is clickable but does not click.  This is now bugged and you can not run the dungeon.  Did this on a 110 DK.\n\nThere is a bug in the encounter now.  you can not kill the 3 guys controlling razorgore.  you need to just use the orb and let them aggro on you.  then the encounter works.", "date": "2017-09-06T07:58:08-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "confirmed today, clickable but not able to activate, bug submitted.", "creationdate": "2018-04-12T06:30:49-05:00", "id": 1108221, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2520316, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "oneevilchef", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "But, as a hunter, dismissed pets and was able to activate orb, there seems to be an issue with pets.", "creationdate": "2018-04-12T06:34:26-05:00", "id": 1108222, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2520316, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "oneevilchef", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2017-09-06T08:11:13-05:00", 1, "cisconetdude"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 357, "id": 2528064, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "warp9pnt9", "body": "I had no \"Exit Vehicle\" button anywhere on my user interface.  I just ran around and randomly popped out of control, so I just clicked the orb again after Razorgore killed the mobs stalking him.  Once I stopped accidentally killing him with my AoE, this was actually simple.  Destroy all eggs and you enter phase 2 and 1-hit him.  Should only need 1 control reset.  According to other posts, you don't even need to exit vehicle, nor need to be near the orb anymore.", "date": "2017-10-05T08:14:11-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 358, "id": 2530070, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Yooper1120", "body": "I need some help with this one...I'm hoping it's just a instance bug.\r\n\r\nI can't destroy any eggs with my player, and when I'm MCing RG he can't destroy any of them either  I don't know what to click in order to initiate the Destroy Egg function.\r\n\r\nWill he destroy eggs automatically if I just point him at them?  Do I have to destroy them one at a time?\r\n\r\nThanks", "date": "2017-10-16T23:09:09-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Nevermind...I didn't realize there were new control buttons at the bottom of the screen. Done deal...easy.", "creationdate": "2017-10-16T23:15:12-05:00", "id": 1080146, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2530070, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Yooper1120", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 359, "id": 2530895, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "ElClintoro", "body": "I just ran the raid and during the Razorgore encounter, I noticed there is no longer a cast time on the destroy egg. I destroyed every egg with a third of the mc channel bar left and only 1 group of adds spawning. Laughably easy now.", "date": "2017-10-21T18:59:20-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed: No cast time and laughably easy now. woot!", "creationdate": "2017-10-24T13:20:29-05:00", "id": 1081347, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2530895, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Haqin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 360, "id": 2543414, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "LEERIE", "body": "Just Solo'd this as a 110 Destruction Warlock - it was extremely easy as of 7.3.2.  \r\n\r\n*Make sure all pets are dismissed. \r\n\r\nEnter and kill the controller on the platform to the left. \r\nClick the orb, you become mind controlled & control Razorgore. \r\nJust go around destroying ALL of the eggs in the room - i just went to each egg and pressed 4. \r\n(I didn't worry about adds, as I had plenty of health.)\r\nOnce all the eggs are destroyed - you can kill the boss. \r\n\r\n:)", "date": "2018-01-01T02:24:29-06:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Ran this as a 110 Ret Pally and this worked perfectly. Thanks!", "creationdate": "2018-08-11T17:20:36-05:00", "id": 1127912, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2543414, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "TheiaDarkHeart", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
